```
if api_key is None:
print("Error: Missing API key. Make sure you have SERPAPI_API_KEY in your environment variables.")
else:
print("API key found, proceeding with targeted verification search...")
print("=" * 80)
print("VERIFYING 2011 ELSEVIER PUBLICATION: 'Extractive Metallurgy of Nickel, Cobalt and Platinum-Group Metals'")
print("=" * 80)

# Define highly specific search queries to verify the publication contains both required processes
verification_queries = [
'"Extractive Metallurgy of Nickel, Cobalt and Platinum-Group Metals" 2011 Elsevier calcination lithium salts automotive catalysts',
'"Extractive Metallurgy of Nickel, Cobalt and Platinum-Group Metals" 2011 bioleaching Acidithiobacillus thiooxidans cobalt',
'"Extractive Metallurgy of Nickel, Cobalt and Platinum-Group Metals" table of contents chapters',
'"Extractive Metallurgy of Nickel, Cobalt and Platinum-Group Metals" 2011 Elsevier review summary',
'Elsevier 2011 "calcination process lithium salts" "spent automotive catalysts" nickel cobalt platinum',
'Elsevier 2011 "two-stage bioleaching" "Acidithiobacillus thiooxidans" "low-grade cobalt ores"',
'"Extractive Metallurgy of Nickel, Cobalt and Platinum-Group Metals" publisher catalog description',
'ScienceDirect "Extractive Metallurgy of Nickel, Cobalt and Platinum-Group Metals" 2011 chapters'
]

print(f"Executing {len(verification_queries)} targeted verification searches...\n")

# Store all verification results
verification_results = []

for i, query in enumerate(verification_queries, 1):
print(f"Verification Search {i}/{len(verification_queries)}: {query}")
print("-" * 60)

# Prepare API request parameters
params = {
"q": query,
"api_key": api_key,
"engine": "google",
"google_domain": "google.com",
"safe": "off",
"num": 15, # Increased number for better coverage
"type": "search"
}

try:
# Make API request to SerpAPI
response = requests.get("https://serpapi.com/search.json", params=params, timeout=30)

if response.status_code == 200:
results = response.json()

if results.get("organic_results"):
print(f"Found {len(results['organic_results'])} results")

# Store results with query context
query_results = {
'query': query,
'results': results['organic_results'],
'search_number': i,
'timestamp': datetime.now().isoformat()
}
verification_results.append(query_results)

# Display and analyze top results for this query
relevant_found = False
for j, result in enumerate(results['organic_results'][:8], 1):
title = result.get('title', 'No title')
link = result.get('link', 'No URL')
snippet = result.get('snippet', 'No snippet')

# Check for highly relevant indicators
title_lower = title.lower()
snippet_lower = snippet.lower()
combined_text = f"{title_lower} {snippet_lower}"

# Key indicators for the specific publication
key_indicators = [
'extractive metallurgy of nickel, cobalt and platinum-group metals',
'calcination process',
'lithium salts',
'automotive catalysts',
'bioleaching',
'acidithiobacillus thiooxidans',
'cobalt ores',
'elsevier',
'2011'
]

matching_indicators = [ind for ind in key_indicators if ind in combined_text]

print(f"\n Result {j}:")
print(f" Title: {title}")
print(f" URL: {link}")
print(f" Snippet: {snippet[:300]}{'...' if len(snippet) > 300 else ''}")

if matching_indicators:
print(f" ‚≠ê MATCHING INDICATORS: {', '.join(matching_indicators)}")
relevant_found = True

# Special attention to publisher sites, academic databases, and book catalogs
if any(domain in link.lower() for domain in ['elsevier', 'sciencedirect', 'springer', 'wiley', 'worldcat', 'amazon', 'google.com/books']):
print(f" üéØ HIGH-PRIORITY SOURCE: Publisher/Academic database result")

if not relevant_found:
print(" No highly relevant results found for this query")

else:
print("No organic results found for this query")
verification_results.append({
'query': query,
'results': [],
'search_number': i,
'timestamp': datetime.now().isoformat()
})
else:
print(f"Error: API request failed with status {response.status_code}: {response.text}")

except Exception as e:
print(f"Error during verification search {i}: {str(e)}")
continue

print("\n")

print("\n" + "=" * 80)
print("VERIFICATION ANALYSIS SUMMARY")
print("=" * 80)

# Save all verification results to workspace for detailed analysis
timestamp = datetime.now().strftime("%Y%m%d_%H%M%S")
results_file = f"workspace/elsevier_2011_verification_results_{timestamp}.json"

with open(results_file, 'w', encoding='utf-8') as f:
json.dump({
'publication_title': 'Extractive Metallurgy of Nickel, Cobalt and Platinum-Group Metals',
'publication_year': '2011',
'publisher': 'Elsevier',
'verification_timestamp': timestamp,
'total_queries': len(verification_queries),
'queries_executed': verification_queries,
'verification_results': verification_results
}, f, indent=2, ensure_ascii=False)

print(f"Verification results saved to: {results_file}")

# Analyze findings
total_results = sum(len(query_result['results']) for query_result in verification_results)
print(f"Total verification results collected: {total_results}")

# Look for direct publication matches
direct_matches = []
calcination_mentions = []
bioleaching_mentions = []
elsevier_2011_matches = []

for query_result in verification_results:
for result in query_result['results']:
title = result.get('title', '').lower()
snippet = result.get('snippet', '').lower()
link = result.get('link', '').lower()
combined = f"{title} {snippet} {link}"

# Direct publication title matches
if 'extractive metallurgy of nickel, cobalt and platinum-group metals' in combined:
direct_matches.append({
'query': query_result['query'],
'title': result.get('title'),
'link': result.get('link'),
'snippet': result.get('snippet')
})

# Calcination process mentions
if 'calcination' in combined and ('lithium' in combined or 'automotive' in combined or 'catalyst' in combined):
calcination_mentions.append({
'query': query_result['query'],
'title': result.get('title'),
'link': result.get('link'),
'snippet': result.get('snippet')
})

# Bioleaching mentions
if 'bioleaching' in combined and ('acidithiobacillus' in combined or 'thiooxidans' in combined or 'cobalt' in combined):
bioleaching_mentions.append({
'query': query_result['query'],
'title': result.get('title'),
'link': result.get('link'),
'snippet': result.get('snippet')
})

# Elsevier 2011 matches
if 'elsevier' in combined and '2011' in combined:
elsevier_2011_matches.append({
'query': query_result['query'],
'title': result.get('title'),
'link': result.get('link'),
'snippet': result.get('snippet')
})

print(f"\nüìä VERIFICATION FINDINGS:")
print(f"Direct publication title matches: {len(direct_matches)}")
print(f"Calcination process mentions: {len(calcination_mentions)}")
print(f"Bioleaching process mentions: {len(bioleaching_mentions)}")
print(f"Elsevier 2011 matches: {len(elsevier_2011_matches)}")

if direct_matches:
print(f"\nüéØ DIRECT PUBLICATION MATCHES FOUND:")
for i, match in enumerate(direct_matches[:5], 1):
print(f" {i}. {match['title']}")
print(f" URL: {match['link']}")
print(f" Query: {match['query']}")
print(f" Snippet: {match['snippet'][:200]}...")
print()

if calcination_mentions:
print(f"\n‚öóÔ∏è CALCINATION PROCESS MENTIONS:")
for i, mention in enumerate(calcination_mentions[:3], 1):
print(f" {i}. {mention['title']}")
print(f" Snippet: {mention['snippet'][:150]}...")
print()

if bioleaching_mentions:
print(f"\nü¶† BIOLEACHING PROCESS MENTIONS:")
for i, mention in enumerate(bioleaching_mentions[:3], 1):
print(f" {i}. {mention['title']}")
print(f" Snippet: {mention['snippet'][:150]}...")
print()

print(f"\nüìã VERIFICATION STATUS:")
if direct_matches and (calcination_mentions or bioleaching_mentions):
print("‚úÖ PUBLICATION IDENTIFIED with some process mentions")
print(" - Direct publication matches found")
print(" - Some relevant process mentions detected")
print(" - Requires deeper analysis of specific chapters/content")
elif direct_matches:
print("‚ö†Ô∏è PUBLICATION IDENTIFIED but limited process verification")
print(" - Direct publication matches found")
print(" - Limited specific process mentions")
print(" - May require access to full publication content")
else:
print("‚ùå LIMITED VERIFICATION RESULTS")
print(" - No direct publication title matches")
print(" - May need alternative search strategies")
print(" - Publication may not be widely indexed or accessible")

print(f"\nDetailed verification data saved to: {results_file}")
print("Ready for next phase: detailed content analysis if publication is confirmed.")
```

import os import requests import json from datetime import datetime import time # Create workspace directory if it doesn't exist if not os.path.exists('workspace'): os.makedirs('workspace') print('=== WHITNEY MUSEUM 2022 PHOTOGRAPHY ACQUISITIONS SEARCH ===') print('Objective: Find photographs from Whitney Museum 2022 acquisitions showing person holding book') print('Note: Previous research indicates accession 2022.128 is a Calder sculpture, not a photograph\n') # Get SerpAPI key from environment variables api_key = os.getenv("SERPAPI_API_KEY") if api_key is None: print("Warning: No SERPAPI_API_KEY found. Will attempt direct web searches only.") use_google_search = False else: print("API key found, will use comprehensive Google search approach") use_google_search = True print('\n=== PHASE 1: DIRECT WHITNEY MUSEUM WEBSITE SEARCH ===') print('Attempting to access Whitney Museum collection and acquisition pages...') # Whitney Museum official URLs to try whitney_urls = [ 'https://whitney.org/collection', 'https://whitney.org/collection/search', 'https://whitney.org/about/acquisitions', 'https://whitney.org/collection/search?year=2022', 'https://whitney.org/press', 'https://whitney.org/press/2022', 'https://whitney.org/collection/search?medium=photography', 'https://whitney.org/collection/search?medium=photograph' ] headers = { 'User-Agent': 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 10.0; Win64; x64) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/91.0.4472.124 Safari/537.36' } whitney_results = [] for i, url in enumerate(whitney_urls, 1): print(f'\nTrying Whitney URL {i}/{len(whitney_urls)}: {url}') try: response = requests.get(url, headers=headers, timeout=20) print(f'Response status: {response.status_code}') if response.status_code == 200: print(f'‚úì Successfully accessed {url}') # Save the response for analysis filename = f'workspace/whitney_direct_search_{i}.html' with open(filename, 'w', encoding='utf-8') as f: f.write(response.text) print(f' Saved response to: {filename}') print(f' Content length: {len(response.text)} characters') # Quick analysis of content content_lower = response.text.lower() # Look for 2022 acquisition indicators acquisition_indicators = ['2022', 'acquisition', 'photograph', 'photography', 'portrait', 'book'] found_indicators = [ind for ind in acquisition_indicators if ind in content_lower] if found_indicators: print(f' Found indicators: {found_indicators}') # Look for specific terms if '2022' in content_lower and ('photograph' in content_lower or 'photography' in content_lower): print(' *** CONTAINS 2022 + PHOTOGRAPHY REFERENCES ***') if 'book' in content_lower and 'photograph' in content_lower: print(' *** CONTAINS BOOK + PHOTOGRAPH REFERENCES ***') whitney_results.append({ 'url': url, 'status': response.status_code, 'filename': filename, 'content_length': len(response.text), 'indicators_found': found_indicators }) else: print(f'‚úó Failed - Status: {response.status_code}') whitney_results.append({ 'url': url, 'status': response.status_code, 'error': f'HTTP {response.status_code}' }) except Exception as e: print(f'‚úó Error: {str(e)}') whitney_results.append({ 'url': url, 'error': str(e) }) time.sleep(2) # Be respectful to servers print(f'\n=== WHITNEY DIRECT SEARCH SUMMARY ===') successful_whitney = [r for r in whitney_results if r.get('status') == 200] print(f'Successfully accessed {len(successful_whitney)} of {len(whitney_urls)} Whitney Museum URLs') for result in successful_whitney: print(f'‚úì {result["url"]} -> {result["filename"]} ({len(result.get("indicators_found", []))} indicators)') if use_google_search: print('\n=== PHASE 2: COMPREHENSIVE GOOGLE SEARCH ===') print('Executing targeted searches for Whitney 2022 photography acquisitions...') # Comprehensive search queries focusing on Whitney 2022 photography acquisitions search_queries = [ 'Whitney Museum 2022 acquisitions photographs person holding book', 'Whitney Museum American Art 2022 photograph portrait book', '"Whitney Museum" 2022 acquisitions photography collection', 'Whitney Museum press release 2022 photography acquisitions', '"Whitney Museum" 2022 "new acquisitions" photograph portrait', 'Whitney Museum 2022 contemporary photography collection book', 'site:whitney.org 2022 acquisitions photography photograph', 'Whitney Museum 2022 portrait photography "holding book"', '"Whitney Museum of American Art" 2022 photography collection news', 'Whitney Museum 2022 acquisitions art news photography portrait' ] google_results = [] for i, query in enumerate(search_queries, 1): print(f'\nGoogle Search {i}/{len(search_queries)}: "{query}"') print('-' * 60) params = { "q": query, "api_key": api_key, "engine": "google", "google_domain": "google.com", "safe": "off", "num": 12, "type": "search" } try: response = requests.get("https://serpapi.com/search.json", params=params, timeout=30) if response.status_code == 200: results = response.json() if results.get("organic_results"): print(f'Found {len(results["organic_results"])} results') query_results = { 'query': query, 'results': results['organic_results'], 'search_number': i, 'timestamp': datetime.now().isoformat() } google_results.append(query_results) # Analyze top results for this query relevant_found = False for j, result in enumerate(results['organic_results'][:8], 1): title = result.get('title', 'No title') link = result.get('link', 'No URL') snippet = result.get('snippet', 'No snippet') # Check for highly relevant indicators title_lower = title.lower() snippet_lower = snippet.lower() link_lower = link.lower() combined_text = f"{title_lower} {snippet_lower} {link_lower}" # Key indicators for Whitney 2022 photography acquisitions key_indicators = [ 'whitney museum', '2022', 'acquisition', 'photograph', 'photography', 'portrait', 'book', 'collection', 'american art' ] matching_indicators = [ind for ind in key_indicators if ind in combined_text] print(f'\n Result {j}:') print(f' Title: {title}') print(f' URL: {link}') print(f' Snippet: {snippet[:250]}{"..." if len(snippet) > 250 else ""}') if matching_indicators: print(f' ‚≠ê MATCHING INDICATORS: {matching_indicators}') relevant_found = True # Special attention to official Whitney sources and art news if any(domain in link_lower for domain in ['whitney.org', 'artforum', 'artnet', 'artnews', 'frieze', 'hyperallergic']): print(f' üéØ HIGH-PRIORITY SOURCE: Official/Art news source') # Look for specific 2022 + photography combinations if '2022' in combined_text and ('photograph' in combined_text or 'photography' in combined_text): print(f' üì∏ PHOTOGRAPHY + 2022 MATCH') # Look for book + portrait combinations if 'book' in combined_text and ('portrait' in combined_text or 'person' in combined_text): print(f' üìö BOOK + PORTRAIT MATCH') if not relevant_found: print(' No highly relevant results found for this query') else: print('No organic results found for this query') google_results.append({ 'query': query, 'results': [], 'search_number': i, 'timestamp': datetime.now().isoformat() }) else: print(f'Error: API request failed with status {response.status_code}: {response.text}') except Exception as e: print(f'Error during search {i}: {str(e)}') continue time.sleep(1) # Rate limiting # Save comprehensive Google search results timestamp = datetime.now().strftime("%Y%m%d_%H%M%S") google_results_file = f'workspace/whitney_2022_photography_google_results_{timestamp}.json' with open(google_results_file, 'w', encoding='utf-8') as f: json.dump({ 'search_objective': 'Whitney Museum 2022 photography acquisitions - person holding book', 'search_timestamp': timestamp, 'total_queries': len(search_queries), 'queries_executed': search_queries, 'google_results': google_results }, f, indent=2, ensure_ascii=False) print(f'\n=== GOOGLE SEARCH RESULTS SAVED ===') print(f'Results saved to: {google_results_file}') # Analyze Google search findings total_google_results = sum(len(query_result['results']) for query_result in google_results) print(f'Total Google results collected: {total_google_results}') # Identify most promising results whitney_official_results = [] photography_2022_results = [] book_portrait_results = [] for query_result in google_results: for result in query_result['results']: title = result.get('title', '').lower() snippet = result.get('snippet', '').lower() link = result.get('link', '').lower() combined = f"{title} {snippet} {link}" # Official Whitney results if 'whitney.org' in link: whitney_official_results.append({ 'query': query_result['query'], 'title': result.get('title'), 'link': result.get('link'), 'snippet': result.get('snippet') }) # import os import json from bs4 import BeautifulSoup import re from datetime import datetime print('=== PHASE 2: ANALYZING COLLECTED WHITNEY MUSEUM DATA ===') print('Objective: Extract specific 2022 photography acquisitions from saved HTML files') print('Focus: Find photographs showing person holding book\n') # First, let's inspect the workspace directory and understand what files we have workspace_dirs = [d for d in os.listdir('.') if d.startswith('workspace')] if workspace_dirs: workspace_dir = workspace_dirs[0] print(f'Found workspace directory: {workspace_dir}') else: workspace_dir = 'workspace' print(f'Using default workspace directory: {workspace_dir}') if os.path.exists(workspace_dir): files = os.listdir(workspace_dir) print(f'Files in {workspace_dir}: {files}\n') # Focus on the promising HTML files that contained relevant indicators promising_files = [f for f in files if f.startswith('whitney_direct_search_') and f.endswith('.html')] print('=== ANALYZING PROMISING WHITNEY HTML FILES ===') print('Based on previous execution, focusing on files with 2022+photography indicators\n') for filename in promising_files: filepath = os.path.join(workspace_dir, filename) print(f'Analyzing: {filename}') print('-' * 50) try: with open(filepath, 'r', encoding='utf-8') as f: html_content = f.read() print(f'Content length: {len(html_content)} characters') # Parse with BeautifulSoup soup = BeautifulSoup(html_content, 'html.parser') # Get page title for context title = soup.find('title') page_title = title.get_text().strip() if title else 'No title found' print(f'Page title: {page_title}') # Look for 2022 acquisition mentions text_content = soup.get_text().lower() # Search for 2022 mentions with context lines = text_content.split('\n') lines_with_2022 = [line.strip() for line in lines if '2022' in line and line.strip()] print(f'\nFound {len(lines_with_2022)} lines containing "2022"') # Look specifically for acquisition-related 2022 mentions acquisition_2022_lines = [] for line in lines_with_2022: if any(keyword in line for keyword in ['acquisition', 'acquired', 'collection', 'new work', 'added']): acquisition_2022_lines.append(line) if acquisition_2022_lines: print(f'\nüéØ FOUND {len(acquisition_2022_lines)} ACQUISITION-RELATED 2022 MENTIONS:') for i, line in enumerate(acquisition_2022_lines[:10], 1): # Show first 10 print(f' {i}. {line[:200]}...' if len(line) > 200 else f' {i}. {line}') # Look for photography/photograph mentions with 2022 photography_2022_lines = [] for line in lines_with_2022: if any(keyword in line for keyword in ['photograph', 'photography', 'portrait', 'image']): photography_2022_lines.append(line) if photography_2022_lines: print(f'\nüì∏ FOUND {len(photography_2022_lines)} PHOTOGRAPHY + 2022 MENTIONS:') for i, line in enumerate(photography_2022_lines[:8], 1): # Show first 8 print(f' {i}. {line[:200]}...' if len(line) > 200 else f' {i}. {line}') # Look for book mentions in context book_lines = [line.strip() for line in lines if 'book' in line and line.strip()] if book_lines: print(f'\nüìö FOUND {len(book_lines)} BOOK MENTIONS:') for i, line in enumerate(book_lines[:5], 1): # Show first 5 print(f' {i}. {line[:150]}...' if len(line) > 150 else f' {i}. {line}') # Look for specific HTML elements that might contain artwork information # Common patterns: article tags, divs with artwork/collection classes, etc. artwork_elements = soup.find_all(['article', 'div', 'section'], class_=re.compile(r'(artwork|collection|acquisition|press|news)', re.I)) if artwork_elements: print(f'\nüé® FOUND {len(artwork_elements)} POTENTIAL ARTWORK ELEMENTS:') for i, element in enumerate(artwork_elements[:5], 1): # Analyze first 5 element_text = element.get_text().strip().lower() # Check if this element mentions 2022 AND photography/photograph if '2022' in element_text and ('photograph' in element_text or 'photography' in element_text): print(f'\n *** ELEMENT {i} - CONTAINS 2022 + PHOTOGRAPHY ***') print(f' Element tag: {element.name}') print(f' Element class: {element.get("class", "No class")}') print(f' Text preview: {element_text[:300]}...') # Look for book mentions within this element if 'book' in element_text: print(f' üìö ALSO CONTAINS BOOK REFERENCE!') # Look for person/portrait mentions if any(word in element_text for word in ['person', 'portrait', 'figure', 'holding', 'man', 'woman']): print(f' üë§ ALSO CONTAINS PERSON/PORTRAIT REFERENCE!') # Look for press release or news items from 2022 press_elements = soup.find_all(['article', 'div', 'li'], class_=re.compile(r'(press|news|announcement)', re.I)) if press_elements: print(f'\nüì∞ FOUND {len(press_elements)} PRESS/NEWS ELEMENTS:') relevant_press = [] for element in press_elements: element_text = element.get_text().strip().lower() if '2022' in element_text: relevant_press.append(element) if relevant_press: print(f' {len(relevant_press)} contain 2022 references') for i, element in enumerate(relevant_press[:3], 1): element_text = element.get_text().strip() print(f'\n Press Item {i}:') print(f' Text: {element_text[:250]}...' if len(element_text) > 250 else f' Text: {element_text}') # Check for photography + book combinations element_lower = element_text.lower() if 'photograph' in element_lower or 'photography' in element_lower: print(f' üì∏ Contains photography reference') if 'book' in element_lower: print(f' üìö Contains book reference') if 'acquisition' in element_lower or 'acquired' in element_lower: print(f' üéØ Contains acquisition reference') print('\n' + '='*50 + '\n') except Exception as e: print(f'Error analyzing {filename}: {e}\n') # Now let's complete the Google search that was cut off in the previous execution print('=== PHASE 3: COMPLETING GOOGLE SEARCH ANALYSIS ===') print('Executing remaining Google searches for comprehensive coverage\n') # Check if we have Google search API available api_key = os.getenv("SERPAPI_API_KEY") if api_key: import requests import time # Additional targeted search queries focusing on specific findings additional_queries = [ 'Whitney Museum 2022 photography acquisitions announcement', '"Whitney Museum" 2022 "new acquisitions" photograph portrait', 'Whitney Museum American Art 2022 contemporary photography collection', 'Whitney press release 2022 photography acquisition book portrait', 'site:artforum.com Whitney Museum 2022 photography acquisitions', 'site:artnet.com Whitney Museum 2022 photography collection', 'Whitney Museum 2022 acquisitions list photography portrait book' ] additional_results = [] for i, query in enumerate(additional_queries, 1): print(f'Additional Search {i}/{len(additional_queries)}: "{query}"') params = { "q": query, "api_key": api_key, "engine": "google", "google_domain": "google.com", "safe": "off", "num": 10, "type": "search" } try: response = requests.get("https://serpapi.com/search.json", params=params, timeout=30) if response.status_code == 200: results = response.json() if results.get("organic_results"): print(f' Found {len(results["organic_results"])} results') # Analyze for highly relevant matches for j, result in enumerate(results['organic_results'][:5], 1): title = result.get('title', 'No title') link = result.get('link', 'No URL') snippet = result.get('snippet', 'No snippet') combined_text = f"{title.lower()} {snippet.lower()}" # Look for exact matches to our criteria exact_matches = [] if 'whitney' in combined_text and '2022' in combined_text: exact_matches.append('Whitney + 2022') if 'photograph' in combined_text or 'photography' in combined_text: exact_matches.append('Photography') if 'acquisition' in combined_text or 'acquired' in combined_text: exact_matches.append('Acquisition') if 'book' in combined_text: exact_matches.append('Book') if 'portrait' in combined_text or 'person' in combined_text: exact_matches.append('Portrait/Person') if len(exact_matches) >= 3: # At least 3 matching criteria print(f'\n üéØ HIGH-RELEVANCE RESULT {j}:') print(f' Title: {title}') print(f' URL: {link}') print(f' Matches: {exact_matches}') print(f' Snippet: {snippet[:200]}...') additional_results.append({ 'query': query, 'results': results['organic_results'], 'timestamp': datetime.now().isoformat() }) else: print(' No results found') else: print(f' Search failed: {response.status_code}') except Exception as e: print(f' Search error: {e}') time.sleep(1) # Rate limiting # Save additional search results if additional_results: timestamp = datetime.now().strftime("%Y%m%d_%H%M%S") additional_file = f'whitney_2022_additional_search_{timestamp}.json' with open(os.path.join(workspace_dir, additional_file), 'w', encoding='utf-8') as f: json.dump({ 'objective': 'Whitney Museum 2022 photography acquisitions - additional targeted search', 'search_timestamp': timestamp, 'additional_queries': additional_queries, 'results': additional_results }, f, indent=2, ensure_ascii=False) print(f'\nAdditional search results saved to: {additional_file}') else: print('No Google API key available - skipping additional searches') # Create comprehensive analysis summary analysis_summary = { 'analysis_timestamp': datetime.now().strftime('%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S'), 'objective': 'Find Whitney Museum 2022 photography acquisition showing person holding book', 'files_analyzed': promising_files, 'key_findings': { 'whitney_collection_page': 'Contains book + photograph references', 'whitney_press_page': 'Contains 2022 + photography + book references', 'analysis_status': 'HTML content analyzed for 2022 acquisition patterns' }, 'next_steps': [ 'Review specific press releases from 2022', 'Cross-reference with art news sources', 'Identify specific photographer and artwork details' ] } with open(os.path.join(workspace_dir, 'whitney_analysis_summary.json'), 'w') as f: json.dump(analysis_summary, f, indent=2) print('\n=== ANALYSIS COMPLETE ===') print('Comprehensive analysis of Whitney Museum data completed') print('Key findings: Whitney press page contains 2022 + photography + book references') print('HTML files have been thoroughly analyzed for acquisition patterns') print('Analysis summary saved to: whitney_analysis_summary.json') else: print(f'Workspace directory {workspace_dir} not found') print('Cannot proceed with analysis - no data files available')

import os import json from datetime import datetime print('=== WHITNEY MUSEUM 2022 PHOTOGRAPHY SEARCH: ALTERNATIVE APPROACH ===') print('Objective: Find Whitney Museum 2022 photography acquisition showing person holding book') print('Strategy: Examine existing workspace data and try alternative search methods\n') # First, let's examine the workspace directory structure workspace_dirs = [d for d in os.listdir('.') if d.startswith('workspace')] if workspace_dirs: workspace_dir = workspace_dirs[0] print(f'Found workspace directory: {workspace_dir}') else: workspace_dir = 'workspace' print(f'Using default workspace directory: {workspace_dir}') if os.path.exists(workspace_dir): files = os.listdir(workspace_dir) print(f'Total files in workspace: {len(files)}') print('Files:', files) print() # Let's examine the JSON files first to understand what data we have json_files = [f for f in files if f.endswith('.json')] print(f'=== EXAMINING {len(json_files)} JSON FILES ===') for json_file in json_files: print(f'\nAnalyzing: {json_file}') print('-' * 40) try: filepath = os.path.join(workspace_dir, json_file) with open(filepath, 'r', encoding='utf-8') as f: data = json.load(f) # Inspect the structure if isinstance(data, dict): print(f'Structure: Dictionary with {len(data)} keys') print(f'Keys: {list(data.keys())}') # Look for specific keys that might contain search results if 'google_results' in data: google_results = data['google_results'] if isinstance(google_results, list): print(f'Google results: {len(google_results)} search queries') # Examine the results for relevant findings total_results = 0 relevant_results = [] for query_data in google_results: if isinstance(query_data, dict) and 'results' in query_data: query_results = query_data['results'] total_results += len(query_results) # Look for highly relevant results for result in query_results: if isinstance(result, dict): title = result.get('title', '').lower() snippet = result.get('snippet', '').lower() link = result.get('link', '').lower() combined = f'{title} {snippet} {link}' # Check for key criteria has_whitney = 'whitney' in combined has_2022 = '2022' in combined has_photo = 'photograph' in combined or 'photography' in combined has_book = 'book' in combined has_portrait = 'portrait' in combined or 'person' in combined has_acquisition = 'acquisition' in combined or 'acquired' in combined criteria_count = sum([has_whitney, has_2022, has_photo, has_book, has_portrait, has_acquisition]) if criteria_count >= 4: # At least 4 of 6 criteria relevant_results.append({ 'title': result.get('title'), 'link': result.get('link'), 'snippet': result.get('snippet'), 'criteria_count': criteria_count, 'query': query_data.get('query', 'Unknown query') }) print(f'Total search results found: {total_results}') print(f'Highly relevant results (4+ criteria): {len(relevant_results)}') if relevant_results: print('\nüéØ TOP RELEVANT RESULTS:') for i, result in enumerate(relevant_results[:5], 1): print(f' {i}. {result["title"]}') print(f' URL: {result["link"]}') print(f' Criteria score: {result["criteria_count"]}/6') print(f' Query: {result["query"]}') print(f' Snippet: {result["snippet"][:150]}...') print() elif 'verification_results' in data: print('Contains verification results data') elif 'search_timestamp' in data: print(f'Search timestamp: {data["search_timestamp"]}') if 'objective' in data: print(f'Objective: {data["objective"]}') elif isinstance(data, list): print(f'Structure: List with {len(data)} items') if len(data) > 0: print(f'First item type: {type(data[0])}') if isinstance(data[0], dict): print(f'First item keys: {list(data[0].keys())}') except Exception as e: print(f'Error reading {json_file}: {e}') # Now let's try a different approach - search for Whitney Museum annual reports or acquisition lists print('\n=== ALTERNATIVE SEARCH STRATEGY ===') print('Trying specific searches for Whitney Museum annual reports and acquisition announcements') api_key = os.getenv("SERPAPI_API_KEY") if api_key: import requests import time # More specific search queries focusing on annual reports and official announcements alternative_queries = [ 'Whitney Museum annual report 2022 acquisitions photography', 'Whitney Museum "annual report" 2022 filetype:pdf', '"Whitney Museum of American Art" "2022 acquisitions" list', 'Whitney Museum trustees report 2022 photography collection', 'Whitney Museum "new works" 2022 photography portrait', 'Whitney Museum press release "recent acquisitions" 2022' ] print(f'Executing {len(alternative_queries)} alternative searches...') alternative_results = [] successful_searches = 0 for i, query in enumerate(alternative_queries, 1): print(f'\nAlternative Search {i}/{len(alternative_queries)}: "{query}"') params = { "q": query, "api_key": api_key, "engine": "google", "google_domain": "google.com", "safe": "off", "num": 8, "type": "search" } try: response = requests.get("https://serpapi.com/search.json", params=params, timeout=30) if response.status_code == 200: results = response.json() successful_searches += 1 if results.get("organic_results"): print(f' ‚úì Found {len(results["organic_results"])} results') # Look for official Whitney sources and PDFs priority_results = [] for result in results['organic_results']: title = result.get('title', '') link = result.get('link', '') snippet = result.get('snippet', '') # Prioritize official Whitney sources and PDF documents is_official = 'whitney.org' in link.lower() is_pdf = '.pdf' in link.lower() or 'pdf' in title.lower() has_2022 = '2022' in f'{title} {snippet}'.lower() has_acquisition = any(word in f'{title} {snippet}'.lower() for word in ['acquisition', 'acquired', 'new work', 'collection']) priority_score = sum([is_official, is_pdf, has_2022, has_acquisition]) if priority_score >= 2: priority_results.append({ 'title': title, 'link': link, 'snippet': snippet, 'priority_score': priority_score, 'is_official': is_official, 'is_pdf': is_pdf }) if priority_results: print(f' üéØ {len(priority_results)} priority results found:') for j, result in enumerate(priority_results[:3], 1): print(f' {j}. {result["title"]}') print(f' URL: {result["link"]}') print(f' Priority score: {result["priority_score"]}/4') if result['is_official']: print(' ‚≠ê Official Whitney source') if result['is_pdf']: print(' üìÑ PDF document') print(f' Snippet: {result["snippet"][:120]}...') print() alternative_results.append({ 'query': query, 'results': results['organic_results'], 'priority_results': priority_results, 'timestamp': datetime.now().isoformat() }) else: print(' No results found') elif response.status_code == 429: print(' ‚ö†Ô∏è Rate limit reached - pausing searches') break else: print(f' ‚úó Search failed: HTTP {response.status_code}') except Exception as e: print(f' ‚úó Search error: {e}') time.sleep(2) # Longer delay to avoid rate limits if alternative_results: # Save alternative search results timestamp = datetime.now().strftime("%Y%m%d_%H%M%S") alt_results_file = f'whitney_alternative_search_{timestamp}.json' with open(os.path.join(workspace_dir, alt_results_file), 'w', encoding='utf-8') as f: json.dump({ 'search_strategy': 'Alternative approach - annual reports and official announcements', 'search_timestamp': timestamp, 'successful_searches': successful_searches, 'queries': alternative_queries, 'results': alternative_results }, f, indent=2, ensure_ascii=False) print(f'\nAlternative search results saved to: {alt_results_file}') # Analyze the most promising findings all_priority_results = [] for query_result in alternative_results: all_priority_results.extend(query_result.get('priority_results', [])) print(f'\nüìä ALTERNATIVE SEARCH SUMMARY:') print(f'Successful searches: {successful_searches}/{len(alternative_queries)}') print(f'Total priority results: {len(all_priority_results)}') # Group by type official_sources = [r for r in all_priority_results if r['is_official']] pdf_documents = [r for r in all_priority_results if r['is_pdf']] print(f'Official Whitney sources: {len(official_sources)}') print(f'PDF documents: {len(pdf_documents)}') if official_sources: print('\nüèõÔ∏è OFFICIAL WHITNEY SOURCES:') for i, source in enumerate(official_sources[:3], 1): print(f' {i}. {source["title"]}') print(f' {source["link"]}') if pdf_documents: print('\nüìÑ PDF DOCUMENTS:') for i, doc in enumerate(pdf_documents[:3], 1): print(f' {i}. {doc["title"]}') print(f' {doc["link"]}') else: print('No Google API key available - cannot perform additional searches') print('Recommendation: Examine existing JSON files for any missed relevant results') # Create final assessment final_assessment = { 'assessment_timestamp': datetime.now().strftime('%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S'), 'objective': 'Find Whitney Museum 2022 photography acquisition showing person holding book', 'search_status': 'Comprehensive search completed with mixed results', 'files_examined': len(files), 'json_files_analyzed': len(json_files), 'key_challenges': [ 'API rate limits preventing extensive Google searches', 'Whitney website structure limiting direct access to acquisition data', 'No clear match found for specific photograph description' ], 'recommendations': [ 'Contact Whitney Museum directly for 2022 acquisition information', 'Search art databases like Benezit Dictionary or Oxford Art Online', 'Check museum press archives and art news sources manually', 'Consider that the photograph may not be widely documented online' ], 'next_steps': [ 'Review existing search results for any missed connections', 'Try searching with artist names if any are mentioned in existing data', 'Look for Whitney Museum annual reports or trustee reports from 2022' ] } with open(os.path.join(workspace_dir, 'whitney_final_search_assessment.json'), 'w') as f: json.dump(final_assessment, f, indent=2) print('\n=== FINAL ASSESSMENT ===') print('Comprehensive search approach completed') print('Multiple strategies attempted: direct website access, Google searches, alternative queries') print('Challenge: Specific 2022 Whitney photography acquisition not clearly identified') print('Recommendation: May require direct contact with Whitney Museum or specialized art databases') print('Final assessment saved to: whitney_final_search_assessment.json') else: print(f'Workspace directory {workspace_dir} not found') print('Cannot proceed with analysis - no previous search data available')

Look for nested structures for key, value in data.items(): if isinstance(value, list) and len(value) > 0: print(f' {key}: List with {len(value)} items') if isinstance(value[0], dict): print(f' First item keys: {list(value[0].keys())}') elif isinstance(value, dict): print(f' {key}: Dictionary with {len(value)} keys') print(f' Sub-keys: {list(value.keys())}') else: print(f' {key}: {type(value).__name__}') elif isinstance(data, list): print(f' Type: List with {len(data)} items') if len(data) > 0: print(f' First item type: {type(data[0])}') if isinstance(data[0], dict): print(f' First item keys: {list(data[0].keys())}') file_structures[json_file] = data except Exception as e: print(f' Error reading {json_file}: {e}') file_structures[json_file] = None print('\n=== STEP 2: DEEP ANALYSIS OF SEARCH RESULTS ===') # Handle different data structures carefully if isinstance(data, dict): # Look for google_results key if 'google_results' in data: google_results = data['google_results'] print(f' Found google_results key') if isinstance(google_results, list): print(f' Google results: {len(google_results)} query sets') for i, query_set in enumerate(google_results): if isinstance(query_set, dict) and 'results' in query_set: results = query_set['results'] query = query_set.get('query', f'Query {i+1}') print(f' Query: "{query}"') print(f' Results: {len(results)} items') total_search_results += len(results) # Analyze each result for Whitney + 2022 + photography + book combinations highly_relevant = [] for result in results: if isinstance(result, dict): title = result.get('title', '').lower() snippet = result.get('snippet', '').lower() link = result.get('link', '').lower() combined = f'{title} {snippet} {link}' # Scoring system for relevance score = 0 criteria_met = [] if 'whitney' in combined: score += 2 criteria_met.append('Whitney') if '2022' in combined: score += 2 criteria_met.append('2022') if 'photograph' in combined or 'photography' in combined: score += 2 criteria_met.append('Photography') if 'book' in combined: score += 1 criteria_met.append('Book') if 'portrait' in combined or 'person' in combined: score += 1 criteria_met.append('Portrait/Person') if 'acquisition' in combined or 'acquired' in combined: score += 1 criteria_met.append('Acquisition') if 'holding' in combined: score += 1 criteria_met.append('Holding') if score >= 5: # High relevance threshold highly_relevant.append({ 'title': result.get('title'), 'link': result.get('link'), 'snippet': result.get('snippet'), 'score': score, 'criteria': criteria_met, 'query': query }) if highly_relevant: print(f' üéØ Found {len(highly_relevant)} highly relevant results:') for hr in highly_relevant[:3]: # Show top 3 print(f' - {hr["title"]}\n Score: {hr["score"]}, Criteria: {hr["criteria"]}') print(f' URL: {hr["link"]}') print(f' Snippet: {hr["snippet"][:120]}...\n') search_results_found.extend(highly_relevant) # Conservative rate limiting if final_results: timestamp = datetime.now().strftime("%Y%m%d_%H%M%S") final_file = f'whitney_final_targeted_search_{timestamp}.json' with open(os.path.join(workspace_dir, final_file), 'w', encoding='utf-8') as f: json.dump({ 'search_type': 'Final ultra-targeted search', 'timestamp': timestamp, 'queries': final_queries, 'results': final_results }, f, indent=2, ensure_ascii=False) print(f'\nFinal search results saved to: {final_file}') else: print('No API key available for final search attempt') # Analyze each result for Whitney + 2022 + photography + book combinations highly_relevant = [] for result in results: if isinstance(result, dict): title = result.get('title', '').lower() snippet = result.get('snippet', '').lower() link = result.get('link', '').lower() combined = f'{title} {snippet} {link}' # Scoring system for relevance score = 0 criteria_met = [] if 'whitney' in combined: score += 2 criteria_met.append('Whitney') if '2022' in combined: score += 2 criteria_met.append('2022') if 'photograph' in combined or 'photography' in combined: score += 2 criteria_met.append('Photography') if 'book' in combined: score += 1 criteria_met.append('Book') if 'portrait' in combined or 'person' in combined: score += 1 criteria_met.append('Portrait/Person') if 'acquisition' in combined or 'acquired' in combined: score += 1 criteria_met.append('Acquisition') if 'holding' in combined: score += 1 criteria_met.append('Holding') if score >= 5: # High relevance threshold highly_relevant.append({ 'title': result.get('title'), 'link': result.get('link'), 'snippet': result.get('snippet'), 'score': score, 'criteria': criteria_met, 'query': query }) if highly_relevant: print(f' üéØ Found {len(highly_relevant)} highly relevant results:') for hr in highly_relevant[:3]: # Show top 3 print(f' - {hr["title"]}\n Score: {hr["score"]}, Criteria: {hr["criteria"]}') print(f' URL: {hr["link"]}') print(f' Snippet: {hr["snippet"][:120]}...\n') search_results_found.extend(highly_relevant) # Sort by relevance score search_results_found.sort(key=lambda x: x['score'], reverse=True) if search_results_found: print(f'\nüèÜ TOP RELEVANT FINDINGS:') for i, result in enumerate(search_results_found[:5], 1): print(f'\n{i}. {result["title"]}') print(f' Score: {result["score"]}/9 | Criteria: {result["criteria"]}') print(f' URL: {result["link"]}') print(f' Query: {result["query"]}') print(f' Snippet: {result["snippet"][:200]}...') else: print('\n‚ùå No highly relevant results found in existing data') # Final relevance check combined = f'{title} {snippet} {link}'.lower() if all(term in combined for term in ['whitney', '2022']) and \ ('photograph' in combined or 'photography' in combined): print(' üéØ HIGH RELEVANCE MATCH!') final_results.append({ 'query': query, 'results': results['organic_results'], 'timestamp': datetime.now().isoformat() }) else: print(' No results found') elif response.status_code == 429: print(' ‚ö†Ô∏è Rate limit reached') break else: print(f' ‚úó Search failed: HTTP {response.status_code}') except Exception as e: print(f' ‚úó Search error: {e}') time.sleep(3) # Conservative rate limiting if final_results: timestamp = datetime.now().strftime("%Y%m%d_%H%M%S") final_file = f'whitney_final_targeted_search_{timestamp}.json' with open(os.path.join(workspace_dir, final_file), 'w', encoding='utf-8') as f: json.dump({ 'search_type': 'Final ultra-targeted search', 'timestamp': timestamp, 'queries': final_queries, 'results': final_results }, f, indent=2, ensure_ascii=False) print(f'\nFinal search results saved to: {final_file}') else: print('No API key available for final search attempt') # ### Development Step 2: Metropolitan Museum Portrait Accession 29.100.5: Title, Artist, Subject, and Metadata Search

**Description**: Search for information about the Metropolitan Museum of Art portrait with accession number 29.100.5. Look for the artwork's title, artist, subject, and any available metadata or catalog information. Use multiple search approaches including: (1) Direct search on the Met Museum's official website and collection database, (2) Google search with terms 'Metropolitan Museum Art 29.100.5 accession portrait', (3) Art history databases and museum catalog searches. Extract complete details about the portrait including who is depicted in the artwork.

**Use Cases**:
- Museum collection management and automated metadata synchronization for accession 29.100.5 in digital archives
- Graduate art history research and batch extraction of portrait details for thematic analysis in academic publications
- Auction house provenance verification and authenticity checks using cross-referenced Met Museum accession metadata
- Virtual tour application development and real-time retrieval of portrait metadata for enhanced visitor engagement
- Digital marketing content enrichment and SEO optimization with official artwork titles and artist information
- Journalism fact-checking and rapid aggregation of catalog details for museum exhibit coverage

```
import os
import requests
from bs4 import BeautifulSoup
import json
import time

# Create workspace directory if it doesn't exist
if not os.path.exists('workspace'):
os.makedirs('workspace')

print('=== METROPOLITAN MUSEUM OF ART PORTRAIT RESEARCH ===\n')
print('Target: Accession number 29.100.5')
print('Objective: Find artwork title, artist, subject, and complete metadata\n')

# Fix the syntax error by treating accession number as string
accession_number = '29.100.5'
print(f'Searching for accession number: {accession_number}')

# First, try to access the Met Museum's official collection database directly
print('Step 1: Attempting direct access to Met Museum collection database...')

# The Met has a public API and collection search
met_collection_urls = [
f'https://www.metmuseum.org/art/collection/search/{accession_number}',
f'https://www.metmuseum.org/art/collection/search?q={accession_number}',
f'https://collectionapi.metmuseum.org/public/collection/v1/search?q={accession_number}',
f'https://www.metmuseum.org/art/collection/search?accessionNumber={accession_number}'
]

headers = {
'User-Agent': 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 10.0; Win64; x64) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/91.0.4472.124 Safari/537.36'
}

met_results = []
for i, url in enumerate(met_collection_urls):
print(f'\nTrying Met URL {i+1}: {url}')

try:
response = requests.get(url, headers=headers, timeout=20)
print(f'Response status: {response.status_code}')

if response.status_code == 200:
print(f'‚úì Successfully accessed {url}')

# Save the response for analysis
filename = f'workspace/met_direct_search_{i+1}.html'

# Check if it's JSON or HTML
try:
json_data = response.json()
filename = f'workspace/met_api_response_{i+1}.json'
with open(filename, 'w') as f:
json.dump(json_data, f, indent=2)
print(f' Saved JSON response to: {filename}')
print(f' JSON keys: {list(json_data.keys()) if isinstance(json_data, dict) else "List with " + str(len(json_data)) + " items"}')
except:
# It's HTML
with open(filename, 'w', encoding='utf-8') as f:
f.write(response.text)
print(f' Saved HTML response to: {filename}')

# Quick analysis of HTML content
soup = BeautifulSoup(response.content, 'html.parser')
title = soup.find('title')
title_text = title.get_text().strip() if title else 'No title found'
print(f' Page title: {title_text}')

# Look for accession number mentions
content_text = response.text.lower()
if accession_number in content_text:
print(' *** ACCESSION NUMBER FOUND IN CONTENT ***')

# Look for portrait/artwork indicators
artwork_indicators = ['portrait', 'painting', 'artist', 'artwork', 'collection']
found_indicators = [ind for ind in artwork_indicators if ind in content_text]
if found_indicators:
print(f' Artwork indicators found: {found_indicators}')

met_results.append({
'url': url,
'status': response.status_code,
'filename': filename,
'content_length': len(response.text)
})

else:
print(f'‚úó Failed - Status: {response.status_code}')
met_results.append({
'url': url,
'status': response.status_code,
'error': f'HTTP {response.status_code}'
})

except Exception as e:
print(f'‚úó Error: {str(e)}')
met_results.append({
'url': url,
'error': str(e)
})

time.sleep(2) # Be respectful to servers

print(f'\n=== MET MUSEUM DIRECT SEARCH RESULTS ===\n')
print(f'Attempted {len(met_collection_urls)} direct Met Museum URLs')
successful_met = [r for r in met_results if r.get('status') == 200]
print(f'Successful responses: {len(successful_met)}')

for result in successful_met:
print(f' ‚úì {result["url"]} -> {result["filename"]}')

# Now use Google Search API for comprehensive search
api_key = os.getenv("SERPAPI_API_KEY")

if api_key:
print('\n=== GOOGLE SEARCH FOR MET PORTRAIT 29.100.5 ===\n')

# Multiple search queries to maximize information gathering
search_queries = [
f'Metropolitan Museum Art {accession_number} accession portrait',
f'Met Museum {accession_number} painting artwork collection',
f'"{accession_number}" Metropolitan Museum portrait artist subject',
f'metmuseum.org {accession_number} accession number artwork'
]

google_results = []

for i, query in enumerate(search_queries):
print(f'Search {i+1}: "{query}"')

params = {
"q": query,
"api_key": api_key,
"engine": "google",
"google_domain": "google.com",
"safe": "off",
"num": 8
}

try:
response = requests.get("https://serpapi.com/search.json", params=params)

if response.status_code == 200:
results = response.json()

if results.get("organic_results"):
print(f' Found {len(results["organic_results"])} results')

for j, result in enumerate(results["organic_results"]):
title = result.get('title', 'No title')
link = result.get('link', 'No link')
snippet = result.get('snippet', 'No snippet')

print(f'\n Result {j+1}:')
print(f' Title: {title}')
print(f' URL: {link}')
print(f' Snippet: {snippet}')

# Check for key information
combined_text = f'{title} {snippet}'.lower()

key_findings = []
if accession_number in combined_text:
key_findings.append('Accession number found')
if 'portrait' in combined_text:
key_findings.append('Portrait mentioned')
if 'artist' in combined_text or 'painter' in combined_text:
key_findings.append('Artist information')
if 'metmuseum.org' in link:
key_findings.append('Official Met Museum source')

if key_findings:
print(f' *** KEY FINDINGS: {key_findings} ***')

google_results.append({
'search_query': query,
'result_index': j+1,
'title': title,
'link': link,
'snippet': snippet,
'key_findings': key_findings
})
else:
print(' No organic results found')
else:
print(f' Search failed with status: {response.status_code}')

except Exception as e:
print(f' Search error: {str(e)}')

time.sleep(1) # Rate limiting

# Save all Google search results
with open('workspace/met_29_100_5_google_results.json', 'w') as f:
json.dump(google_results, f, indent=2)

print(f'\nGoogle search results saved to: workspace/met_29_100_5_google_results.json')

print(f'Priority results with key findings: {len(priority_results)}')

else:
print('\nNo SERPAPI key available - skipping Google search')
google_results = []

# Compile initial research summary
research_summary = {
'target_accession': accession_number,
'museum': 'Metropolitan Museum of Art',
'search_timestamp': time.strftime('%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S'),
'direct_met_searches': {
'attempted_urls': len(met_collection_urls),
'successful_responses': len(successful_met),
'results': met_results
},
'google_searches': {
'queries_attempted': len(search_queries) if api_key else 0,
'total_results': len(google_results),
'priority_results': len([r for r in google_results if r.get('key_findings')]) if google_results else 0
},
'files_created': [
f for f in os.listdir('workspace')
if f.startswith('met_') and (f.endswith('.html') or f.endswith('.json'))
]
}

with open('workspace/met_portrait_research_summary.json', 'w') as f:
```

### Development Step 3: Met Museum Portrait Accession 29.100.5: Title, Artist, Subject & Complete Catalog Metadata

**Description**: Search for information about the Metropolitan Museum of Art portrait with accession number 29.100.5. Look for the artwork's title, artist, subject, and any available metadata or catalog information. Extract complete details about the portrait including who is depicted in the artwork.

**Use Cases**:
- Automated catalog synchronization for museum registrars to ensure internal databases reflect the latest Met accession details (title, artist, medium, dimensions) without manual entry
- Art historical research pipeline that aggregates portrait metadata (artist dates, subject constituents, tags) across online museum collections for a comparative study of 18th‚Äêcentury portraiture
- E-learning module generator for an online art history platform that programmatically pulls portrait data (objectDate, culture, classification) to create interactive lesson plans
- Digital marketing dashboard integration that fetches high-resolution images and object URLs from the Met API in real time for promoting featured artworks on social media
- Art investment analytics tool that extracts medium, artist provenance, and object dimensions to feed valuation models and auction readiness reports
- Virtual reality museum exhibit builder that retrieves primaryImage URLs and descriptive metadata to dynamically populate immersive gallery environments

```
print(f'\n=== PORTRAIT DETAILS EXTRACTED ===\n')
print(f'Accession Number: {portrait_details["accession_number"]}')

print(f'Object URL: {portrait_details["object_url"]}')

# Look for subject information in constituents or tags

if isinstance(constituent, dict):
```

### Development Step 1: Search Met Museum Portrait Accession 29.100.5: Title, Artist, Subject, Metadata

**Description**: Search for information about the Metropolitan Museum of Art portrait with accession number 29.100.5. Look for the artwork's title, artist, subject, and any available metadata or catalog information. Use multiple search approaches including: (1) Direct search on the Met Museum's official website and collection database, (2) Google search with terms 'Metropolitan Museum Art 29.100.5 accession portrait', (3) Art history databases and museum catalog searches. Extract complete details about the portrait including who is depicted in the artwork.

**Use Cases**:
- Museum collections management and digital archive enrichment by automatically fetching accession 29.100.5 metadata from the Met Museum website into internal cataloging systems
- Art marketplace listing automation integrating real-time retrieval of official title, artist, and subject for artwork 29.100.5 to populate e-commerce product pages with authoritative museum data

- Educational platform content generation dynamically pulling high-resolution images and metadata of accession 29.100.5 to create interactive lecture slides and online course modules on portrait art

- Art authentication and provenance verification service cross-referencing the Met‚Äôs accession 29.100.5 metadata via API and Google search results to confirm ownership history and artist attribution
- Digital humanities text analysis pipeline extracting and normalizing descriptive metadata (artist, subject, date) from accession 29.100.5 as part of a corpus for NLP-driven insights on art historical narratives
- Virtual reality exhibition builder fetching live metadata and imagery for accession 29.100.5 to automatically populate virtual gallery spaces with accurate artwork details and contextual information

```
import requests
from bs4 import BeautifulSoup
import json
import time

# Create workspace directory if it doesn't exist

os.makedirs('workspace')

print('Target: Accession number 29.100.5')
print('Objective: Find artwork title, artist, subject, and complete metadata\n')

# First, try to access the Met Museum's official collection database directly
print('Step 1: Attempting direct access to Met Museum collection database...')

# The Met has a public API and collection search
met_collection_urls = [
f'https://www.metmuseum.org/art/collection/search/{29.100.5}',
f'https://www.metmuseum.org/art/collection/search?q=29.100.5',
'https://collectionapi.metmuseum.org/public/collection/v1/search?q=29.100.5',
'https://www.metmuseum.org/art/collection/search?accessionNumber=29.100.5'
]

headers = {
'User-Agent': 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 10.0; Win64; x64) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/91.0.4472.124 Safari/537.36'
}

met_results = []
for i, url in enumerate(met_collection_urls):
print(f'\nTrying Met URL {i+1}: {url}')

try:
response = requests.get(url, headers=headers, timeout=20)
print(f'Response status: {response.status_code}')

if response.status_code == 200:
print(f'‚úì Successfully accessed {url}')

# Save the response for analysis
filename = f'workspace/met_direct_search_{i+1}.html'

# Check if it's JSON or HTML
try:
json_data = response.json()
filename = f'workspace/met_api_response_{i+1}.json'
with open(filename, 'w') as f:
json.dump(json_data, f, indent=2)
print(f' Saved JSON response to: {filename}')
print(f' JSON keys: {list(json_data.keys()) if isinstance(json_data, dict) else "List with " + str(len(json_data)) + " items"}')
except:
# It's HTML
with open(filename, 'w', encoding='utf-8') as f:
f.write(response.text)
print(f' Saved HTML response to: {filename}')

# Quick analysis of HTML content
soup = BeautifulSoup(response.content, 'html.parser')
title = soup.find('title')
title_text = title.get_text().strip() if title else 'No title found'
print(f' Page title: {title_text}')

# Look for accession number mentions
content_text = response.text.lower()
if '29.100.5' in content_text:
print(' *** ACCESSION NUMBER FOUND IN CONTENT ***')

# Look for portrait/artwork indicators
artwork_indicators = ['portrait', 'painting', 'artist', 'artwork', 'collection']
found_indicators = [ind for ind in artwork_indicators if ind in content_text]
if found_indicators:
print(f' Artwork indicators found: {found_indicators}')

met_results.append({
'url': url,
'status': response.status_code,
'filename': filename,
'content_length': len(response.text)
})

else:
print(f'‚úó Failed - Status: {response.status_code}')
met_results.append({
'url': url,
'status': response.status_code,
'error': f'HTTP {response.status_code}'
})

except Exception as e:
print(f'‚úó Error: {str(e)}')
met_results.append({
'url': url,
'error': str(e)
})

time.sleep(2) # Be respectful to servers

print(f'\n=== MET MUSEUM DIRECT SEARCH RESULTS ===\n')
print(f'Attempted {len(met_collection_urls)} direct Met Museum URLs')
successful_met = [r for r in met_results if r.get('status') == 200]
print(f'Successful responses: {len(successful_met)}')

for result in successful_met:
print(f' ‚úì {result["url"]} -> {result["filename"]}')

# Now use Google Search API for comprehensive search
api_key = os.getenv("SERPAPI_API_KEY")

if api_key:
print('\n=== GOOGLE SEARCH FOR MET PORTRAIT 29.100.5 ===\n')

# Multiple search queries to maximize information gathering
search_queries = [
'Metropolitan Museum Art 29.100.5 accession portrait',
'Met Museum 29.100.5 painting artwork collection',
'"29.100.5" Metropolitan Museum portrait artist subject',
'metmuseum.org 29.100.5 accession number artwork'
]

google_results = []

for i, query in enumerate(search_queries):
print(f'Search {i+1}: "{query}"')

params = {
"q": query,
"api_key": api_key,
"engine": "google",
"google_domain": "google.com",
"safe": "off",
"num": 8
}

try:
response = requests.get("https://serpapi.com/search.json", params=params)

if response.status_code == 200:
results = response.json()

if results.get("organic_results"):
print(f' Found {len(results["organic_results"])} results')

for j, result in enumerate(results["organic_results"]):
title = result.get('title', 'No title')
link = result.get('link', 'No link')
snippet = result.get('snippet', 'No snippet')

print(f'\n Result {j+1}:')
print(f' Title: {title}')
print(f' URL: {link}')
print(f' Snippet: {snippet}')

# Check for key information
combined_text = f'{title} {snippet}'.lower()

key_findings = []
if '29.100.5' in combined_text:
key_findings.append('Accession number found')
if 'portrait' in combined_text:
key_findings.append('Portrait mentioned')
if 'artist' in combined_text or 'painter' in combined_text:
key_findings.append('Artist information')
if 'metmuseum.org' in link:
key_findings.append('Official Met Museum source')

if key_findings:
print(f' *** KEY FINDINGS: {key_findings} ***')

google_results.append({
'search_query': query,
'result_index': j+1,
'title': title,
'link': link,
'snippet': snippet,
'key_findings': key_findings
})
else:
print(' No organic results found')
else:
print(f' Search failed with status: {response.status_code}')

except Exception as e:
print(f' Search error: {str(e)}')

time.sleep(1) # Rate limiting

# Save all Google search results
with open('workspace/met_29_100_5_google_results.json', 'w') as f:
json.dump(google_results, f, indent=2)

print(f'\nGoogle search results saved to: workspace/met_29_100_5_google_results.json')
print(f'Total Google results collected: {len(google_results)}')

# Identify most promising results
priority_results = [r for r in google_results if r['key_findings']]
print(f'Priority results with key findings: {len(priority_results)}')

else:
print('\nNo SERPAPI key available - skipping Google search')
google_results = []

# Compile initial research summary
research_summary = {
'target_accession': '29.100.5',
'museum': 'Metropolitan Museum of Art',
'search_timestamp': time.strftime('%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S'),
'direct_met_searches': {
'attempted_urls': len(met_collection_urls),
'successful_responses': len(successful_met),
'results': met_results
},
'google_searches': {
'queries_attempted': len(search_queries) if api_key else 0,
'total_results': len(google_results),
'priority_results': len([r for r in google_results if r.get('key_findings')]) if google_results else 0
},
'files_created': [
f for f in os.listdir('workspace')
if f.startswith('met_') and (f.endswith('.html') or f.endswith('.json'))
]
}

with open('workspace/met_portrait_research_summary.json', 'w') as f:
json.dump(research_summary, f, indent=2)

print(f'\n=== PHASE 1 RESEARCH COMPLETE ===\n')
print(f'Research summary saved to: workspace/met_portrait_research_summary.json')
print(f'Files created in workspace: {len(research_summary["files_created"])}')
print(f'Next step: Analyze collected data to extract portrait details')

# Quick preview of findings
```

### Development Step 1: Find Merriam-Webster‚Äôs Word of the Day for June 27, 2022 and Identify the Featured Author

**Description**: Search for Merriam-Webster's Word of the Day archive or specific entry from June 27, 2022. Use web search with targeted queries such as 'Merriam-Webster Word of the Day June 27 2022', 'site:merriam-webster.com word of the day June 2022', and 'Merriam-Webster WOTD archive 06/27/2022'. Look for the official Merriam-Webster page showing the word selection, definition, etymology, and any quoted usage examples. Extract the complete entry including the featured word, writer attribution, and quote context to identify which author is referenced in the daily feature.

**Use Cases**:
- Automated vocabulary builder for language learners: fetch the June 27, 2022 WOTD entry with definition, etymology, and usage example to auto-populate flashcards in an Anki deck.
- Content calendar automation for educational blogs: retrieve the archived Word of the Day and author quote from June 27, 2022 to schedule a themed post with minimal manual effort.
- Historical lexicography research pipeline: scrape WOTD entries for specific dates (e.g., June 27, 2022) across multiple years to analyze word choice trends and semantic shifts over time.
- SEO-driven social media campaign management: automatically pull the Merriam-Webster daily word and its author citation to craft timely, searchable posts on Twitter and LinkedIn.
- Competitive analysis for e-learning platforms: monitor Merriam-Webster‚Äôs WOTD archive (including June 27, 2022) to benchmark in-house microlearning vocabulary modules against industry standards.
- Chatbot knowledge-base enrichment in customer support: integrate archived WOTD definitions and usage examples from June 27, 2022 to enhance the bot‚Äôs language understanding and natural-language responses.
- Data integrity audit for educational APIs: cross-verify scraped June 27, 2022 WOTD content against Merriam-Webster‚Äôs API responses to detect missing or inconsistent entries in an internal dictionary database.
- Digital humanities citation index creation: extract author attributions and quoted passages from the June 27, 2022 WOTD to build a searchable database of literary citations and usage contexts.

```
import os
import requests
from datetime import datetime
from bs4 import BeautifulSoup

print("=== SEARCHING FOR MERRIAM-WEBSTER WORD OF THE DAY - JUNE 27, 2022 ===")
print("Objective: Find the specific WOTD entry with author reference from June 27, 2022\n")

# Get SerpAPI key from environment
api_key = os.getenv("SERPAPI_API_KEY")

if not api_key:
print("Error: SERPAPI_API_KEY not found in environment variables")
else:
print(f"API key found: {api_key[:8]}...")

# Multiple targeted search queries for the specific date
search_queries = [
'Merriam-Webster Word of the Day June 27 2022',
'site:merriam-webster.com "word of the day" "June 27, 2022"',
'Merriam-Webster WOTD "June 27" 2022',
'"merriam-webster.com" "word of the day" "06/27/2022"',
'Merriam Webster daily word June 27 2022 archive'
]

print(f"Executing {len(search_queries)} targeted search queries...\n")

all_search_results = []

for i, query in enumerate(search_queries, 1):
print(f"Query {i}: {query}")

# Prepare API request parameters
params = {
"q": query,
"api_key": api_key,
"engine": "google",
"google_domain": "google.com",
"safe": "off",
"num": 10
}

try:
response = requests.get("https://serpapi.com/search.json", params=params)

if response.status_code == 200:
results = response.json()

if results.get("organic_results"):
print(f" Found {len(results['organic_results'])} results")

# Process and analyze each result
for j, result in enumerate(results['organic_results'], 1):
result_info = {
'query_number': i,
'result_number': j,
'title': result.get('title', 'No title'),
'link': result.get('link', 'No link'),
'snippet': result.get('snippet', 'No snippet'),
'is_merriam_webster': 'merriam-webster.com' in result.get('link', '').lower()
}

all_search_results.append(result_info)

# Print relevant results immediately
if result_info['is_merriam_webster']:
print(f" ‚òÖ MERRIAM-WEBSTER RESULT {j}:")
print(f" Title: {result_info['title']}")
print(f" Link: {result_info['link']}")
print(f" Snippet: {result_info['snippet'][:200]}...")
else:
print(f" Result {j}: {result_info['title'][:60]}... | {result_info['link'][:50]}...")
else:
print(f" No organic results found")
else:
print(f" API Error: {response.status_code} - {response.text[:100]}...")

except Exception as e:
print(f" Exception during search: {str(e)}")

print() # Space between queries

print(f"\n=== SEARCH RESULTS SUMMARY ===")
print(f"Total results collected: {len(all_search_results)}")

# Filter and prioritize Merriam-Webster results
mw_results = [r for r in all_search_results if r['is_merriam_webster']]
print(f"Merriam-Webster official results: {len(mw_results)}")

if mw_results:
print("\n=== MERRIAM-WEBSTER OFFICIAL RESULTS ===")
for i, result in enumerate(mw_results, 1):
print(f"{i}. {result['title']}")
print(f" Link: {result['link']}")
print(f" Snippet: {result['snippet']}")
print(f" From Query: {result['query_number']}")
print()

# Try to access the most promising Merriam-Webster link
best_result = mw_results[0] # Take the first MW result
target_url = best_result['link']

print(f"\n=== ATTEMPTING TO ACCESS MERRIAM-WEBSTER PAGE ===")
print(f"Target URL: {target_url}")

try:
headers = {
'User-Agent': 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 10.0; Win64; x64) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/91.0.4472.124 Safari/537.36'
}

page_response = requests.get(target_url, headers=headers, timeout=30)

if page_response.status_code == 200:
print(f"‚úì Successfully accessed page (Status: {page_response.status_code})")
print(f"Content length: {len(page_response.content):,} bytes")

# Parse the HTML content
soup = BeautifulSoup(page_response.content, 'html.parser')

# Extract key information from the page
page_title = soup.find('title')
if page_title:
print(f"Page title: {page_title.get_text().strip()}")

# Save the HTML content for detailed analysis
if not os.path.exists('workspace'):
os.makedirs('workspace')

html_filename = 'workspace/merriam_webster_wotd_june_27_2022.html'
with open(html_filename, 'w', encoding='utf-8') as f:
f.write(page_response.text)

print(f"‚úì Page content saved to: {html_filename}")

# Quick content analysis for WOTD information
page_text = soup.get_text().lower()

# Look for date indicators
date_indicators = ['june 27', '06/27', '6/27', 'june 27, 2022', '27 june']
date_found = any(indicator in page_text for indicator in date_indicators)

# Look for word of the day indicators
wotd_indicators = ['word of the day', 'wotd', 'daily word', 'featured word']
wotd_found = any(indicator in page_text for indicator in wotd_indicators)

# Look for author/quote indicators
author_indicators = ['author', 'quote', 'quotation', 'citation', 'written by', 'by ']
author_found = any(indicator in page_text for indicator in author_indicators)

print(f"\n=== QUICK CONTENT ANALYSIS ===")
print(f"Date reference (June 27): {date_found}")
print(f"Word of the Day content: {wotd_found}")
print(f"Author/quote references: {author_found}")

else:
print(f"‚úó Failed to access page (Status: {page_response.status_code})")
print(f"Response: {page_response.text[:200]}...")

except Exception as e:
print(f"‚úó Exception accessing page: {str(e)}")

else:

for i, result in enumerate(all_search_results[:5], 1): # Show first 5 overall results

print(f" Link: {result['link']}")

'target_date': 'June 27, 2022',

'merriam_webster_results': len(mw_results),
```

import os import requests from bs4 import BeautifulSoup import json import time from urllib.parse import urljoin, urlparse print('=== WHITNEY MUSEUM 2022 ACQUISITIONS - DIRECT WEB SCRAPING APPROACH ===') print('Objective: Scrape Whitney Museum website directly for 2022 acquisition information') print('Focus: Press releases, collection updates, and acquisition announcements\n') # Create workspace directory if it doesn't exist if not os.path.exists('workspace'): os.makedirs('workspace') # Since SerpAPI quota is exhausted, we'll use direct web scraping # Start with Whitney Museum's main pages and navigation headers = { 'User-Agent': 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 10.0; Win64; x64) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/91.0.4472.124 Safari/537.36', 'Accept': 'text/html,application/xhtml+xml,application/xml;q=0.9,image/webp,*/*;q=0.8', 'Accept-Language': 'en-US,en;q=0.5', 'Accept-Encoding': 'gzip, deflate', 'Connection': 'keep-alive', 'Upgrade-Insecure-Requests': '1' } # Target URLs to explore on Whitney Museum website whitney_urls = [ 'https://whitney.org/about/press', 'https://whitney.org/about/press/releases', 'https://whitney.org/collection', 'https://whitney.org/collection/acquisitions', 'https://whitney.org/about/news', 'https://whitney.org/press-releases', 'https://whitney.org/collection/recent-acquisitions', 'https://whitney.org/about/press/2022' ] print(f'Starting direct exploration of {len(whitney_urls)} Whitney Museum URLs...\n') whitney_page_data = [] successful_pages = [] for i, url in enumerate(whitney_urls, 1): print(f'Accessing URL {i}/{len(whitney_urls)}: {url}') try: response = requests.get(url, headers=headers, timeout=30) print(f' Status: {response.status_code}') if response.status_code == 200: print(f' ‚úì Successfully accessed page') print(f' Content length: {len(response.content):,} bytes') # Parse the HTML soup = BeautifulSoup(response.content, 'html.parser') # Extract basic page information page_title = soup.find('title') title_text = page_title.get_text().strip() if page_title else 'No title' print(f' Page title: {title_text}') # Save the HTML content filename = f'whitney_page_{i}_{url.split("/")[-1] or "main"}.html' filepath = os.path.join('workspace', filename) with open(filepath, 'w', encoding='utf-8') as f: f.write(response.text) print(f' Saved to: {filepath}') # Quick content analysis for 2022 and acquisition-related terms page_text = response.text.lower() # Look for key indicators indicators = { 'year_2022': '2022' in page_text, 'acquisition_terms': any(term in page_text for term in ['acquisition', 'acquired', 'new work', 'gift', 'donation']), 'photography_terms': any(term in page_text for term in ['photograph', 'photography', 'photo']), 'portrait_terms': any(term in page_text for term in ['portrait', 'figure', 'person']), 'book_terms': any(term in page_text for term in ['book', 'reading', 'holding']), 'press_release': any(term in page_text for term in ['press release', 'announcement']) } relevance_score = sum(indicators.values()) print(f' Relevance indicators found: {[k for k, v in indicators.items() if v]} (Score: {relevance_score})') # Look for links to press releases or acquisition pages press_links = [] acquisition_links = [] for link in soup.find_all('a', href=True): href = link.get('href', '').lower() link_text = link.get_text().strip().lower() if any(term in href or term in link_text for term in ['press', 'release', 'announcement']): full_url = urljoin(url, link.get('href')) press_links.append({ 'url': full_url, 'text': link.get_text().strip(), 'href': link.get('href') }) if any(term in href or term in link_text for term in ['acquisition', 'collection', 'new work']): full_url = urljoin(url, link.get('href')) acquisition_links.append({ 'url': full_url, 'text': link.get_text().strip(), 'href': link.get('href') }) if press_links: print(f' Found {len(press_links)} press-related links') for link in press_links[:3]: # Show first 3 print(f' - {link["text"][:50]}... -> {link["url"][:60]}...') if acquisition_links: print(f' Found {len(acquisition_links)} acquisition-related links') for link in acquisition_links[:3]: # Show first 3 print(f' - {link["text"][:50]}... -> {link["url"][:60]}...') page_info = { 'url': url, 'status_code': response.status_code, 'title': title_text, 'filename': filename, 'content_length': len(response.content), 'indicators': indicators, 'relevance_score': relevance_score, 'press_links': press_links, 'acquisition_links': acquisition_links, 'timestamp': time.strftime('%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S') } whitney_page_data.append(page_info) successful_pages.append(page_info) elif response.status_code == 404: print(f' ‚úó Page not found (404)') elif response.status_code == 403: print(f' ‚úó Access forbidden (403)') else: print(f' ‚úó HTTP Error: {response.status_code}') except requests.RequestException as e: print(f' ‚úó Request error: {str(e)}') except Exception as e: print(f' ‚úó Unexpected error: {str(e)}') time.sleep(2) # Be respectful to the server print() # Analyze the collected data print(f'=== INITIAL SCRAPING RESULTS ===') print(f'URLs attempted: {len(whitney_urls)}') print(f'Successful pages: {len(successful_pages)}') print(f'Total relevance score: {sum(p["relevance_score"] for p in successful_pages)}') # Identify the most promising pages high_relevance_pages = [p for p in successful_pages if p['relevance_score'] >= 3] print(f'High relevance pages (3+ indicators): {len(high_relevance_pages)}') if high_relevance_pages: print('\nMost promising pages:') for page in sorted(high_relevance_pages, key=lambda x: x['relevance_score'], reverse=True): print(f' ‚Ä¢ {page["title"][:60]}... (Score: {page["relevance_score"]})') print(f' URL: {page["url"]}') print(f' Indicators: {[k for k, v in page["indicators"].items() if v]}') print() # Collect all unique press and acquisition links for further exploration all_press_links = [] all_acquisition_links = [] for page in successful_pages: all_press_links.extend(page.get('press_links', [])) all_acquisition_links.extend(page.get('acquisition_links', [])) # Remove duplicates unique_press_links = [] unique_acquisition_links = [] for link in all_press_links: if link['url'] not in [l['url'] for l in unique_press_links]: unique_press_links.append(link) for link in all_acquisition_links: if link['url'] not in [l['url'] for l in unique_acquisition_links]: unique_acquisition_links.append(link) print(f'\n=== DISCOVERED LINKS FOR FURTHER EXPLORATION ===') print(f'Unique press-related links: {len(unique_press_links)}') print(f'Unique acquisition-related links: {len(unique_acquisition_links)}') # Filter for 2022-related links links_2022 = [] for link in unique_press_links + unique_acquisition_links: if '2022' in link['url'] or '2022' in link['text']: links_2022.append(link) print(f'Links potentially related to 2022: {len(links_2022)}') if links_2022: print('\n2022-related links found:') for link in links_2022[:5]: # Show first 5 print(f' ‚Ä¢ {link["text"][:70]}...') print(f' URL: {link["url"]}') print() # Save comprehensive results scraping_summary = { 'scraping_date': time.strftime('%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S'), 'objective': 'Direct scraping of Whitney Museum for 2022 acquisition information', 'urls_attempted': whitney_urls, 'successful_pages': len(successful_pages), 'total_pages_data': whitney_page_data, 'high_relevance_pages': high_relevance_pages, 'unique_press_links': unique_press_links, 'unique_acquisition_links': unique_acquisition_links, 'links_2022': links_2022, 'files_created': [p['filename'] for p in successful_pages] } with open('workspace/whitney_direct_scraping_results.json', 'w') as f: json.dump(scraping_summary, f, indent=2) print(f'\n=== PHASE 1 SCRAPING COMPLETE ===') print(f'Scraping results saved to: workspace/whitney_direct_scraping_results.json') print(f'HTML pages saved: {len(successful_pages)}') print(f'Next step: Analyze the most promising pages and follow 2022-related links') # Prepare for phase 2: detailed analysis of promising content if high_relevance_pages or links_2022: print(f'\nReady for Phase 2: Detailed content analysis') print(f'- {len(high_relevance_pages)} high-relevance pages to analyze') print(f'- {len(links_2022)} 2022-related links to explore') else: print(f'\nNo high-relevance content found in initial scraping.') print(f'Will proceed with broader content analysis of all collected pages.')
