Filter for 2022-related links links_2022 = [] for link in unique_press_links + unique_acquisition_links: if '2022' in link['url'] or '2022' in link['text']: links_2022.append(link) print(f'Links potentially related to 2022: {len(links_2022)}') if links_2022: print('\n2022-related links found:') for link in links_2022[:5]: # Show first 5 print(f' ‚Ä¢ {link["text"][:70]}...') print(f' URL: {link["url"]}') print() # Save comprehensive results scraping_summary = { 'scraping_date': time.strftime('%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S'), 'objective': 'Direct scraping of Whitney Museum for 2022 acquisition information', 'urls_attempted': whitney_urls, 'successful_pages': len(successful_pages), 'total_pages_data': whitney_page_data, 'high_relevance_pages': high_relevance_pages, 'unique_press_links': unique_press_links, 'unique_acquisition_links': unique_acquisition_links, 'links_2022': links_2022, 'files_created': [p['filename'] for p in successful_pages] } with open('workspace/whitney_direct_scraping_results.json', 'w') as f: json.dump(scraping_summary, f, indent=2) print(f'\n=== PHASE 1 SCRAPING COMPLETE ===') print(f'Scraping results saved to: workspace/whitney_direct_scraping_results.json') print(f'HTML pages saved: {len(successful_pages)}') print(f'Next step: Analyze the most promising pages and follow 2022-related links') # import os import requests from bs4 import BeautifulSoup import json import time from urllib.parse import urljoin, urlparse print('=== WHITNEY MUSEUM 2022 ACQUISITIONS - CORRECTED DIRECT SCRAPING ===') print('Objective: Find Whitney Museum press releases and acquisition info for 2022') print('Focus: Photographs featuring portraits or figures with books\n') # Create workspace directory if it doesn't exist if not os.path.exists('workspace'): os.makedirs('workspace') # First, let's check what files we already have from previous attempts print('=== CHECKING EXISTING WORKSPACE FILES ===') workspace_files = [f for f in os.listdir('workspace') if f.endswith('.html') or f.endswith('.json')] print(f'Found {len(workspace_files)} existing files: {workspace_files}\n') # If we have the collection page, let's analyze it first collection_file = None for f in workspace_files: if 'collection' in f and f.endswith('.html'): collection_file = f break if collection_file: print(f'=== ANALYZING EXISTING COLLECTION PAGE: {collection_file} ===') with open(os.path.join('workspace', collection_file), 'r', encoding='utf-8') as f: collection_html = f.read() print(f'Collection page content length: {len(collection_html):,} characters') # Parse the collection page to understand Whitney's site structure soup = BeautifulSoup(collection_html, 'html.parser') # Look for navigation links and site structure nav_links = [] press_links = [] acquisition_links = [] for link in soup.find_all('a', href=True): href = link.get('href', '') text = link.get_text().strip() if not href or not text: continue # Make absolute URLs if href.startswith('/'): full_url = f'https://whitney.org{href}' elif href.startswith('http'): full_url = href else: continue text_lower = text.lower() href_lower = href.lower() # Look for press/news related links if any(term in text_lower or term in href_lower for term in ['press', 'news', 'announcement', 'release']): press_links.append({'url': full_url, 'text': text, 'href': href}) # Look for acquisition/collection related links if any(term in text_lower or term in href_lower for term in ['acquisition', 'recent', 'new', 'gift', 'donate']): acquisition_links.append({'url': full_url, 'text': text, 'href': href}) # General navigation if href.startswith('/') and len(href.split('/')) <= 3: # Top-level pages nav_links.append({'url': full_url, 'text': text, 'href': href}) # Remove duplicates unique_press = list({link['url']: link for link in press_links}.values()) unique_acquisition = list({link['url']: link for link in acquisition_links}.values()) unique_nav = list({link['url']: link for link in nav_links}.values()) print(f'Found {len(unique_press)} unique press-related links') print(f'Found {len(unique_acquisition)} unique acquisition-related links') print(f'Found {len(unique_nav)} unique navigation links') # Show some examples if unique_press: print('\nPress-related links found:') for link in unique_press[:5]: print(f' ‚Ä¢ {link["text"][:50]}... -> {link["url"]}') if unique_acquisition: print('\nAcquisition-related links found:') for link in unique_acquisition[:5]: print(f' ‚Ä¢ {link["text"][:50]}... -> {link["url"]}') # Now let's try the main Whitney homepage to find the correct structure headers = { 'User-Agent': 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 10.0; Win64; x64) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/91.0.4472.124 Safari/537.36', 'Accept': 'text/html,application/xhtml+xml,application/xml;q=0.9,image/webp,*/*;q=0.8', 'Accept-Language': 'en-US,en;q=0.5', 'Connection': 'keep-alive' } print('\n=== EXPLORING WHITNEY MUSEUM HOMEPAGE ===') try: response = requests.get('https://whitney.org', headers=headers, timeout=30) print(f'Homepage status: {response.status_code}') if response.status_code == 200: print(f'‚úì Successfully accessed Whitney homepage') print(f'Content length: {len(response.content):,} bytes') # Save homepage with open('workspace/whitney_homepage.html', 'w', encoding='utf-8') as f: f.write(response.text) print('Saved homepage to: workspace/whitney_homepage.html') # Parse homepage for navigation structure homepage_soup = BeautifulSoup(response.content, 'html.parser') # Look for main navigation main_nav_links = [] # Check common navigation selectors nav_selectors = ['nav', '.nav', '.navigation', '.menu', 'header nav', '[role="navigation"]'] for selector in nav_selectors: nav_elements = homepage_soup.select(selector) if nav_elements: print(f'\nFound navigation using selector: {selector}') for nav in nav_elements: for link in nav.find_all('a', href=True): href = link.get('href', '') text = link.get_text().strip() if href and text and href.startswith('/'): full_url = f'https://whitney.org{href}' main_nav_links.append({'url': full_url, 'text': text, 'href': href}) break # Use first successful selector # Remove duplicates from main nav unique_main_nav = list({link['url']: link for link in main_nav_links}.values()) print(f'\nMain navigation links found: {len(unique_main_nav)}') for link in unique_main_nav[:10]: # Show first 10 print(f' ‚Ä¢ {link["text"]} -> {link["url"]}') # Look for press/news links specifically page_text = response.text.lower() # Search for press-related content press_indicators = page_text.count('press') + page_text.count('news') + page_text.count('announcement') acquisition_indicators = page_text.count('acquisition') + page_text.count('collection') + page_text.count('new work') year_2022_indicators = page_text.count('2022') print(f'\nContent analysis of homepage:') print(f'Press-related mentions: {press_indicators}') print(f'Acquisition-related mentions: {acquisition_indicators}') print(f'2022 mentions: {year_2022_indicators}') # Extract all links that might lead to press or acquisition info all_links = [] for link in homepage_soup.find_all('a', href=True): href = link.get('href', '') text = link.get_text().strip() if href and text: if href.startswith('/'): full_url = f'https://whitney.org{href}' elif href.startswith('http'): full_url = href else: continue all_links.append({'url': full_url, 'text': text, 'href': href}) # Filter for potentially relevant links relevant_links = [] for link in all_links: text_lower = link['text'].lower() href_lower = link['href'].lower() relevance_score = 0 # Score based on text content if any(term in text_lower for term in ['press', 'news', 'announcement', 'release']): relevance_score += 3 if any(term in text_lower for term in ['acquisition', 'collection', 'recent', 'new']): relevance_score += 3 if any(term in text_lower for term in ['2022', 'twenty twenty two']): relevance_score += 2 if any(term in text_lower for term in ['photo', 'photograph', 'image']): relevance_score += 2 if any(term in text_lower for term in ['about', 'info', 'learn']): relevance_score += 1 # Score based on URL structure if any(term in href_lower for term in ['press', 'news', 'announcement']): relevance_score += 3 if any(term in href_lower for term in ['acquisition', 'collection']): relevance_score += 3 if '2022' in href_lower: relevance_score += 2 if relevance_score >= 2: link['relevance_score'] = relevance_score relevant_links.append(link) # Sort by relevance relevant_links.sort(key=lambda x: x['relevance_score'], reverse=True) print(f'\nFound {len(relevant_links)} potentially relevant links:') for link in relevant_links[:10]: # Show top 10 print(f' ‚Ä¢ [{link["relevance_score"]}] {link["text"][:50]}... -> {link["url"]}') # Save the discovered links for next phase discovery_data = { 'timestamp': time.strftime('%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S'), 'homepage_analyzed': True, 'main_navigation_links': unique_main_nav, 'relevant_links': relevant_links[:20], # Top 20 most relevant 'content_indicators': { 'press_mentions': press_indicators, 'acquisition_mentions': acquisition_indicators, 'year_2022_mentions': year_2022_indicators } } with open('workspace/whitney_site_discovery.json', 'w') as f: json.dump(discovery_data, f, indent=2) print('\nSite discovery data saved to: workspace/whitney_site_discovery.json') else: print(f'‚úó Failed to access homepage: HTTP {response.status_code}') except Exception as e: print(f'‚úó Error accessing homepage: {str(e)}') print('\n=== PHASE 1 COMPLETE: SITE STRUCTURE DISCOVERY ===') print('Next step: Access the most promising links found for 2022 acquisition information') # Prepare URLs for next phase exploration if 'relevant_links' in locals() and relevant_links: high_priority_urls = [link['url'] for link in relevant_links[:5] if link['relevance_score'] >= 4] medium_priority_urls = [link['url'] for link in relevant_links[:10] if 3 <= link['relevance_score'] < 4] print(f'\nIdentified for next phase:') print(f'High priority URLs (score 4+): {len(high_priority_urls)}') print(f'Medium priority URLs (score 3): {len(medium_priority_urls)}') if high_priority_urls: print('\nHigh priority URLs:') for url in high_priority_urls: print(f' ‚Ä¢ {url}') if medium_priority_urls: print('\nMedium priority URLs:') for url in medium_priority_urls: print(f' ‚Ä¢ {url}') else: print('\nNo relevant links discovered. Will need to try alternative approaches.')

import os import json from datetime import datetime print('=== ANALYZING EXISTING WHITNEY MUSEUM RESEARCH FILES ===') print('Objective: Review collected data for 2022 photographic acquisitions') print('Focus: Photographs featuring portraits or figures with books\n') # First, let's inspect what files we have in workspace workspace_files = [f for f in os.listdir('workspace') if os.path.isfile(os.path.join('workspace', f))] print(f'Found {len(workspace_files)} files in workspace:') for i, filename in enumerate(workspace_files, 1): filepath = os.path.join('workspace', filename) file_size = os.path.getsize(filepath) print(f' {i:2d}. {filename} ({file_size:,} bytes)') print('\n=== INSPECTING KEY JSON FILES FOR EXISTING RESEARCH ===') # Look for the most comprehensive JSON files first json_files = [f for f in workspace_files if f.endswith('.json')] print(f'\nFound {len(json_files)} JSON files to analyze:') for json_file in json_files: print(f'\n--- Analyzing: {json_file} ---') filepath = os.path.join('workspace', json_file) try: with open(filepath, 'r', encoding='utf-8') as f: data = json.load(f) print(f'File type: JSON') print(f'Size: {os.path.getsize(filepath):,} bytes') if isinstance(data, dict): print(f'Structure: Dictionary with {len(data)} top-level keys') print(f'Keys: {list(data.keys())}') # Look for key information for key, value in data.items(): if isinstance(value, list): print(f' {key}: List with {len(value)} items') if len(value) > 0 and isinstance(value[0], dict): sample_keys = list(value[0].keys()) if value[0] else [] print(f' Sample item keys: {sample_keys[:5]}') elif isinstance(value, dict): print(f' {key}: Dictionary with {len(value)} keys') if len(value) <= 5: print(f' Keys: {list(value.keys())}') else: value_str = str(value)[:100] print(f' {key}: {type(value).__name__} = {value_str}...') # Check for 2022-related content json_str = json.dumps(data).lower() indicators = { '2022_mentions': json_str.count('2022'), 'acquisition_mentions': json_str.count('acquisition') + json_str.count('acquired'), 'photograph_mentions': json_str.count('photograph') + json_str.count('photo'), 'portrait_mentions': json_str.count('portrait'), 'book_mentions': json_str.count('book'), 'whitney_mentions': json_str.count('whitney') } relevant_indicators = {k: v for k, v in indicators.items() if v > 0} if relevant_indicators: print(f' *** RELEVANCE INDICATORS: {relevant_indicators} ***') elif isinstance(data, list): print(f'Structure: List with {len(data)} items') if len(data) > 0: print(f'First item type: {type(data[0])}') if isinstance(data[0], dict): print(f'First item keys: {list(data[0].keys())}') except json.JSONDecodeError as e: print(f'JSON decode error: {e}') except Exception as e: print(f'Error reading file: {e}') print('\n=== INSPECTING HTML FILES FOR CONTENT ===') # Look at HTML files for actual Whitney Museum content html_files = [f for f in workspace_files if f.endswith('.html')] print(f'\nFound {len(html_files)} HTML files:') for html_file in html_files: print(f'\n--- Analyzing: {html_file} ---') filepath = os.path.join('workspace', html_file) try: with open(filepath, 'r', encoding='utf-8') as f: html_content = f.read() print(f'File type: HTML') print(f'Size: {len(html_content):,} characters') # Quick content analysis content_lower = html_content.lower() # Check for key terms key_terms = { '2022': content_lower.count('2022'), 'acquisition': content_lower.count('acquisition'), 'acquired': content_lower.count('acquired'), 'photograph': content_lower.count('photograph'), 'photography': content_lower.count('photography'), 'portrait': content_lower.count('portrait'), 'book': content_lower.count('book'), 'collection': content_lower.count('collection'), 'press release': content_lower.count('press release'), 'announcement': content_lower.count('announcement') } relevant_terms = {k: v for k, v in key_terms.items() if v > 0} print(f'Key terms found: {relevant_terms}') # Look for title if '<title>' in html_content: title_start = html_content.find('<title>') + 7 title_end = html_content.find('</title>', title_start) if title_end > title_start: title = html_content[title_start:title_end].strip() print(f'Page title: {title}') # Check if this looks like Whitney Museum content if 'whitney' in content_lower and sum(relevant_terms.values()) > 5: print('*** POTENTIALLY VALUABLE WHITNEY CONTENT ***') # Look for specific 2022 acquisition content if relevant_terms.get('2022', 0) > 0 and relevant_terms.get('acquisition', 0) > 0: print('*** CONTAINS 2022 ACQUISITION INFORMATION ***') # Extract some context around 2022 mentions lines = html_content.split('\n') context_lines = [] for i, line in enumerate(lines): if '2022' in line.lower(): start = max(0, i-2) end = min(len(lines), i+3) context = lines[start:end] context_lines.extend(context) if context_lines: print('Sample 2022 context (first 10 lines):') for line in context_lines[:10]: line = line.strip() if line and len(line) > 10: print(f' {line[:100]}...') except Exception as e: print(f'Error reading HTML file: {e}') print('\n=== IDENTIFYING MOST PROMISING FILES FOR DETAILED ANALYSIS ===') # Based on the inspection, identify the most valuable files print('\nRecommendations for detailed analysis:') print('1. Look for JSON files with high relevance indicators') print('2. Examine HTML files that contain Whitney Museum content with 2022 acquisitions') print('3. Focus on files with both acquisition and photography mentions') print('\n=== INSPECTION COMPLETE ===') print('Next step: Perform detailed analysis of the most promising files')

import os import json from datetime import datetime print('=== ANALYZING EXISTING WHITNEY MUSEUM RESEARCH FILES ===') print('Objective: Review collected data for 2022 photographic acquisitions') print('Focus: Photographs featuring portraits or figures with books\n') # First, let's inspect what files we have in workspace workspace_files = [f for f in os.listdir('workspace') if os.path.isfile(os.path.join('workspace', f))] print(f'Found {len(workspace_files)} files in workspace:') for i, filename in enumerate(workspace_files, 1): filepath = os.path.join('workspace', filename) file_size = os.path.getsize(filepath) print(f' {i:2d}. {filename} ({file_size:,} bytes)') print('\n=== INSPECTING KEY JSON FILES FOR EXISTING RESEARCH ===') # Look for the most comprehensive JSON files first json_files = [f for f in workspace_files if f.endswith('.json')] print(f'\nFound {len(json_files)} JSON files to analyze:') for json_file in json_files: print(f'\n--- Analyzing: {json_file} ---') filepath = os.path.join('workspace', json_file) try: with open(filepath, 'r', encoding='utf-8') as f: data = json.load(f) print(f'File type: JSON') print(f'Size: {os.path.getsize(filepath):,} bytes') if isinstance(data, dict): print(f'Structure: Dictionary with {len(data)} top-level keys') print(f'Keys: {list(data.keys())}') # Look for key information for key, value in data.items(): if isinstance(value, list): print(f' {key}: List with {len(value)} items') if len(value) > 0 and isinstance(value[0], dict): sample_keys = list(value[0].keys()) if value[0] else [] print(f' Sample item keys: {sample_keys[:5]}') elif isinstance(value, dict): print(f' {key}: Dictionary with {len(value)} keys') if len(value) <= 5: print(f' Keys: {list(value.keys())}') else: value_str = str(value)[:100] print(f' {key}: {type(value).__name__} = {value_str}...') # Check for 2022-related content json_str = json.dumps(data).lower() indicators = { '2022_mentions': json_str.count('2022'), 'acquisition_mentions': json_str.count('acquisition') + json_str.count('acquired'), 'photograph_mentions': json_str.count('photograph') + json_str.count('photo'), 'portrait_mentions': json_str.count('portrait'), 'book_mentions': json_str.count('book'), 'whitney_mentions': json_str.count('whitney') } relevant_indicators = {k: v for k, v in indicators.items() if v > 0} if relevant_indicators: print(f' *** RELEVANCE INDICATORS: {relevant_indicators} ***') elif isinstance(data, list): print(f'Structure: List with {len(data)} items') if len(data) > 0: print(f'First item type: {type(data[0])}') if isinstance(data[0], dict): print(f'First item keys: {list(data[0].keys())}') except json.JSONDecodeError as e: print(f'JSON decode error: {e}') except Exception as e: print(f'Error reading file: {e}') print('\n=== INSPECTING HTML FILES FOR CONTENT ===') # Look at HTML files for actual Whitney Museum content html_files = [f for f in workspace_files if f.endswith('.html')] print(f'\nFound {len(html_files)} HTML files:') for html_file in html_files: print(f'\n--- Analyzing: {html_file} ---') filepath = os.path.join('workspace', html_file) try: with open(filepath, 'r', encoding='utf-8') as f: html_content = f.read() print(f'File type: HTML') print(f'Size: {len(html_content):,} characters') # Quick content analysis content_lower = html_content.lower() # Check for key terms key_terms = { '2022': content_lower.count('2022'), 'acquisition': content_lower.count('acquisition'), 'acquired': content_lower.count('acquired'), 'photograph': content_lower.count('photograph'), 'photography': content_lower.count('photography'), 'portrait': content_lower.count('portrait'), 'book': content_lower.count('book'), 'collection': content_lower.count('collection'), 'press release': content_lower.count('press release'), 'announcement': content_lower.count('announcement') } relevant_terms = {k: v for k, v in key_terms.items() if v > 0} print(f'Key terms found: {relevant_terms}') # Look for title if '<title>' in html_content: title_start = html_content.find('<title>') + 7 title_end = html_content.find('</title>', title_start) if title_end > title_start: title = html_content[title_start:title_end].strip() print(f'Page title: {title}') # Check if this looks like Whitney Museum content if 'whitney' in content_lower and sum(relevant_terms.values()) > 5: print('*** POTENTIALLY VALUABLE WHITNEY CONTENT ***') # Look for specific 2022 acquisition content if relevant_terms.get('2022', 0) > 0 and relevant_terms.get('acquisition', 0) > 0: print('*** CONTAINS 2022 ACQUISITION INFORMATION ***') # import os from bs4 import BeautifulSoup import re import json from datetime import datetime print('=== DETAILED ANALYSIS OF WHITNEY PRESS OFFICE PAGE ===') print('Target: whitney_direct_search_5.html (Whitney Press Office)') print('Objective: Extract 2022 acquisition announcements for photographs\n') # First, let's examine the most promising file: whitney_direct_search_5.html press_file = 'workspace/whitney_direct_search_5.html' if os.path.exists(press_file): print(f'Analyzing: {press_file}') print(f'File size: {os.path.getsize(press_file):,} bytes') with open(press_file, 'r', encoding='utf-8') as f: html_content = f.read() print(f'Content loaded: {len(html_content):,} characters') # Parse with BeautifulSoup soup = BeautifulSoup(html_content, 'html.parser') # Extract page title title = soup.find('title') if title: print(f'Page title: {title.get_text().strip()}') # Look for press releases or announcements print('\n=== SEARCHING FOR PRESS RELEASES AND ANNOUNCEMENTS ===') # Find all text containing 2022 text_content = soup.get_text() lines = text_content.split('\n') # Find lines mentioning 2022 lines_2022 = [] for i, line in enumerate(lines): if '2022' in line: # Get context around the 2022 mention start = max(0, i-2) end = min(len(lines), i+3) context = lines[start:end] lines_2022.append({ 'line_number': i, 'line': line.strip(), 'context': [l.strip() for l in context if l.strip()] }) print(f'Found {len(lines_2022)} lines mentioning 2022:') for i, item in enumerate(lines_2022[:10], 1): # Show first 10 print(f'\n{i}. Line {item["line_number"]}: {item["line"]}') if item['context']: print(' Context:') for ctx_line in item['context'][:5]: # Show first 5 context lines if ctx_line != item['line']: print(f' {ctx_line[:100]}...') # Look for specific acquisition-related content print('\n=== SEARCHING FOR ACQUISITION ANNOUNCEMENTS ===') # Search for acquisition keywords with 2022 acquisition_patterns = [ r'acquisition.*2022|2022.*acquisition', r'acquired.*2022|2022.*acquired', r'new work.*2022|2022.*new work', r'gift.*2022|2022.*gift', r'donation.*2022|2022.*donation', r'collection.*2022|2022.*collection' ] acquisition_matches = [] content_lower = html_content.lower() for pattern in acquisition_patterns: matches = re.finditer(pattern, content_lower, re.IGNORECASE) for match in matches: # Get surrounding context start = max(0, match.start() - 200) end = min(len(html_content), match.end() + 200) context = html_content[start:end] acquisition_matches.append({ 'pattern': pattern, 'match_text': match.group(), 'context': context.replace('\n', ' ').strip() }) print(f'Found {len(acquisition_matches)} acquisition-related matches:') for i, match in enumerate(acquisition_matches[:5], 1): # Show first 5 print(f'\n{i}. Pattern: {match["pattern"]}') print(f' Match: {match["match_text"]}') print(f' Context: {match["context"][:300]}...') # Look for photography-related content with 2022 print('\n=== SEARCHING FOR PHOTOGRAPHY CONTENT ===') photo_patterns = [ r'photograph.*2022|2022.*photograph', r'photography.*2022|2022.*photography', r'photo.*2022|2022.*photo', r'image.*2022|2022.*image' ] photo_matches = [] for pattern in photo_patterns: matches = re.finditer(pattern, content_lower, re.IGNORECASE) for match in matches: start = max(0, match.start() - 200) end = min(len(html_content), match.end() + 200) context = html_content[start:end] photo_matches.append({ 'pattern': pattern, 'match_text': match.group(), 'context': context.replace('\n', ' ').strip() }) print(f'Found {len(photo_matches)} photography-related matches:') for i, match in enumerate(photo_matches[:5], 1): # Show first 5 print(f'\n{i}. Pattern: {match["pattern"]}') print(f' Match: {match["match_text"]}') print(f' Context: {match["context"][:300]}...') # Look for press release links or sections print('\n=== SEARCHING FOR PRESS RELEASE LINKS ===') press_links = [] for link in soup.find_all('a', href=True): href = link.get('href', '') text = link.get_text().strip() if any(term in href.lower() or term in text.lower() for term in ['press', 'release', 'announcement', 'news']): # Check if it's related to 2022 if '2022' in href or '2022' in text: press_links.append({ 'url': href, 'text': text, 'is_2022_related': True }) else: press_links.append({ 'url': href, 'text': text, 'is_2022_related': False }) # Remove duplicates unique_press_links = list({link['url']: link for link in press_links}.values()) print(f'Found {len(unique_press_links)} press-related links:') # Prioritize 2022-related links links_2022 = [link for link in unique_press_links if link['is_2022_related']] other_links = [link for link in unique_press_links if not link['is_2022_related']] if links_2022: print(f'\n2022-related press links ({len(links_2022)}):' ) for link in links_2022: print(f' ‚Ä¢ {link["text"][:60]}... -> {link["url"]}') if other_links: print(f'\nOther press links ({len(other_links[:10])}):') # Show first 10 for link in other_links[:10]: print(f' ‚Ä¢ {link["text"][:60]}... -> {link["url"]}') # Look for specific sections or headings about acquisitions print('\n=== SEARCHING FOR ACQUISITION SECTIONS ===') headings = soup.find_all(['h1', 'h2', 'h3', 'h4', 'h5', 'h6']) acquisition_headings = [] for heading in headings: text = heading.get_text().strip() if any(term in text.lower() for term in ['acquisition', 'collection', 'new work', 'gift']): acquisition_headings.append({ 'tag': heading.name, 'text': text, 'has_2022': '2022' in text }) print(f'Found {len(acquisition_headings)} acquisition-related headings:') for heading in acquisition_headings: marker = '‚òÖ' if heading['has_2022'] else '‚Ä¢' print(f' {marker} [{heading["tag"].upper()}] {heading["text"]}') # Save detailed analysis results analysis_results = { 'analysis_timestamp': datetime.now().strftime('%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S'), 'file_analyzed': press_file, 'page_title': title.get_text().strip() if title else 'No title', 'content_stats': { 'total_characters': len(html_content), 'lines_with_2022': len(lines_2022), 'acquisition_matches': len(acquisition_matches), 'photography_matches': len(photo_matches), 'press_links_found': len(unique_press_links), 'press_links_2022': len(links_2022) }, 'lines_mentioning_2022': lines_2022[:20], # First 20 'acquisition_matches': acquisition_matches, 'photography_matches': photo_matches, 'press_links_2022': links_2022, 'other_press_links': other_links[:10], # First 10 'acquisition_headings': acquisition_headings } with open('workspace/whitney_press_office_detailed_analysis.json', 'w') as f: json.dump(analysis_results, f, indent=2) print(f'\n=== ANALYSIS COMPLETE ===') print(f'Detailed analysis saved to: workspace/whitney_press_office_detailed_analysis.json') # Summary of findings print(f'\n=== SUMMARY OF FINDINGS ===') print(f'‚Ä¢ Lines mentioning 2022: {len(lines_2022)}') print(f'‚Ä¢ Acquisition-related matches: {len(acquisition_matches)}') print(f'‚Ä¢ Photography-related matches: {len(photo_matches)}') print(f'‚Ä¢ Press links found: {len(unique_press_links)}') print(f'‚Ä¢ 2022-specific press links: {len(links_2022)}') print(f'‚Ä¢ Acquisition-related headings: {len(acquisition_headings)}') if acquisition_matches and photo_matches: print('\n‚òÖ PROMISING: Found both acquisition and photography content with 2022 mentions') elif acquisition_matches: print('\n‚óÜ PARTIAL: Found acquisition content with 2022 mentions') elif photo_matches: print('\n‚óÜ PARTIAL: Found photography content with 2022 mentions') else: print('\n‚óã LIMITED: No direct acquisition+photography matches found') else: print(f'File not found: {press_file}') print('Available files:') for f in os.listdir('workspace'): if f.endswith('.html'): print(f' ‚Ä¢ {f}')

Pattern: {match["pattern"]}') print(f' Match: {match["match_text"]}') print(f' Context: {match["context"][:300]}...') # Look for press release links or sections print('\n=== SEARCHING FOR PRESS RELEASE LINKS ===') press_links = [] for link in soup.find_all('a', href=True): href = link.get('href', '') text = link.get_text().strip() if any(term in href.lower() or term in text.lower() for term in ['press', 'release', 'announcement', 'news']): # Check if it's related to 2022 if '2022' in href or '2022' in text: press_links.append({ 'url': href, 'text': text, 'is_2022_related': True }) else: press_links.append({ 'url': href, 'text': text, 'is_2022_related': False }) # Remove duplicates unique_press_links = list({link['url']: link for link in press_links}.values()) print(f'Found {len(unique_press_links)} press-related links:') # Prioritize 2022-related links links_2022 = [link for link in unique_press_links if link['is_2022_related']] other_links = [link for link in unique_press_links if not link['is_2022_related']] if links_2022: print(f'\n2022-related press links ({len(links_2022)}):' ) for link in links_2022: print(f' ‚Ä¢ {link["text"][:60]}... -> {link["url"]}') if other_links: print(f'\nOther press links ({len(other_links[:10])}):') # Show first 10 for link in other_links[:10]: print(f' ‚Ä¢ {link["text"][:60]}... -> {link["url"]}') # Look for specific sections or headings about acquisitions print('\n=== SEARCHING FOR ACQUISITION SECTIONS ===') headings = soup.find_all(['h1', 'h2', 'h3', 'h4', 'h5', 'h6']) acquisition_headings = [] for heading in headings: text = heading.get_text().strip() if any(term in text.lower() for term in ['acquisition', 'collection', 'new work', 'gift']): acquisition_headings.append({ 'tag': heading.name, 'text': text, 'has_2022': '2022' in text }) print(f'Found {len(acquisition_headings)} acquisition-related headings:') for heading in acquisition_headings: marker = '‚òÖ' if heading['has_2022'] else '‚Ä¢' print(f' {marker} [{heading["tag"].upper()}] {heading["text"]}') # import os from bs4 import BeautifulSoup import re import json from datetime import datetime print('=== WHITNEY MUSEUM 2022 ACQUISITIONS - FIXED PRESS OFFICE ANALYSIS ===') print('Objective: Complete analysis of Whitney Press Office page for 2022 photographic acquisitions') print('Focus: Press releases and acquisition announcements about photographs with portraits/books\n') # Create workspace directory if it doesn't exist if not os.path.exists('workspace'): os.makedirs('workspace') # First, let's check what HTML files we have available print('=== CHECKING AVAILABLE HTML FILES ===') html_files = [f for f in os.listdir('workspace') if f.endswith('.html')] print(f'Found {len(html_files)} HTML files:') for i, f in enumerate(html_files, 1): file_size = os.path.getsize(os.path.join('workspace', f)) print(f' {i}. {f} ({file_size:,} bytes)') # Look for the Whitney Press Office file specifically press_office_files = [f for f in html_files if 'press' in f.lower() or 'direct_search_5' in f] if press_office_files: target_file = press_office_files[0] print(f'\nAnalyzing Whitney Press Office file: {target_file}') else: # Use any Whitney HTML file that might contain press information target_file = html_files[0] if html_files else None print(f'\nUsing available HTML file: {target_file}') if target_file: filepath = os.path.join('workspace', target_file) print(f'File path: {filepath}') print(f'File size: {os.path.getsize(filepath):,} bytes') # Load and parse the HTML content with open(filepath, 'r', encoding='utf-8') as f: html_content = f.read() print(f'Content loaded: {len(html_content):,} characters') # Parse with BeautifulSoup soup = BeautifulSoup(html_content, 'html.parser') # Extract basic page information title = soup.find('title') page_title = title.get_text().strip() if title else 'No title found' print(f'Page title: {page_title}') # Get all text content for analysis text_content = soup.get_text() content_lower = text_content.lower() print('\n=== CONTENT ANALYSIS FOR 2022 ACQUISITIONS ===') # Count key terms key_terms = { '2022': content_lower.count('2022'), 'acquisition': content_lower.count('acquisition'), 'acquired': content_lower.count('acquired'), 'photograph': content_lower.count('photograph'), 'photography': content_lower.count('photography'), 'portrait': content_lower.count('portrait'), 'book': content_lower.count('book'), 'press release': content_lower.count('press release'), 'announcement': content_lower.count('announcement'), 'collection': content_lower.count('collection') } print('Key term frequencies:') for term, count in key_terms.items(): if count > 0: print(f' ‚Ä¢ {term}: {count} mentions') # Search for 2022-related content with context print('\n=== SEARCHING FOR 2022 CONTENT WITH CONTEXT ===') lines = text_content.split('\n') lines_with_2022 = [] for i, line in enumerate(lines): line_stripped = line.strip() if '2022' in line_stripped and len(line_stripped) > 5: # Get surrounding context context_start = max(0, i-2) context_end = min(len(lines), i+3) context_lines = [] for j in range(context_start, context_end): ctx_line = lines[j].strip() if ctx_line and len(ctx_line) > 5: context_lines.append(ctx_line) lines_with_2022.append({ 'line_number': i, 'line': line_stripped, 'context': context_lines }) print(f'Found {len(lines_with_2022)} substantial lines mentioning 2022:') for i, item in enumerate(lines_with_2022[:8], 1): # Show first 8 print(f'\n{i}. Line {item["line_number"]}: {item["line"][:100]}...') if item['context']: print(' Context:') for ctx_line in item['context'][:3]: # Show first 3 context lines if ctx_line != item['line'] and len(ctx_line) > 10: print(f' {ctx_line[:80]}...') # Look for acquisition announcements with 2022 print('\n=== SEARCHING FOR 2022 ACQUISITION ANNOUNCEMENTS ===') # Use regex to find acquisition-related content near 2022 acquisition_keywords = ['acquisition', 'acquired', 'new work', 'gift', 'donation', 'added to collection'] acquisition_contexts = [] for keyword in acquisition_keywords: # Search for keyword within 100 characters of 2022 pattern = rf'.{{0,100}}{re.escape(keyword)}.{{0,100}}2022.{{0,100}}|.{{0,100}}2022.{{0,100}}{re.escape(keyword)}.{{0,100}}' matches = re.finditer(pattern, content_lower, re.IGNORECASE | re.DOTALL) for match in matches: context_text = match.group() # Clean up the context clean_context = re.sub(r'\s+', ' ', context_text).strip() if len(clean_context) > 20: acquisition_contexts.append({ 'keyword': keyword, 'context': clean_context, 'position': match.start() }) print(f'Found {len(acquisition_contexts)} acquisition contexts with 2022:') for i, ctx in enumerate(acquisition_contexts[:5], 1): # Show first 5 print(f'\n{i}. Keyword: "{ctx["keyword"]}"') print(f' Context: {ctx["context"][:200]}...') # Look for photography-related content with 2022 print('\n=== SEARCHING FOR 2022 PHOTOGRAPHY CONTENT ===') photo_keywords = ['photograph', 'photography', 'photo', 'image', 'picture'] photo_contexts = [] for keyword in photo_keywords: pattern = rf'.{{0,100}}{re.escape(keyword)}.{{0,100}}2022.{{0,100}}|.{{0,100}}2022.{{0,100}}{re.escape(keyword)}.{{0,100}}' matches = re.finditer(pattern, content_lower, re.IGNORECASE | re.DOTALL) for match in matches: context_text = match.group() clean_context = re.sub(r'\s+', ' ', context_text).strip() if len(clean_context) > 20: photo_contexts.append({ 'keyword': keyword, 'context': clean_context, 'position': match.start() }) print(f'Found {len(photo_contexts)} photography contexts with 2022:') for i, ctx in enumerate(photo_contexts[:5], 1): # Show first 5 print(f'\n{i}. Keyword: "{ctx["keyword"]}"') print(f' Context: {ctx["context"][:200]}...') # Extract all links for press releases and announcements print('\n=== EXTRACTING PRESS RELEASE LINKS ===') all_links = [] for link_element in soup.find_all('a', href=True): link_href = link_element.get('href', '') link_text = link_element.get_text().strip() if link_href and link_text: all_links.append({ 'url': link_href, 'text': link_text }) # Filter for press-related links press_keywords = ['press', 'release', 'announcement', 'news'] press_links = [] for link in all_links: link_text_lower = link['text'].lower() link_url_lower = link['url'].lower() # Check if link is press-related is_press_related = any(keyword in link_text_lower or keyword in link_url_lower for keyword in press_keywords) if is_press_related: # Check if it mentions 2022 has_2022 = '2022' in link['text'] or '2022' in link['url'] press_links.append({ 'url': link['url'], 'text': link['text'], 'has_2022': has_2022, 'relevance_score': 3 if has_2022 else 1 }) # Remove duplicates and sort by relevance unique_press_links = list({link['url']: link for link in press_links}.values()) unique_press_links.sort(key=lambda x: x['relevance_score'], reverse=True) print(f'Found {len(unique_press_links)} press-related links:') links_with_2022 = [link for link in unique_press_links if link['has_2022']] other_links = [link for link in unique_press_links if not link['has_2022']] if links_with_2022: print(f'\n2022-related press links ({len(links_with_2022)}):') for link in links_with_2022: print(f' ‚òÖ {link["text"][:60]}... -> {link["url"]}') if other_links: print(f'\nOther press links ({len(other_links[:8])}):') for link in other_links[:8]: # Show first 8 print(f' ‚Ä¢ {link["text"][:60]}... -> {link["url"]}') # Look for section headings about acquisitions or collections print('\n=== SEARCHING FOR ACQUISITION-RELATED HEADINGS ===') headings = soup.find_all(['h1', 'h2', 'h3', 'h4', 'h5', 'h6']) relevant_headings = [] for heading in headings: heading_text = heading.get_text().strip() heading_lower = heading_text.lower() # Check for acquisition/collection keywords is_relevant = any(keyword in heading_lower for keyword in ['acquisition', 'collection', 'new work', 'gift', 'recent']) if is_relevant: has_2022 = '2022' in heading_text relevant_headings.append({ 'tag': heading.name, 'text': heading_text, 'has_2022': has_2022 }) print(f'Found {len(relevant_headings)} relevant headings:') for heading in relevant_headings: marker = '‚òÖ' if heading['has_2022'] else '‚Ä¢' print(f' {marker} [{heading["tag"].upper()}] {heading["text"]}') # Compile comprehensive analysis results analysis_results = { 'analysis_timestamp': datetime.now().strftime('%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S'), 'file_analyzed': target_file, 'page_title': page_title, 'objective': 'Find Whitney Museum 2022 photographic acquisitions featuring portraits/figures with books', 'content_statistics': { 'total_characters': len(html_content), 'key_term_counts': key_terms, 'lines_with_2022': len(lines_with_2022), 'acquisition_contexts_found': len(acquisition_contexts), 'photography_contexts_found': len(photo_contexts), 'press_links_total': len(unique_press_links), 'press_links_with_2022': len(links_with_2022), 'relevant_headings': len(relevant_headings) }, 'key_findings': { 'lines_mentioning_2022': lines_with_2022[:10], # First 10 'acquisition_contexts': acquisition_contexts, 'photography_contexts': photo_contexts, 'press_links_2022': links_with_2022, 'other_press_links': other_links[:5], # First 5 'relevant_headings': relevant_headings } } # Save comprehensive results output_filename = 'workspace/whitney_2022_acquisitions_comprehensive_analysis.json' with open(output_filename, 'w') as f: json.dump(analysis_results, f, indent=2) print(f'\n=== COMPREHENSIVE ANALYSIS COMPLETE ===') print(f'Results saved to: {output_filename}') # Summary assessment print(f'\n=== SUMMARY ASSESSMENT ===') print(f'Page analyzed: {page_title}') print(f'2022 mentions: {key_terms["2022"]} times') print(f'Acquisition contexts with 2022: {len(acquisition_contexts)}') print(f'Photography contexts with 2022: {len(photo_contexts)}') print(f'2022-specific press links: {len(links_with_2022)}') # Determine if we found promising content if acquisition_contexts and photo_contexts: print('\n‚òÖ‚òÖ‚òÖ EXCELLENT: Found both acquisition and photography content with 2022 references') recommendation = 'High probability of finding 2022 photographic acquisitions' elif acquisition_contexts: print('\n‚òÖ‚òÖ GOOD: Found acquisition content with 2022 references') recommendation = 'Moderate probability of finding 2022 acquisitions' elif photo_contexts: print('\n‚òÖ‚òÖ GOOD: Found photography content with 2022 references') recommendation = 'Moderate probability of relevant photography content' elif links_with_2022: print('\n‚òÖ FAIR: Found 2022-related press links to explore') recommendation = 'Links available for further investigation' else: print('\n‚óã LIMITED: Minimal 2022 acquisition/photography content found') recommendation = 'May need to explore alternative approaches' print(f'Recommendation: {recommendation}') # If we found promising links, suggest next steps if links_with_2022: print(f'\nSuggested next steps:') print(f'1. Access the {len(links_with_2022)} 2022-related press links found') print(f'2. Search for specific press releases about photographic acquisitions') print(f'3. Look for announcements mentioning portraits or figures with books') else: print('No HTML files found in workspace to analyze') print('Available files:') for f in os.listdir('workspace'): print(f' ‚Ä¢ {f}')

Line {item["line_number"]}: {item["line"][:100]}...') if item['context']: print(' Context:') for ctx_line in item['context'][:3]: # Show first 3 context lines if ctx_line != item['line'] and len(ctx_line) > 10: print(f' {ctx_line[:80]}...') # Look for acquisition announcements with 2022 print('\n=== SEARCHING FOR 2022 ACQUISITION ANNOUNCEMENTS ===') # Use regex to find acquisition-related content near 2022 acquisition_keywords = ['acquisition', 'acquired', 'new work', 'gift', 'donation', 'added to collection'] acquisition_contexts = [] for keyword in acquisition_keywords: # Search for keyword within 100 characters of 2022 pattern = rf'.{{0,100}}{re.escape(keyword)}.{{0,100}}2022.{{0,100}}|.{{0,100}}2022.{{0,100}}{re.escape(keyword)}.{{0,100}}' matches = re.finditer(pattern, content_lower, re.IGNORECASE | re.DOTALL) for match in matches: context_text = match.group() # Clean up the context clean_context = re.sub(r'\s+', ' ', context_text).strip() if len(clean_context) > 20: acquisition_contexts.append({ 'keyword': keyword, 'context': clean_context, 'position': match.start() }) print(f'Found {len(acquisition_contexts)} acquisition contexts with 2022:') for i, ctx in enumerate(acquisition_contexts[:5], 1): # Show first 5 print(f'\n{i}. Keyword: "{ctx["keyword"]}"') print(f' Context: {ctx["context"][:200]}...') # Look for photography-related content with 2022 print('\n=== SEARCHING FOR 2022 PHOTOGRAPHY CONTENT ===') photo_keywords = ['photograph', 'photography', 'photo', 'image', 'picture'] photo_contexts = [] for keyword in photo_keywords: pattern = rf'.{{0,100}}{re.escape(keyword)}.{{0,100}}2022.{{0,100}}|.{{0,100}}2022.{{0,100}}{re.escape(keyword)}.{{0,100}}' matches = re.finditer(pattern, content_lower, re.IGNORECASE | re.DOTALL) for match in matches: context_text = match.group() clean_context = re.sub(r'\s+', ' ', context_text).strip() if len(clean_context) > 20: photo_contexts.append({ 'keyword': keyword, 'context': clean_context, 'position': match.start() }) print(f'Found {len(photo_contexts)} photography contexts with 2022:') for i, ctx in enumerate(photo_contexts[:5], 1): # Show first 5 print(f'\n{i}. Keyword: "{ctx["keyword"]}"') print(f' Context: {ctx["context"][:200]}...') # Extract all links for press releases and announcements print('\n=== EXTRACTING PRESS RELEASE LINKS ===') all_links = [] for link_element in soup.find_all('a', href=True): link_href = link_element.get('href', '') link_text = link_element.get_text().strip() if link_href and link_text: all_links.append({ 'url': link_href, 'text': link_text }) # Filter for press-related links press_keywords = ['press', 'release', 'announcement', 'news'] press_links = [] for link in all_links: link_text_lower = link['text'].lower() link_url_lower = link['url'].lower() # Check if link is press-related is_press_related = any(keyword in link_text_lower or keyword in link_url_lower for keyword in press_keywords) if is_press_related: # Check if it mentions 2022 has_2022 = '2022' in link['text'] or '2022' in link['url'] press_links.append({ 'url': link['url'], 'text': link['text'], 'has_2022': has_2022, 'relevance_score': 3 if has_2022 else 1 }) # Remove duplicates and sort by relevance unique_press_links = list({link['url']: link for link in press_links}.values()) unique_press_links.sort(key=lambda x: x['relevance_score'], reverse=True) print(f'Found {len(unique_press_links)} press-related links:') links_with_2022 = [link for link in unique_press_links if link['has_2022']] other_links = [link for link in unique_press_links if not link['has_2022']] if links_with_2022: print(f'\n2022-related press links ({len(links_with_2022)}):') for link in links_with_2022: print(f' ‚òÖ {link["text"][:60]}... -> {link["url"]}') if other_links: print(f'\nOther press links ({len(other_links[:8])}):') for link in other_links[:8]: # Show first 8 print(f' ‚Ä¢ {link["text"][:60]}... -> {link["url"]}') # Look for section headings about acquisitions or collections print('\n=== SEARCHING FOR ACQUISITION-RELATED HEADINGS ===') headings = soup.find_all(['h1', 'h2', 'h3', 'h4', 'h5', 'h6']) relevant_headings = [] for heading in headings: heading_text = heading.get_text().strip() heading_lower = heading_text.lower() # Check for acquisition/collection keywords is_relevant = any(keyword in heading_lower for keyword in ['acquisition', 'collection', 'new work', 'gift', 'recent']) if is_relevant: has_2022 = '2022' in heading_text relevant_headings.append({ 'tag': heading.name, 'text': heading_text, 'has_2022': has_2022 }) print(f'Found {len(relevant_headings)} relevant headings:') for heading in relevant_headings: marker = '‚òÖ' if heading['has_2022'] else '‚Ä¢' print(f' {marker} [{heading["tag"].upper()}] {heading["text"]}') # Space between queries # Rate limiting import time time.sleep(1) # Sort all results by relevance score all_results.sort(key=lambda x: x['relevance_score'], reverse=True) whitney_official_results.sort(key=lambda x: x['relevance_score'], reverse=True) art_news_results.sort(key=lambda x: x['relevance_score'], reverse=True) print(f'\n=== SEARCH RESULTS SUMMARY ===\n') print(f'Total results collected: {len(all_results)}') print(f'Whitney official results: {len(whitney_official_results)}') print(f'Art news source results: {len(art_news_results)}') # Show top results by category high_relevance_results = [r for r in all_results if r['relevance_score'] >= 8] medium_relevance_results = [r for r in all_results if 5 <= r['relevance_score'] < 8] print(f'High relevance results (8+): {len(high_relevance_results)}') print(f'Medium relevance results (5-7): {len(medium_relevance_results)}') if high_relevance_results: print(f'\n=== TOP HIGH RELEVANCE RESULTS ===\n') for i, result in enumerate(high_relevance_results[:5], 1): print(f'{i}. import os import requests from bs4 import BeautifulSoup import json from datetime import datetime import time import re print('=== WHITNEY MUSEUM 2022 PRESS RELEASES - DIRECT WEB SCRAPING ===') print('Objective: Find Whitney Museum press releases about 2022 photographic acquisitions') print('Focus: Press releases mentioning portraits or figures with books\n') # Create workspace directory if it doesn't exist if not os.path.exists('workspace'): os.makedirs('workspace') # Set up headers for web scraping headers = { 'User-Agent': 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 10.0; Win64; x64) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/91.0.4472.124 Safari/537.36', 'Accept': 'text/html,application/xhtml+xml,application/xml;q=0.9,image/webp,*/*;q=0.8', 'Accept-Language': 'en-US,en;q=0.5', 'Accept-Encoding': 'gzip, deflate', 'Connection': 'keep-alive', 'Upgrade-Insecure-Requests': '1' } # Target URLs for Whitney Museum press and news content whitney_urls = [ 'https://whitney.org/about/press', 'https://whitney.org/about/press/releases', 'https://whitney.org/about/press/news', 'https://whitney.org/collection/recent-acquisitions', 'https://whitney.org/about/news', 'https://whitney.org/press-releases', 'https://whitney.org/about/press-office', 'https://whitney.org/collection/acquisitions' ] print(f'Attempting to access {len(whitney_urls)} Whitney Museum URLs...\n') scraped_pages = [] press_release_links = [] for i, url in enumerate(whitney_urls, 1): print(f'{i}. Accessing: {url}') try: response = requests.get(url, headers=headers, timeout=30) if response.status_code == 200: print(f' ‚úì Success (Status: {response.status_code})') print(f' Content length: {len(response.content):,} bytes') # Parse the HTML content soup = BeautifulSoup(response.content, 'html.parser') # Extract page title title = soup.find('title') page_title = title.get_text().strip() if title else 'No title found' print(f' Page title: {page_title}') # Get all text content for analysis text_content = soup.get_text() content_lower = text_content.lower() # Count key terms key_terms = { '2022': content_lower.count('2022'), 'acquisition': content_lower.count('acquisition'), 'acquired': content_lower.count('acquired'), 'photograph': content_lower.count('photograph'), 'photography': content_lower.count('photography'), 'portrait': content_lower.count('portrait'), 'book': content_lower.count('book'), 'press release': content_lower.count('press release'), 'announcement': content_lower.count('announcement') } relevant_terms = {k: v for k, v in key_terms.items() if v > 0} if relevant_terms: print(f' Key terms found: {relevant_terms}') # Look for press release links on this page page_links = [] for link in soup.find_all('a', href=True): link_href = link.get('href', '') link_text = link.get_text().strip() if link_href and link_text: # Check if link is press release related link_lower = f'{link_text} {link_href}'.lower() is_press_related = any(term in link_lower for term in ['press', 'release', 'announcement', 'news', 'acquisition']) has_2022 = '2022' in link_lower if is_press_related: # Make sure href is a full URL if link_href.startswith('/'): full_url = 'https://whitney.org' + link_href elif link_href.startswith('http'): full_url = link_href else: full_url = 'https://whitney.org/' + link_href page_links.append({ 'url': full_url, 'text': link_text, 'has_2022': has_2022, 'source_page': url }) print(f' Found {len(page_links)} press-related links on this page') # Add links with 2022 to our master list links_with_2022 = [link for link in page_links if link['has_2022']] if links_with_2022: print(f' ‚òÖ {len(links_with_2022)} links mention 2022') press_release_links.extend(links_with_2022) # Save page data page_data = { 'url': url, 'status_code': response.status_code, 'page_title': page_title, 'content_length': len(response.content), 'key_terms': key_terms, 'press_links_found': len(page_links), 'links_with_2022': len(links_with_2022), 'scraped_successfully': True } scraped_pages.append(page_data) # Save HTML content if it contains 2022 references if key_terms.get('2022', 0) > 0: filename = f'workspace/whitney_page_{i}_with_2022.html' with open(filename, 'w', encoding='utf-8') as f: f.write(response.text) print(f' ‚òÖ Saved page with 2022 content: {filename}') page_data['saved_file'] = filename else: print(f' ‚úó Failed (Status: {response.status_code})') scraped_pages.append({ 'url': url, 'status_code': response.status_code, 'error': f'HTTP {response.status_code}', 'scraped_successfully': False }) except Exception as e: print(f' ‚úó Exception: {str(e)}') scraped_pages.append({ 'url': url, 'error': str(e), 'scraped_successfully': False }) print() time.sleep(2) # Be respectful to the server # Remove duplicate press release links unique_press_links = list({link['url']: link for link in press_release_links}.values()) print(f'=== INITIAL SCRAPING SUMMARY ===') successful_pages = [p for p in scraped_pages if p.get('scraped_successfully', False)] print(f'Successfully scraped: {len(successful_pages)}/{len(whitney_urls)} pages') print(f'Unique press release links found: {len(unique_press_links)}') # Show press release links with 2022 if unique_press_links: print(f'\n=== PRESS RELEASE LINKS WITH 2022 REFERENCES ===') for i, link in enumerate(unique_press_links, 1): print(f'{i}. {link["text"][:60]}...') print(f' URL: {link["url"]}') print(f' Source: {link["source_page"]}') print() # Now try to access the most promising press release links if unique_press_links: print(f'=== ACCESSING PRESS RELEASE PAGES ===') press_release_content = [] for i, link in enumerate(unique_press_links[:5], 1): # Access first 5 links print(f'{i}. Accessing press release: {link["text"][:50]}...') print(f' URL: {link["url"]}') try: response = requests.get(link['url'], headers=headers, timeout=30) if response.status_code == 200: print(f' ‚úì Success (Status: {response.status_code})') # Parse the press release content soup = BeautifulSoup(response.content, 'html.parser') # Extract title title = soup.find('title') page_title = title.get_text().strip() if title else 'No title' # Get text content text_content = soup.get_text() content_lower = text_content.lower() # Check for key acquisition and photography terms acquisition_score = 0 if 'acquisition' in content_lower or 'acquired' in content_lower: acquisition_score += 3 if 'photograph' in content_lower or 'photography' in content_lower: acquisition_score += 3 if 'portrait' in content_lower: acquisition_score += 2 if 'book' in content_lower: acquisition_score += 2 if '2022' in content_lower: acquisition_score += 2 print(f' Title: {page_title}') print(f' Content length: {len(text_content):,} characters') print(f' Acquisition relevance score: {acquisition_score}') # Look for specific phrases about acquisitions acquisition_phrases = [] lines = text_content.split('\n') for line in lines: line_lower = line.lower().strip() if any(term in line_lower for term in ['acquisition', 'acquired', 'new work', 'gift']) and '2022' in line_lower: if len(line.strip()) > 20: acquisition_phrases.append(line.strip()) if acquisition_phrases: print(f' ‚òÖ Found {len(acquisition_phrases)} acquisition-related phrases with 2022:') for phrase in acquisition_phrases[:3]: # Show first 3 print(f' "{phrase[:100]}..."') # Save high-relevance press releases if acquisition_score >= 5: filename = f'workspace/whitney_press_release_{i}_score_{acquisition_score}.html' with open(filename, 'w', encoding='utf-8') as f: f.write(response.text) print(f' ‚òÖ‚òÖ Saved high-relevance press release: {filename}') press_release_content.append({ 'url': link['url'], 'title': page_title, 'original_link_text': link['text'], 'acquisition_score': acquisition_score, 'content_length': len(text_content), 'acquisition_phrases': acquisition_phrases, 'saved_file': filename if acquisition_score >= 5 else None }) else: print(f' ‚úó Failed (Status: {response.status_code})') except Exception as e: print(f' ‚úó Exception: {str(e)}') print() time.sleep(2) # Rate limiting # Compile comprehensive results scraping_results = { 'scraping_timestamp': datetime.now().strftime('%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S'), 'objective': 'Find Whitney Museum 2022 press releases about photographic acquisitions', 'urls_attempted': whitney_urls, 'successful_pages': len(successful_pages), 'total_press_links_found': len(unique_press_links), 'press_releases_accessed': len(press_release_content) if 'press_release_content' in locals() else 0, 'scraped_pages_summary': scraped_pages, 'press_release_links': unique_press_links, 'press_release_content': press_release_content if 'press_release_content' in locals() else [] } # Save comprehensive results output_filename = 'workspace/whitney_2022_press_releases_scraping.json' with open(output_filename, 'w') as f: json.dump(scraping_results, f, indent=2) print(f'=== SCRAPING COMPLETE ===') print(f'Comprehensive results saved to: {output_filename}') # Summary and assessment print(f'\n=== FINAL ASSESSMENT ===') print(f'Pages successfully scraped: {len(successful_pages)}/{len(whitney_urls)}') print(f'Press release links with 2022: {len(unique_press_links)}') if 'press_release_content' in locals(): high_relevance_releases = [pr for pr in press_release_content if pr['acquisition_score'] >= 5] print(f'High-relevance press releases found: {len(high_relevance_releases)}') if high_relevance_releases: print(f'\n‚òÖ‚òÖ‚òÖ EXCELLENT: Found {len(high_relevance_releases)} high-relevance press releases') print(f'These likely contain information about 2022 photographic acquisitions') print(f'\nTop results:') for i, pr in enumerate(high_relevance_releases[:3], 1): print(f'{i}. {pr["title"]} (Score: {pr["acquisition_score"]})') print(f' URL: {pr["url"]}') if pr['acquisition_phrases']: print(f' Key phrase: "{pr["acquisition_phrases"][0][:80]}..."') print() elif press_release_content: print(f'‚òÖ MODERATE: Found {len(press_release_content)} press releases to review') print(f'May contain relevant acquisition information') else: print(f'‚óã LIMITED: No high-relevance press releases found') else: print(f'‚óã LIMITED: No press release content accessed') print(f'\nRecommendation: Review saved HTML files for detailed acquisition information') print(f'Files to examine:') for page in scraped_pages: if page.get('saved_file'): print(f' ‚Ä¢ {page["saved_file"]} - Page with 2022 content') if 'press_release_content' in locals(): for pr in press_release_content: if pr.get('saved_file'): print(f' ‚Ä¢ {pr["saved_file"]} - High-relevance press release')

Be respectful to the server # Remove duplicate press release links unique_press_links = list({link['url']: link for link in press_release_links}.values()) print(f'=== INITIAL SCRAPING SUMMARY ===') successful_pages = [p for p in scraped_pages if p.get('scraped_successfully', False)] print(f'Successfully scraped: {len(successful_pages)}/{len(whitney_urls)} pages') print(f'Unique press release links found: {len(unique_press_links)}') # Check for key acquisition and photography terms acquisition_score = 0 if 'acquisition' in content_lower or 'acquired' in content_lower: acquisition_score += 3 if 'photograph' in content_lower or 'photography' in content_lower: acquisition_score += 3 if 'portrait' in content_lower: acquisition_score += 2 if 'book' in content_lower: acquisition_score += 2 if '2022' in content_lower: acquisition_score += 2 print(f' Title: {page_title}') print(f' Content length: {len(text_content):,} characters') print(f' Acquisition relevance score: {acquisition_score}') # import os import requests from bs4 import BeautifulSoup import json from datetime import datetime import time print('=== WHITNEY MUSEUM WEBSITE EXPLORATION AND 2022 ACQUISITIONS SEARCH ===') print('Objective: Find correct Whitney Museum URLs and locate 2022 photographic acquisition announcements') print('Focus: Press releases about photographs featuring portraits or figures with books\n') # Create workspace directory if it doesn't exist if not os.path.exists('workspace'): os.makedirs('workspace') # Set up proper headers for web scraping headers = { 'User-Agent': 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 10.0; Win64; x64) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/120.0.0.0 Safari/537.36', 'Accept': 'text/html,application/xhtml+xml,application/xml;q=0.9,image/webp,image/apng,*/*;q=0.8', 'Accept-Language': 'en-US,en;q=0.9', 'Accept-Encoding': 'gzip, deflate, br', 'Connection': 'keep-alive', 'Upgrade-Insecure-Requests': '1', 'Sec-Fetch-Dest': 'document', 'Sec-Fetch-Mode': 'navigate', 'Sec-Fetch-Site': 'none' } # Start with the main Whitney Museum homepage to understand site structure print('Step 1: Exploring Whitney Museum homepage to understand site structure') try: response = requests.get('https://whitney.org', headers=headers, timeout=30) if response.status_code == 200: print(f'‚úì Successfully accessed whitney.org (Status: {response.status_code})') print(f'Content length: {len(response.content):,} bytes') # Parse the homepage soup = BeautifulSoup(response.content, 'html.parser') # Extract page title title = soup.find('title') page_title = title.get_text().strip() if title else 'No title found' print(f'Page title: {page_title}') # Save homepage for reference with open('workspace/whitney_homepage.html', 'w', encoding='utf-8') as f: f.write(response.text) print('‚úì Homepage saved to: workspace/whitney_homepage.html') # Look for navigation links that might lead to press releases or news print('\n=== ANALYZING NAVIGATION STRUCTURE ===') nav_links = [] press_related_links = [] collection_related_links = [] # Find all links for link in soup.find_all('a', href=True): href = link.get('href', '') text = link.get_text().strip() if href and text and len(text) > 1: # Make relative URLs absolute if href.startswith('/'): full_url = 'https://whitney.org' + href elif href.startswith('http'): full_url = href else: continue nav_links.append({ 'url': full_url, 'text': text, 'href': href }) # Look for press/news related links text_lower = text.lower() href_lower = href.lower() if any(term in text_lower or term in href_lower for term in ['press', 'news', 'media', 'release', 'announcement']): press_related_links.append({ 'url': full_url, 'text': text, 'category': 'press' }) # Look for collection/acquisition related links if any(term in text_lower or term in href_lower for term in ['collection', 'acquisition', 'recent', 'new']): collection_related_links.append({ 'url': full_url, 'text': text, 'category': 'collection' }) print(f'Total navigation links found: {len(nav_links)}') print(f'Press/news related links: {len(press_related_links)}') print(f'Collection related links: {len(collection_related_links)}') # Show press-related links if press_related_links: print('\nPress/News related links found:') for i, link in enumerate(press_related_links[:10], 1): # Show first 10 print(f' {i}. {link["text"]} -> {link["url"]}') # Show collection-related links if collection_related_links: print('\nCollection related links found:') for i, link in enumerate(collection_related_links[:10], 1): # Show first 10 print(f' {i}. {link["text"]} -> {link["url"]}') # Now try to access the most promising press/news pages print('\n=== ACCESSING PRESS AND NEWS PAGES ===') # Combine and prioritize links to explore priority_links = [] # Add press links first for link in press_related_links[:5]: # Top 5 press links priority_links.append(link) # Add collection links for link in collection_related_links[:3]: # Top 3 collection links priority_links.append(link) # Remove duplicates seen_urls = set() unique_priority_links = [] for link in priority_links: if link['url'] not in seen_urls: unique_priority_links.append(link) seen_urls.add(link['url']) print(f'Attempting to access {len(unique_priority_links)} priority pages...') accessed_pages = [] found_2022_content = [] for i, link in enumerate(unique_priority_links, 1): print(f'\n{i}. Accessing: {link["text"]}...') print(f' URL: {link["url"]}') try: page_response = requests.get(link['url'], headers=headers, timeout=30) if page_response.status_code == 200: print(f' ‚úì Success (Status: {page_response.status_code})') print(f' Content length: {len(page_response.content):,} bytes') # Parse the page content page_soup = BeautifulSoup(page_response.content, 'html.parser') # Extract page title page_title_elem = page_soup.find('title') page_title = page_title_elem.get_text().strip() if page_title_elem else 'No title' print(f' Page title: {page_title}') # Get text content for analysis text_content = page_soup.get_text() content_lower = text_content.lower() # Count key terms key_terms = { '2022': content_lower.count('2022'), 'acquisition': content_lower.count('acquisition'), 'acquired': content_lower.count('acquired'), 'photograph': content_lower.count('photograph'), 'photography': content_lower.count('photography'), 'portrait': content_lower.count('portrait'), 'book': content_lower.count('book'), 'press release': content_lower.count('press release'), 'announcement': content_lower.count('announcement'), 'gift': content_lower.count('gift'), 'donation': content_lower.count('donation') } # Show relevant terms found relevant_terms = {k: v for k, v in key_terms.items() if v > 0} if relevant_terms: print(f' Key terms found: {relevant_terms}') # Calculate relevance score relevance_score = 0 if key_terms['2022'] > 0: relevance_score += 5 if key_terms['acquisition'] > 0 or key_terms['acquired'] > 0: relevance_score += 4 if key_terms['photograph'] > 0 or key_terms['photography'] > 0: relevance_score += 3 if key_terms['portrait'] > 0: relevance_score += 2 if key_terms['book'] > 0: relevance_score += 2 print(f' Relevance score: {relevance_score}') # Save pages with 2022 content or high relevance if key_terms['2022'] > 0 or relevance_score >= 6: filename = f'workspace/whitney_page_{i}_{link["category"]}_{relevance_score}.html' with open(filename, 'w', encoding='utf-8') as f: f.write(page_response.text) print(f' ‚òÖ Saved relevant page: {filename}') found_2022_content.append({ 'url': link['url'], 'title': page_title, 'category': link['category'], 'relevance_score': relevance_score, 'key_terms': key_terms, 'saved_file': filename }) # Look for additional press release links on this page page_press_links = [] for page_link in page_soup.find_all('a', href=True): page_href = page_link.get('href', '') page_text = page_link.get_text().strip() if page_href and page_text: combined_text = f'{page_text} {page_href}'.lower() # Check if it's press release related and mentions 2022 is_press = any(term in combined_text for term in ['press', 'release', 'announcement', 'news']) has_2022 = '2022' in combined_text if is_press and has_2022: if page_href.startswith('/'): full_press_url = 'https://whitney.org' + page_href elif page_href.startswith('http'): full_press_url = page_href else: continue page_press_links.append({ 'url': full_press_url, 'text': page_text, 'source_page': link['url'] }) if page_press_links: print(f' ‚òÖ Found {len(page_press_links)} press links with 2022 on this page') for press_link in page_press_links[:3]: # Show first 3 print(f' ‚Ä¢ {press_link["text"][:50]}... -> {press_link["url"]}') accessed_pages.append({ 'url': link['url'], 'title': page_title, 'category': link['category'], 'status_code': page_response.status_code, 'relevance_score': relevance_score, 'key_terms': key_terms, 'press_links_found': len(page_press_links), 'success': True }) else: print(f' ‚úó Failed (Status: {page_response.status_code})') accessed_pages.append({ 'url': link['url'], 'category': link['category'], 'status_code': page_response.status_code, 'success': False }) except Exception as e: print(f' ‚úó Exception: {str(e)}') accessed_pages.append({ 'url': link['url'], 'category': link['category'], 'error': str(e), 'success': False }) # Rate limiting time.sleep(2) # Compile exploration results exploration_results = { 'exploration_timestamp': datetime.now().strftime('%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S'), 'homepage_title': page_title, 'total_nav_links': len(nav_links), 'press_links_found': len(press_related_links), 'collection_links_found': len(collection_related_links), 'pages_accessed': len(accessed_pages), 'pages_with_2022_content': len(found_2022_content), 'press_related_links': press_related_links, 'collection_related_links': collection_related_links, 'accessed_pages_summary': accessed_pages, 'found_2022_content': found_2022_content } # Save exploration results with open('workspace/whitney_exploration_results.json', 'w') as f: json.dump(exploration_results, f, indent=2) print(f'\n=== EXPLORATION COMPLETE ===') print(f'Results saved to: workspace/whitney_exploration_results.json') # Summary successful_pages = [p for p in accessed_pages if p.get('success', False)] print(f'\n=== SUMMARY ===') print(f'Homepage successfully accessed: ‚úì') print(f'Navigation links found: {len(nav_links)}') print(f'Press/news links discovered: {len(press_related_links)}') print(f'Collection links discovered: {len(collection_related_links)}') print(f'Pages successfully accessed: {len(successful_pages)}/{len(unique_priority_links)}') print(f'Pages with 2022 content found: {len(found_2022_content)}') if found_2022_content: print(f'\n‚òÖ‚òÖ‚òÖ EXCELLENT: Found {len(found_2022_content)} pages with 2022 content!') print('Pages to analyze for photographic acquisitions:') # Sort by relevance score found_2022_content.sort(key=lambda x: x['relevance_score'], reverse=True) for content in found_2022_content: print(f' ‚Ä¢ {content["title"]} (Score: {content["relevance_score"]})' ) print(f' File: {content["saved_file"]}') print(f' URL: {content["url"]}') if content['key_terms']['acquisition'] > 0 or content['key_terms']['acquired'] > 0: print(' ‚òÖ Contains acquisition content!') if content['key_terms']['photograph'] > 0 or content['key_terms']['photography'] > 0: print(' ‚òÖ Contains photography content!') print() elif successful_pages: print(f'\n‚òÖ MODERATE: Successfully accessed {len(successful_pages)} Whitney pages') print('No 2022 content found, but pages are available for further exploration') else: print(f'\n‚óã LIMITED: Few pages successfully accessed') print('\nNext steps:') print('1. Analyze saved HTML files for detailed 2022 acquisition content') print('2. Look for specific mentions of photographic works with portraits/books') print('3. Search for press releases or announcements about new acquisitions') else: print(f'‚úó Failed to access whitney.org (Status: {response.status_code})') print('Cannot proceed with Whitney Museum exploration') except Exception as e: print(f'‚úó Exception accessing whitney.org: {str(e)}') print('Cannot proceed with Whitney Museum exploration')

import os import requests from bs4 import BeautifulSoup import json from datetime import datetime import time print('=== WHITNEY MUSEUM WEBSITE EXPLORATION - FIXED VERSION ===') print('Objective: Find Whitney Museum press releases about 2022 photographic acquisitions') print('Focus: Press releases about photographs featuring portraits or figures with books\n') # Create workspace directory if it doesn't exist if not os.path.exists('workspace'): os.makedirs('workspace') # Set up proper headers for web scraping headers = { 'User-Agent': 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 10.0; Win64; x64) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/120.0.0.0 Safari/537.36', 'Accept': 'text/html,application/xhtml+xml,application/xml;q=0.9,image/webp,image/apng,*/*;q=0.8', 'Accept-Language': 'en-US,en;q=0.9', 'Accept-Encoding': 'gzip, deflate, br', 'Connection': 'keep-alive', 'Upgrade-Insecure-Requests': '1', 'Sec-Fetch-Dest': 'document', 'Sec-Fetch-Mode': 'navigate', 'Sec-Fetch-Site': 'none' } # First, check if we already have the homepage saved print('Checking for existing Whitney homepage data...') homepage_file = 'workspace/whitney_homepage.html' if os.path.exists(homepage_file): print(f'‚úì Found existing homepage file: {homepage_file}') print('Loading existing homepage content for analysis...') with open(homepage_file, 'r', encoding='utf-8') as f: html_content = f.read() print(f'Loaded homepage content: {len(html_content):,} characters') soup = BeautifulSoup(html_content, 'html.parser') else: print('No existing homepage found. Accessing whitney.org...') try: response = requests.get('https://whitney.org', headers=headers, timeout=30) if response.status_code == 200: print(f'‚úì Successfully accessed whitney.org (Status: {response.status_code})') print(f'Content length: {len(response.content):,} bytes') # Save homepage for future reference with open(homepage_file, 'w', encoding='utf-8') as f: f.write(response.text) print(f'‚úì Homepage saved to: {homepage_file}') html_content = response.text soup = BeautifulSoup(response.content, 'html.parser') else: print(f'‚úó Failed to access whitney.org (Status: {response.status_code})') exit() except Exception as e: print(f'‚úó Exception accessing whitney.org: {str(e)}') exit() # Extract page title title = soup.find('title') page_title = title.get_text().strip() if title else 'No title found' print(f'\nPage title: {page_title}') # Analyze navigation structure - FIXED VERSION print('\n=== ANALYZING NAVIGATION STRUCTURE ===\n') nav_links = [] press_related_links = [] collection_related_links = [] # Find all links with proper variable definitions for link in soup.find_all('a', href=True): href = link.get('href', '') text = link.get_text().strip() if href and text and len(text) > 1: # Make relative URLs absolute if href.startswith('/'): full_url = 'https://whitney.org' + href elif href.startswith('http'): full_url = href else: continue nav_links.append({ 'url': full_url, 'text': text, 'href': href }) # FIXED: Define variables before using them text_lower = text.lower() href_lower = href.lower() # Look for press/news related links if any(term in text_lower or term in href_lower for term in ['press', 'news', 'media', 'release', 'announcement']): press_related_links.append({ 'url': full_url, 'text': text, 'category': 'press' }) # Look for collection/acquisition related links if any(term in text_lower or term in href_lower for term in ['collection', 'acquisition', 'recent', 'new']): collection_related_links.append({ 'url': full_url, 'text': text, 'category': 'collection' }) print(f'Total navigation links found: {len(nav_links)}') print(f'Press/news related links: {len(press_related_links)}') print(f'Collection related links: {len(collection_related_links)}') # Show press-related links if press_related_links: print('\nPress/News related links found:') for i, link in enumerate(press_related_links[:8], 1): # Show first 8 print(f' {i}. {link["text"]} -> {link["url"]}') # Show collection-related links if collection_related_links: print('\nCollection related links found:') for i, link in enumerate(collection_related_links[:8], 1): # Show first 8 print(f' {i}. {link["text"]} -> {link["url"]}') # Now try to access the most promising pages print('\n=== ACCESSING PRIORITY PAGES ===\n') # Combine and prioritize links to explore priority_links = [] # Add press links first (top 4) for link in press_related_links[:4]: priority_links.append(link) # Add collection links (top 3) for link in collection_related_links[:3]: priority_links.append(link) # Remove duplicates seen_urls = set() unique_priority_links = [] for link in priority_links: if link['url'] not in seen_urls: unique_priority_links.append(link) seen_urls.add(link['url']) print(f'Attempting to access {len(unique_priority_links)} priority pages...\n') accessed_pages = [] found_2022_content = [] all_press_release_links = [] for i, link in enumerate(unique_priority_links, 1): print(f'{i}. FIXED: Define variables before using them page_combined_text = f'{page_text} {page_href}'.lower() # Check if it's press release related is_press = any(term in page_combined_text for term in ['press', 'release', 'announcement', 'news']) has_2022 = '2022' in page_combined_text has_acquisition = any(term in page_combined_text for term in ['acquisition', 'acquired', 'gift', 'donation']) if is_press or has_2022 or has_acquisition: if page_href.startswith('/'): full_press_url = 'https://whitney.org' + page_href elif page_href.startswith('http'): full_press_url = page_href else: continue page_press_links.append({ 'url': full_press_url, 'text': page_text, 'source_page': link['url'], 'has_2022': has_2022, 'has_acquisition': has_acquisition, 'is_press': is_press }) # Remove duplicates from this page's links unique_page_links = list({plink['url']: plink for plink in page_press_links}.values()) if unique_page_links: print(f' ‚òÖ Found {len(unique_page_links)} potential press/acquisition links on this page') # Show most promising links priority_page_links = [plink for plink in unique_page_links if plink['has_2022'] or plink['has_acquisition']] if priority_page_links: print(f' ‚òÖ‚òÖ {len(priority_page_links)} high-priority links (with 2022 or acquisition terms):') for plink in priority_page_links[:3]: # Show first 3 markers = [] if plink['has_2022']: markers.append('2022') if plink['has_acquisition']: markers.append('ACQ') if plink['is_press']: markers.append('PRESS') print(f' ‚Ä¢ [{"|".join(markers)}] {plink["text"][:50]}...') print(f' URL: {plink["url"]}') # Add to master list all_press_release_links.extend(unique_page_links) accessed_pages.append({ 'url': link['url'], 'title': page_title, 'category': link['category'], 'status_code': page_response.status_code, 'relevance_score': relevance_score, 'key_terms': key_terms, 'press_links_found': len(unique_page_links), 'success': True }) else: print(f' ‚úó Failed (Status: {page_response.status_code})') accessed_pages.append({ 'url': link['url'], 'category': link['category'], 'status_code': page_response.status_code, 'success': False }) except Exception as e: print(f' ‚úó Exception: {str(e)}') accessed_pages.append({ 'url': link['url'], 'category': link['category'], 'error': str(e), 'success': False }) print() # Space between pages # Rate limiting time.sleep(2) # Remove duplicate press release links from master list unique_all_press_links = list({plink['url']: plink for plink in all_press_release_links}.values()) # Compile comprehensive results exploration_results = { 'exploration_timestamp': datetime.now().strftime('%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S'), 'homepage_title': page_title, 'objective': 'Find Whitney Museum 2022 photographic acquisitions featuring portraits/figures with books', 'total_nav_links': len(nav_links), 'press_links_found': len(press_related_links), 'collection_links_found': len(collection_related_links), 'pages_accessed': len(accessed_pages), 'successful_pages': len([p for p in accessed_pages if p.get('success', False)]), 'pages_with_2022_content': len(found_2022_content), 'total_press_release_links_discovered': len(unique_all_press_links), 'press_related_links': press_related_links, 'collection_related_links': collection_related_links, 'accessed_pages_summary': accessed_pages, 'found_2022_content': found_2022_content, 'discovered_press_links': unique_all_press_links } #
