Look for collection/acquisition related links if any(term in text_lower or term in href_lower for term in ['collection', 'acquisition', 'recent', 'new']): collection_related_links.append({ 'url': full_url, 'text': text, 'category': 'collection' }) print(f'Total navigation links found: {len(nav_links)}') print(f'Press/news related links: {len(press_related_links)}') print(f'Collection related links: {len(collection_related_links)}') # Show press-related links if press_related_links: print('\nPress/News related links found:') for i, link in enumerate(press_related_links[:8], 1): # Show first 8 print(f' {i}. {link["text"]} -> {link["url"]}') # Show collection-related links if collection_related_links: print('\nCollection related links found:') for i, link in enumerate(collection_related_links[:8], 1): # Show first 8 print(f' {i}. {link["text"]} -> {link["url"]}') # Now try to access the most promising pages print('\n=== ACCESSING PRIORITY PAGES ===\n') # Combine and prioritize links to explore priority_links = [] # Add press links first (top 4) for link in press_related_links[:4]: priority_links.append(link) # Add collection links (top 3) for link in collection_related_links[:3]: priority_links.append(link) # Remove duplicates seen_urls = set() unique_priority_links = [] for link in priority_links: if link['url'] not in seen_urls: unique_priority_links.append(link) seen_urls.add(link['url']) print(f'Attempting to access {len(unique_priority_links)} priority pages...\n') accessed_pages = [] found_2022_content = [] all_press_release_links = [] for i, link in enumerate(unique_priority_links, 1): print(f'{i}. Accessing: {link["text"]}...') print(f' URL: {link["url"]}') try: page_response = requests.get(link['url'], headers=headers, timeout=30) if page_response.status_code == 200: print(f' ‚úì Success (Status: {page_response.status_code})') print(f' Content length: {len(page_response.content):,} bytes') # Parse the page content page_soup = BeautifulSoup(page_response.content, 'html.parser') # Extract page title page_title_elem = page_soup.find('title') page_title = page_title_elem.get_text().strip() if page_title_elem else 'No title' print(f' Page title: {page_title}') # Get text content for analysis text_content = page_soup.get_text() content_lower = text_content.lower() # Count key terms key_terms = { '2022': content_lower.count('2022'), 'acquisition': content_lower.count('acquisition'), 'acquired': content_lower.count('acquired'), 'photograph': content_lower.count('photograph'), 'photography': content_lower.count('photography'), 'portrait': content_lower.count('portrait'), 'book': content_lower.count('book'), 'press release': content_lower.count('press release'), 'announcement': content_lower.count('announcement'), 'gift': content_lower.count('gift'), 'donation': content_lower.count('donation') } # Show relevant terms found relevant_terms = {k: v for k, v in key_terms.items() if v > 0} if relevant_terms: print(f' Key terms found: {relevant_terms}') # Calculate relevance score relevance_score = 0 if key_terms['2022'] > 0: relevance_score += 5 if key_terms['acquisition'] > 0 or key_terms['acquired'] > 0: relevance_score += 4 if key_terms['photograph'] > 0 or key_terms['photography'] > 0: relevance_score += 3 if key_terms['portrait'] > 0: relevance_score += 2 if key_terms['book'] > 0: relevance_score += 2 if key_terms['press release'] > 0 or key_terms['announcement'] > 0: relevance_score += 2 print(f' Relevance score: {relevance_score}') # Save pages with 2022 content or high relevance if key_terms['2022'] > 0 or relevance_score >= 6: filename = f'workspace/whitney_page_{i}_{link["category"]}_{relevance_score}.html' with open(filename, 'w', encoding='utf-8') as f: f.write(page_response.text) print(f' ‚òÖ Saved relevant page: {filename}') found_2022_content.append({ 'url': link['url'], 'title': page_title, 'category': link['category'], 'relevance_score': relevance_score, 'key_terms': key_terms, 'saved_file': filename }) # Look for additional press release links on this page page_press_links = [] for page_link in page_soup.find_all('a', href=True): page_href = page_link.get('href', '') page_text = page_link.get_text().strip() if page_href and page_text and len(page_text) > 5: # FIXED: Define variables before using them page_combined_text = f'{page_text} {page_href}'.lower() # Check if it's press release related is_press = any(term in page_combined_text for term in ['press', 'release', 'announcement', 'news']) has_2022 = '2022' in page_combined_text has_acquisition = any(term in page_combined_text for term in ['acquisition', 'acquired', 'gift', 'donation']) if is_press or has_2022 or has_acquisition: if page_href.startswith('/'): full_press_url = 'https://whitney.org' + page_href elif page_href.startswith('http'): full_press_url = page_href else: continue page_press_links.append({ 'url': full_press_url, 'text': page_text, 'source_page': link['url'], 'has_2022': has_2022, 'has_acquisition': has_acquisition, 'is_press': is_press }) # Remove duplicates from this page's links unique_page_links = list({plink['url']: plink for plink in page_press_links}.values()) if unique_page_links: print(f' ‚òÖ Found {len(unique_page_links)} potential press/acquisition links on this page') # Show most promising links priority_page_links = [plink for plink in unique_page_links if plink['has_2022'] or plink['has_acquisition']] if priority_page_links: print(f' ‚òÖ‚òÖ {len(priority_page_links)} high-priority links (with 2022 or acquisition terms):') for plink in priority_page_links[:3]: # Show first 3 markers = [] if plink['has_2022']: markers.append('2022') if plink['has_acquisition']: markers.append('ACQ') if plink['is_press']: markers.append('PRESS') print(f' ‚Ä¢ [{"|".join(markers)}] {plink["text"][:50]}...') print(f' URL: {plink["url"]}') # Add to master list all_press_release_links.extend(unique_page_links) accessed_pages.append({ 'url': link['url'], 'title': page_title, 'category': link['category'], 'status_code': page_response.status_code, 'relevance_score': relevance_score, 'key_terms': key_terms, 'press_links_found': len(unique_page_links), 'success': True }) else: print(f' ‚úó Failed (Status: {page_response.status_code})') accessed_pages.append({ 'url': link['url'], 'category': link['category'], 'status_code': page_response.status_code, 'success': False }) except Exception as e: print(f' ‚úó Exception: {str(e)}') accessed_pages.append({ 'url': link['url'], 'category': link['category'], 'error': str(e), 'success': False }) print() # Space between pages # Rate limiting time.sleep(2) # Remove duplicate press release links from master list unique_all_press_links = list({plink['url']: plink for plink in all_press_release_links}.values()) # Compile comprehensive results exploration_results = { 'exploration_timestamp': datetime.now().strftime('%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S'), 'homepage_title': page_title, 'objective': 'Find Whitney Museum 2022 photographic acquisitions featuring portraits/figures with books', 'total_nav_links': len(nav_links), 'press_links_found': len(press_related_links), 'collection_links_found': len(collection_related_links), 'pages_accessed': len(accessed_pages), 'successful_pages': len([p for p in accessed_pages if p.get('success', False)]), 'pages_with_2022_content': len(found_2022_content), 'total_press_release_links_discovered': len(unique_all_press_links), 'press_related_links': press_related_links, 'collection_related_links': collection_related_links, 'accessed_pages_summary': accessed_pages, 'found_2022_content': found_2022_content, 'discovered_press_links': unique_all_press_links } # Save exploration results with open('workspace/whitney_exploration_results.json', 'w') as f: json.dump(exploration_results, f, indent=2) print(f'=== EXPLORATION COMPLETE ===') print(f'Results saved to: workspace/whitney_exploration_results.json\n') # import os import requests from bs4 import BeautifulSoup import json from datetime import datetime import time print('=== WHITNEY MUSEUM WEBSITE EXPLORATION - VARIABLE SCOPE FIXED ===') print('Objective: Find Whitney Museum press releases about 2022 photographic acquisitions') print('Focus: Press releases about photographs featuring portraits or figures with books\n') # Create workspace directory if it doesn't exist if not os.path.exists('workspace'): os.makedirs('workspace') # Set up proper headers for web scraping headers = { 'User-Agent': 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 10.0; Win64; x64) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/120.0.0.0 Safari/537.36', 'Accept': 'text/html,application/xhtml+xml,application/xml;q=0.9,image/webp,image/apng,*/*;q=0.8', 'Accept-Language': 'en-US,en;q=0.9', 'Accept-Encoding': 'gzip, deflate, br', 'Connection': 'keep-alive', 'Upgrade-Insecure-Requests': '1' } # First, check if we already have the homepage saved print('Checking for existing Whitney homepage data...') homepage_file = 'workspace/whitney_homepage.html' if os.path.exists(homepage_file): print(f'‚úì Found existing homepage file: {homepage_file}') print('Loading existing homepage content for analysis...') with open(homepage_file, 'r', encoding='utf-8') as f: html_content = f.read() print(f'Loaded homepage content: {len(html_content):,} characters') soup = BeautifulSoup(html_content, 'html.parser') else: print('No existing homepage found. Accessing whitney.org...') try: response = requests.get('https://whitney.org', headers=headers, timeout=30) if response.status_code == 200: print(f'‚úì Successfully accessed whitney.org (Status: {response.status_code})') print(f'Content length: {len(response.content):,} bytes') # Save homepage for future reference with open(homepage_file, 'w', encoding='utf-8') as f: f.write(response.text) print(f'‚úì Homepage saved to: {homepage_file}') html_content = response.text soup = BeautifulSoup(response.content, 'html.parser') else: print(f'‚úó Failed to access whitney.org (Status: {response.status_code})') exit() except Exception as e: print(f'‚úó Exception accessing whitney.org: {str(e)}') exit() # Extract page title title = soup.find('title') page_title = title.get_text().strip() if title else 'No title found' print(f'\nPage title: {page_title}') # Analyze navigation structure - PROPERLY FIXED VERSION print('\n=== ANALYZING NAVIGATION STRUCTURE ===\n') nav_links = [] press_related_links = [] collection_related_links = [] # Find all links with proper variable definitions - FIXED SCOPE ISSUE for link in soup.find_all('a', href=True): href = link.get('href', '') text = link.get_text().strip() if href and text and len(text) > 1: # Make relative URLs absolute if href.startswith('/'): full_url = 'https://whitney.org' + href elif href.startswith('http'): full_url = href else: continue nav_links.append({ 'url': full_url, 'text': text, 'href': href }) # CRITICAL FIX: Define text_lower and href_lower BEFORE using them text_lower = text.lower() href_lower = href.lower() # Look for press/news related links press_terms = ['press', 'news', 'media', 'release', 'announcement'] if any(term in text_lower or term in href_lower for term in press_terms): press_related_links.append({ 'url': full_url, 'text': text, 'category': 'press' }) # Look for collection/acquisition related links collection_terms = ['collection', 'acquisition', 'recent', 'new'] if any(term in text_lower or term in href_lower for term in collection_terms): collection_related_links.append({ 'url': full_url, 'text': text, 'category': 'collection' }) print(f'Total navigation links found: {len(nav_links)}') print(f'Press/news related links: {len(press_related_links)}') print(f'Collection related links: {len(collection_related_links)}') # Show press-related links if press_related_links: print('\nPress/News related links found:') for i, link in enumerate(press_related_links[:8], 1): # Show first 8 print(f' {i}. {link["text"]} -> {link["url"]}') # Show collection-related links if collection_related_links: print('\nCollection related links found:') for i, link in enumerate(collection_related_links[:8], 1): # Show first 8 print(f' {i}. {link["text"]} -> {link["url"]}') # Now try to access the most promising pages print('\n=== ACCESSING PRIORITY PAGES ===\n') # Combine and prioritize links to explore priority_links = [] # Add press links first (top 4) for link in press_related_links[:4]: priority_links.append(link) # Add collection links (top 3) for link in collection_related_links[:3]: priority_links.append(link) # Remove duplicates seen_urls = set() unique_priority_links = [] for link in priority_links: if link['url'] not in seen_urls: unique_priority_links.append(link) seen_urls.add(link['url']) print(f'Attempting to access {len(unique_priority_links)} priority pages...\n') accessed_pages = [] found_2022_content = [] all_press_release_links = [] for i, link in enumerate(unique_priority_links, 1): print(f'{i}. Accessing: {link["text"]}...') print(f' URL: {link["url"]}') try: page_response = requests.get(link['url'], headers=headers, timeout=30) if page_response.status_code == 200: print(f' ‚úì Success (Status: {page_response.status_code})') print(f' Content length: {len(page_response.content):,} bytes') # Parse the page content page_soup = BeautifulSoup(page_response.content, 'html.parser') # Extract page title page_title_elem = page_soup.find('title') page_title = page_title_elem.get_text().strip() if page_title_elem else 'No title' print(f' Page title: {page_title}') # Get text content for analysis text_content = page_soup.get_text() content_lower = text_content.lower() # Count key terms for 2022 photographic acquisitions key_terms = { '2022': content_lower.count('2022'), 'acquisition': content_lower.count('acquisition'), 'acquired': content_lower.count('acquired'), 'photograph': content_lower.count('photograph'), 'photography': content_lower.count('photography'), 'portrait': content_lower.count('portrait'), 'book': content_lower.count('book'), 'press release': content_lower.count('press release'), 'announcement': content_lower.count('announcement'), 'gift': content_lower.count('gift'), 'donation': content_lower.count('donation') } # Show relevant terms found relevant_terms = {k: v for k, v in key_terms.items() if v > 0} if relevant_terms: print(f' Key terms found: {relevant_terms}') # Calculate relevance score for 2022 photographic acquisitions relevance_score = 0 if key_terms['2022'] > 0: relevance_score += 5 if key_terms['acquisition'] > 0 or key_terms['acquired'] > 0: relevance_score += 4 if key_terms['photograph'] > 0 or key_terms['photography'] > 0: relevance_score += 3 if key_terms['portrait'] > 0: relevance_score += 2 if key_terms['book'] > 0: relevance_score += 2 if key_terms['press release'] > 0 or key_terms['announcement'] > 0: relevance_score += 2 print(f' Relevance score: {relevance_score}') # Save pages with 2022 content or high relevance if key_terms['2022'] > 0 or relevance_score >= 6: filename = f'workspace/whitney_page_{i}_{link["category"]}_{relevance_score}.html' with open(filename, 'w', encoding='utf-8') as f: f.write(page_response.text) print(f' ‚òÖ Saved relevant page: {filename}') found_2022_content.append({ 'url': link['url'], 'title': page_title, 'category': link['category'], 'relevance_score': relevance_score, 'key_terms': key_terms, 'saved_file': filename }) # Look for additional press release links on this page page_press_links = [] for page_link in page_soup.find_all('a', href=True): page_href = page_link.get('href', '') page_text = page_link.get_text().strip() if page_href and page_text and len(page_text) > 5: # Define variables properly for each link page_text_lower = page_text.lower() page_href_lower = page_href.lower() page_combined_text = f'{page_text_lower} {page_href_lower}' # Check if it's press release related is_press = any(term in page_combined_text for term in ['press', 'release', 'announcement', 'news']) has_2022 = '2022' in page_combined_text has_acquisition = any(term in page_combined_text for term in ['acquisition', 'acquired', 'gift', 'donation']) if is_press or has_2022 or has_acquisition: if page_href.startswith('/'): full_press_url = 'https://whitney.org' + page_href elif page_href.startswith('http'): full_press_url = page_href else: continue page_press_links.append({ 'url': full_press_url, 'text': page_text, 'source_page': link['url'], 'has_2022': has_2022, 'has_acquisition': has_acquisition, 'is_press': is_press }) # Remove duplicates from this page's links unique_page_links = list({plink['url']: plink for plink in page_press_links}.values()) if unique_page_links: print(f' ‚òÖ Found {len(unique_page_links)} potential press/acquisition links on this page') # Show most promising links priority_page_links = [plink for plink in unique_page_links if plink['has_2022'] or plink['has_acquisition']] if priority_page_links: print(f' ‚òÖ‚òÖ {len(priority_page_links)} high-priority links (with 2022 or acquisition terms):') for plink in priority_page_links[:3]: # Show first 3 markers = [] if plink['has_2022']: markers.append('2022') if plink['has_acquisition']: markers.append('ACQ') if plink['is_press']: markers.append('PRESS') print(f' ‚Ä¢ [{"|'.join(markers)}] {plink["text"][:50]}...') print(f' URL: {plink["url"]}') # Add to master list all_press_release_links.extend(unique_page_links) accessed_pages.append({ 'url': link['url'], 'title': page_title, 'category': link['category'], 'status_code': page_response.status_code, 'relevance_score': relevance_score, 'key_terms': key_terms, 'press_links_found': len(unique_page_links), 'success': True }) else: print(f' ‚úó Failed (Status: {page_response.status_code})') accessed_pages.append({ 'url': link['url'], 'category': link['category'], 'status_code': page_response.status_code, 'success': False }) except Exception as e: print(f' ‚úó Exception: {str(e)}') accessed_pages.append({ 'url': link['url'], 'category': link['category'], 'error': str(e), 'success': False }) print() # Space between pages # Rate limiting time.sleep(2) # Remove duplicate press release links from master list unique_all_press_links = list({plink['url']: plink for plink in all_press_release_links}.values()) # Compile comprehensive results exploration_results = { 'exploration_timestamp': datetime.now().strftime('%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S'), 'homepage_title': page_title, 'objective': 'Find Whitney Museum 2022 photographic acquisitions featuring portraits/figures with books', 'total_nav_links': len(nav_links), 'press_links_found': len(press_related_links), 'collection_links_found': len(collection_related_links), 'pages_accessed': len(accessed_pages), 'successful_pages': len([p for p in accessed_pages if p.get('success', False)]), 'pages_with_2022_content': len(found_2022_content), 'total_press_release_links_discovered': len(unique_all_press_links), 'press_related_links': press_related_links, 'collection_related_links': collection_related_links, 'accessed_pages_summary': accessed_pages, 'found_2022_content': found_2022_content, 'discovered_press_links': unique_all_press_links } # Save exploration results with open('workspace/whitney_exploration_results.json', 'w') as f: json.dump(exploration_results, f, indent=2) print(f'=== EXPLORATION COMPLETE ===') print(f'Results saved to: workspace/whitney_exploration_results.json\n') # Summary and assessment successful_pages = [p for p in accessed_pages if p.get('success', False)] high_priority_press_links = [plink for plink in unique_all_press_links if plink['has_2022'] or plink['has_acquisition']] print(f'=== COMPREHENSIVE SUMMARY ===') print(f'Homepage successfully accessed: ‚úì') print(f'Navigation links found: {len(nav_links)}') print(f'Press/news links discovered: {len(press_related_links)}') print(f'Collection links discovered: {len(collection_related_links)}') print(f'Pages successfully accessed: {len(successful_pages)}/{len(unique_priority_links)}') print(f'Pages with 2022 content found: {len(found_2022_content)}') print(f'Total press/acquisition links discovered: {len(unique_all_press_links)}') print(f'High-priority links (2022/acquisition): {len(high_priority_press_links)}') if found_2022_content: print(f'\n‚òÖ‚òÖ‚òÖ EXCELLENT: Found {len(found_2022_content)} pages with 2022 content!') print('Pages to analyze for photographic acquisitions:') # Sort by relevance score found_2022_content.sort(key=lambda x: x['relevance_score'], reverse=True) for content in found_2022_content: print(f' ‚Ä¢ {content["title"]} (Score: {content["relevance_score"]})') print(f' File: {content["saved_file"]}') print(f' URL: {content["url"]}') if content['key_terms']['acquisition'] > 0 or content['key_terms']['acquired'] > 0: print(' ‚òÖ Contains acquisition content!') if content['key_terms']['photograph'] > 0 or content['key_terms']['photography'] > 0: print(' ‚òÖ Contains photography content!') print() if high_priority_press_links: print(f'\n‚òÖ‚òÖ‚òÖ DISCOVERED {len(high_priority_press_links)} HIGH-PRIORITY PRESS/ACQUISITION LINKS!') print('Most promising links for 2022 photographic acquisitions:') # import os import requests from bs4 import BeautifulSoup import json from datetime import datetime import time print('=== WHITNEY MUSEUM WEBSITE EXPLORATION - SYNTAX FIXED ===') print('Objective: Find Whitney Museum press releases about 2022 photographic acquisitions') print('Focus: Press releases about photographs featuring portraits or figures with books\n') # Create workspace directory if it doesn't exist if not os.path.exists('workspace'): os.makedirs('workspace') # Set up proper headers for web scraping headers = { 'User-Agent': 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 10.0; Win64; x64) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/120.0.0.0 Safari/537.36', 'Accept': 'text/html,application/xhtml+xml,application/xml;q=0.9,image/webp,image/apng,*/*;q=0.8', 'Accept-Language': 'en-US,en;q=0.9', 'Accept-Encoding': 'gzip, deflate, br', 'Connection': 'keep-alive', 'Upgrade-Insecure-Requests': '1' } # First, check if we already have the homepage saved print('Checking for existing Whitney homepage data...') homepage_file = 'workspace/whitney_homepage.html' if os.path.exists(homepage_file): print(f'‚úì Found existing homepage file: {homepage_file}') print('Loading existing homepage content for analysis...') with open(homepage_file, 'r', encoding='utf-8') as f: html_content = f.read() print(f'Loaded homepage content: {len(html_content):,} characters') soup = BeautifulSoup(html_content, 'html.parser') else: print('No existing homepage found. Accessing whitney.org...') try: response = requests.get('https://whitney.org', headers=headers, timeout=30) if response.status_code == 200: print(f'‚úì Successfully accessed whitney.org (Status: {response.status_code})') print(f'Content length: {len(response.content):,} bytes') # Save homepage for future reference with open(homepage_file, 'w', encoding='utf-8') as f: f.write(response.text) print(f'‚úì Homepage saved to: {homepage_file}') html_content = response.text soup = BeautifulSoup(response.content, 'html.parser') else: print(f'‚úó Failed to access whitney.org (Status: {response.status_code})') exit() except Exception as e: print(f'‚úó Exception accessing whitney.org: {str(e)}') exit() # Extract page title title = soup.find('title') page_title = title.get_text().strip() if title else 'No title found' print(f'\nPage title: {page_title}') # Analyze navigation structure - SYNTAX FIXED VERSION print('\n=== ANALYZING NAVIGATION STRUCTURE ===\n') nav_links = [] press_related_links = [] collection_related_links = [] # Find all links with proper variable definitions for link in soup.find_all('a', href=True): href = link.get('href', '') text = link.get_text().strip() if href and text and len(text) > 1: # Make relative URLs absolute if href.startswith('/'): full_url = 'https://whitney.org' + href elif href.startswith('http'): full_url = href else: continue nav_links.append({ 'url': full_url, 'text': text, 'href': href }) # Define text_lower and href_lower BEFORE using them text_lower = text.lower() href_lower = href.lower() # Look for press/news related links press_terms = ['press', 'news', 'media', 'release', 'announcement'] if any(term in text_lower or term in href_lower for term in press_terms): press_related_links.append({ 'url': full_url, 'text': text, 'category': 'press' }) # Look for collection/acquisition related links collection_terms = ['collection', 'acquisition', 'recent', 'new'] if any(term in text_lower or term in href_lower for term in collection_terms): collection_related_links.append({ 'url': full_url, 'text': text, 'category': 'collection' }) print(f'Total navigation links found: {len(nav_links)}') print(f'Press/news related links: {len(press_related_links)}') print(f'Collection related links: {len(collection_related_links)}') # Show press-related links if press_related_links: print('\nPress/News related links found:') for i, link in enumerate(press_related_links[:8], 1): # Show first 8 print(f' {i}. {link["text"]} -> {link["url"]}') # variables now properly defined is_collection_related = False for term in collection_terms: if term in text_lower or term in href_lower: is_collection_related = True break if is_collection_related: collection_related_links.append({ 'url': full_url, 'text': text, 'category': 'collection' }) print(f'Total navigation links found: {len(nav_links)}') print(f'Press/news related links: {len(press_related_links)}') print(f'Collection related links: {len(collection_related_links)}') # Show press-related links if press_related_links: print('\nPress/News related links found:') for i, link in enumerate(press_related_links[:8], 1): # Show first 8 print(f' {i}. {link["text"]} -> {link["url"]}') # Show collection-related links if collection_related_links: print('\nCollection related links found:') for i, link in enumerate(collection_related_links[:8], 1): # Show first 8 print(f' {i}. {link["text"]} -> {link["url"]}') # Now try to access the most promising pages print('\n=== ACCESSING PRIORITY PAGES ===\n') # Combine and prioritize links to explore priority_links = [] # Add press links first (top 4) for link in press_related_links[:4]: priority_links.append(link) # Add collection links (top 3) for link in collection_related_links[:3]: priority_links.append(link) # Remove duplicates seen_urls = set() unique_priority_links = [] for link in priority_links: if link['url'] not in seen_urls: unique_priority_links.append(link) seen_urls.add(link['url']) print(f'Attempting to access {len(unique_priority_links)} priority pages...\n') accessed_pages = [] found_2022_content = [] all_press_release_links = [] for i, link in enumerate(unique_priority_links, 1): print(f'{i}. Accessing: {link["text"]}...') print(f' URL: {link["url"]}') try: page_response = requests.get(link['url'], headers=headers, timeout=30) if page_response.status_code == 200: print(f' ‚úì Success (Status: {page_response.status_code})') print(f' Content length: {len(page_response.content):,} bytes') # Parse the page content page_soup = BeautifulSoup(page_response.content, 'html.parser') # Extract page title page_title_elem = page_soup.find('title') page_title = page_title_elem.get_text().strip() if page_title_elem else 'No title' print(f' Page title: {page_title}') # Get text content for analysis text_content = page_soup.get_text() content_lower = text_content.lower() # Count key terms for 2022 photographic acquisitions key_terms = { '2022': content_lower.count('2022'), 'acquisition': content_lower.count('acquisition'), 'acquired': content_lower.count('acquired'), 'photograph': content_lower.count('photograph'), 'photography': content_lower.count('photography'), 'portrait': content_lower.count('portrait'), 'book': content_lower.count('book'), 'press release': content_lower.count('press release'), 'announcement': content_lower.count('announcement'), 'gift': content_lower.count('gift'), 'donation': content_lower.count('donation') } # Show relevant terms found relevant_terms = {k: v for k, v in key_terms.items() if v > 0} if relevant_terms: print(f' Key terms found: {relevant_terms}') # Calculate relevance score for 2022 photographic acquisitions relevance_score = 0 if key_terms['2022'] > 0: relevance_score += 5 if key_terms['acquisition'] > 0 or key_terms['acquired'] > 0: relevance_score += 4 if key_terms['photograph'] > 0 or key_terms['photography'] > 0: relevance_score += 3 if key_terms['portrait'] > 0: relevance_score += 2 if key_terms['book'] > 0: relevance_score += 2 if key_terms['press release'] > 0 or key_terms['announcement'] > 0: relevance_score += 2 print(f' Relevance score: {relevance_score}') # Save pages with 2022 content or high relevance if key_terms['2022'] > 0 or relevance_score >= 6: filename = f'workspace/whitney_page_{i}_{link["category"]}_{relevance_score}.html' with open(filename, 'w', encoding='utf-8') as f: f.write(page_response.text) print(f' ‚òÖ Saved relevant page: {filename}') found_2022_content.append({ 'url': link['url'], 'title': page_title, 'category': link['category'], 'relevance_score': relevance_score, 'key_terms': key_terms, 'saved_file': filename }) # Look for additional press release links on this page page_press_links = [] for page_link in page_soup.find_all('a', href=True): page_href = page_link.get('href', '') page_text = page_link.get_text().strip() if page_href and page_text and len(page_text) > 5: # Define variables properly for each link page_text_lower = page_text.lower() page_href_lower = page_href.lower() # Check if it's press release related is_press = False for term in ['press', 'release', 'announcement', 'news']: if term in page_text_lower or term in page_href_lower: is_press = True break has_2022 = '2022' in page_text_lower or '2022' in page_href_lower has_acquisition = False for term in ['acquisition', 'acquired', 'gift', 'donation']: if term in page_text_lower or term in page_href_lower: has_acquisition = True break if is_press or has_2022 or has_acquisition: if page_href.startswith('/'): full_press_url = 'https://whitney.org' + page_href elif page_href.startswith('http'): full_press_url = page_href else: continue page_press_links.append({ 'url': full_press_url, 'text': page_text, 'source_page': link['url'], 'has_2022': has_2022, 'has_acquisition': has_acquisition, 'is_press': is_press }) # Remove duplicates from this page's links unique_page_links = list({plink['url']: plink for plink in page_press_links}.values()) if unique_page_links: print(f' ‚òÖ Found {len(unique_page_links)} potential press/acquisition links on this page') # Show most promising links priority_page_links = [plink for plink in unique_page_links if plink['has_2022'] or plink['has_acquisition']] if priority_page_links: print(f' ‚òÖ‚òÖ {len(priority_page_links)} high-priority links (with 2022 or acquisition terms):') for plink in priority_page_links[:3]: # Show first 3 markers = [] if plink['has_2022']: markers.append('2022') if plink['has_acquisition']: markers.append('ACQ') if plink['is_press']: markers.append('PRESS') markers_str = '|'.join(markers) print(f' ‚Ä¢ [{markers_str}] {plink["text"][:50]}...') print(f' URL: {plink["url"]}') # Add to master list all_press_release_links.extend(unique_page_links) accessed_pages.append({ 'url': link['url'], 'title': page_title, 'category': link['category'], 'status_code': page_response.status_code, 'relevance_score': relevance_score, 'key_terms': key_terms, 'press_links_found': len(unique_page_links), 'success': True }) else: print(f' ‚úó Failed (Status: {page_response.status_code})') accessed_pages.append({ 'url': link['url'], 'category': link['category'], 'status_code': page_response.status_code, 'success': False }) except Exception as e: print(f' ‚úó Exception: {str(e)}') accessed_pages.append({ 'url': link['url'], 'category': link['category'], 'error': str(e), 'success': False }) print() # Space between pages # Rate limiting time.sleep(2) # Remove duplicate press release links from master list unique_all_press_links = list({plink['url']: plink for plink in all_press_release_links}.values()) # Compile comprehensive results exploration_results = { 'exploration_timestamp': datetime.now().strftime('%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S'), 'homepage_title': page_title, 'objective': 'Find Whitney Museum 2022 photographic acquisitions featuring portraits/figures with books', 'total_nav_links': len(nav_links), 'press_links_found': len(press_related_links), 'collection_links_found': len(collection_related_links), 'pages_accessed': len(accessed_pages), 'successful_pages': len([p for p in accessed_pages if p.get('success', False)]), 'pages_with_2022_content': len(found_2022_content), 'total_press_release_links_discovered': len(unique_all_press_links), 'press_related_links': press_related_links, 'collection_related_links': collection_related_links, 'accessed_pages_summary': accessed_pages, 'found_2022_content': found_2022_content, 'discovered_press_links': unique_all_press_links } # Save exploration results with open('workspace/whitney_exploration_results.json', 'w') as f: json.dump(exploration_results, f, indent=2) print(f'=== EXPLORATION COMPLETE ===') print(f'Results saved to: workspace/whitney_exploration_results.json\n') # Summary and assessment successful_pages = [p for p in accessed_pages if p.get('success', False)] high_priority_press_links = [plink for plink in unique_all_press_links if plink['has_2022'] or plink['has_acquisition']] print(f'=== COMPREHENSIVE SUMMARY ===') print(f'Homepage successfully accessed: ‚úì') print(f'Navigation links found: {len(nav_links)}') print(f'Press/news links discovered: {len(press_related_links)}') print(f'Collection links discovered: {len(collection_related_links)}') print(f'Pages successfully accessed: {len(successful_pages)}/{len(unique_priority_links)}') print(f'Pages with 2022 content found: {len(found_2022_content)}') print(f'Total press/acquisition links discovered: {len(unique_all_press_links)}') print(f'High-priority links (2022/acquisition): {len(high_priority_press_links)}') if found_2022_content: print(f'\n‚òÖ‚òÖ‚òÖ EXCELLENT: Found {len(found_2022_content)} pages with 2022 content!') print('Pages to analyze for photographic acquisitions:') # Sort by relevance score found_2022_content.sort(key=lambda x: x['relevance_score'], reverse=True) for content in found_2022_content: print(f' ‚Ä¢ {content["title"]} (Score: {content["relevance_score"]})') print(f' File: {content["saved_file"]}') print(f' URL: {content["url"]}') if content['key_terms']['acquisition'] > 0 or content['key_terms']['acquired'] > 0: print(' ‚òÖ Contains acquisition content!') if content['key_terms']['photograph'] > 0 or content['key_terms']['photography'] > 0: print(' ‚òÖ Contains photography content!') print() if high_priority_press_links: print(f'\n‚òÖ‚òÖ‚òÖ DISCOVERED {len(high_priority_press_links)} HIGH-PRIORITY PRESS/ACQUISITION LINKS!') print('Most promising links for 2022 photographic acquisitions:') # [{markers_str}] {plink["text"]}') print(f' URL: {plink["url"]}') print(f' Source: {plink["source_page"]}') print() print('\n=== NEXT STEPS ===') if found_2022_content: print('1. ‚òÖ PRIORITY: Analyze saved HTML files with 2022 content for detailed acquisition information') if high_priority_press_links: print('2. ‚òÖ PRIORITY: Access high-priority press/acquisition links for 2022 photographic acquisitions') print('3. Accessing whitney.org...') try: response = requests.get('https://whitney.org', headers=headers, timeout=30) if response.status_code == 200: print(f'‚úì Successfully accessed whitney.org (Status: {response.status_code})') print(f'Content length: {len(response.content):,} bytes') # Save homepage for future reference with open(homepage_file, 'w', encoding='utf-8') as f: f.write(response.text) print(f'‚úì Homepage saved to: {homepage_file}') html_content = response.text soup = BeautifulSoup(response.content, 'html.parser') else: print(f'‚úó Failed to access whitney.org (Status: {response.status_code})') exit() except Exception as e: print(f'‚úó Exception accessing whitney.org: {str(e)}') exit() # Extract page title title = soup.find('title') page_title = title.get_text().strip() if title else 'No title found' print(f'\nPage title: {page_title}') # Analyze navigation structure - import os import requests from bs4 import BeautifulSoup import json from datetime import datetime import time print('=== WHITNEY MUSEUM 2022 PHOTOGRAPHIC ACQUISITIONS SEARCH ===') print('Objective: Find Whitney Museum press releases about 2022 photographic acquisitions') print('Focus: Press releases about photographs featuring portraits or figures with books\n') # Create workspace directory if it doesn't exist if not os.path.exists('workspace'): os.makedirs('workspace') # First, let's analyze the saved Whitney press page print('=== ANALYZING SAVED WHITNEY PRESS PAGE ===\n') # Check for the saved press page file press_page_files = [f for f in os.listdir('workspace') if 'whitney_page_2_press' in f and f.endswith('.html')] if press_page_files: press_file = press_page_files[0] print(f'Found saved press page: {press_file}') with open(f'workspace/{press_file}', 'r', encoding='utf-8') as f: press_content = f.read() print(f'Press page content length: {len(press_content):,} characters') # Parse the press page content press_soup = BeautifulSoup(press_content, 'html.parser') # Extract all text for analysis press_text = press_soup.get_text() press_text_lower = press_text.lower() # Look for 2022 content specifically if '2022' in press_text_lower: print('\n‚òÖ‚òÖ‚òÖ FOUND 2022 CONTENT IN PRESS PAGE! ‚òÖ‚òÖ‚òÖ') # Find lines containing 2022 press_lines = press_text.split('\n') relevant_2022_lines = [] for i, line in enumerate(press_lines): if '2022' in line.lower(): # Get context around the 2022 mention start = max(0, i-2) end = min(len(press_lines), i+3) context = press_lines[start:end] relevant_2022_lines.extend(context) # Remove duplicates and empty lines unique_2022_lines = [] for line in relevant_2022_lines: clean_line = line.strip() if clean_line and clean_line not in unique_2022_lines: unique_2022_lines.append(clean_line) print('\n2022 Context from Press Page:') for line in unique_2022_lines[:15]: # Show first 15 relevant lines print(f' {line}') # Look for press release links on the page press_links = [] for link in press_soup.find_all('a', href=True): href = link.get('href', '') text = link.get_text().strip() if href and text and len(text) > 5: # Check for press release indicators combined_text = f'{text} {href}'.lower() if any(term in combined_text for term in ['press', 'release', 'announcement', 'news', '2022']): if href.startswith('/'): full_url = 'https://whitney.org' + href elif href.startswith('http'): full_url = href else: continue press_links.append({ 'url': full_url, 'text': text, 'has_2022': '2022' in combined_text, 'has_press': any(term in combined_text for term in ['press', 'release', 'announcement']) }) print(f'\nFound {len(press_links)} press-related links on the page') # Show most promising links priority_press_links = [link for link in press_links if link['has_2022'] or link['has_press']] if priority_press_links: print(f'\nPriority press links ({len(priority_press_links)}):') for i, link in enumerate(priority_press_links[:5], 1): markers = [] if link['has_2022']: markers.append('2022') if link['has_press']: markers.append('PRESS') print(f' {i}. [{"|".join(markers)}] {link["text"][:60]}...') print(f' URL: {link["url"]}') print() else: print('No saved Whitney press page found') press_links = [] # Now use Google Search API for comprehensive search api_key = os.getenv("SERPAPI_API_KEY") if api_key: print('\n=== GOOGLE SEARCH FOR WHITNEY 2022 PHOTOGRAPHIC ACQUISITIONS ===\n') # Multiple targeted search queries search_queries = [ 'Whitney Museum 2022 acquisition photography portrait book press release', 'site:whitney.org 2022 acquired photograph portrait figure book', '"Whitney Museum" "2022" "acquisition" "photograph" "portrait" "book"', 'Whitney Museum press release 2022 new acquisition photography', '"Whitney Museum" "2022" "gift" "donation" photograph portrait book', 'Whitney Museum 2022 collection acquisition photographic works portrait' ] google_results = [] for i, query in enumerate(search_queries, 1): print(f'Search {i}: "{query}"') params = { "q": query, "api_key": api_key, "engine": "google", "google_domain": "google.com", "safe": "off", "num": 10 } try: response = requests.get("https://serpapi.com/search.json", params=params) if response.status_code == 200: results = response.json() if results.get("organic_results"): print(f' Found {len(results["organic_results"])} results') for j, result in enumerate(results["organic_results"], 1): title = result.get('title', 'No title') link = result.get('link', 'No link') snippet = result.get('snippet', 'No snippet') # Analyze result relevance combined_text = f'{title} {snippet}'.lower() relevance_indicators = { 'has_whitney': 'whitney' in combined_text, 'has_2022': '2022' in combined_text, 'has_acquisition': any(term in combined_text for term in ['acquisition', 'acquired', 'gift', 'donation']), 'has_photograph': any(term in combined_text for term in ['photograph', 'photography', 'photo']), 'has_portrait': 'portrait' in combined_text, 'has_book': 'book' in combined_text, 'is_whitney_official': 'whitney.org' in link.lower() } # Calculate relevance score relevance_score = sum([ relevance_indicators['has_whitney'] * 2, relevance_indicators['has_2022'] * 3, relevance_indicators['has_acquisition'] * 3, relevance_indicators['has_photograph'] * 2, relevance_indicators['has_portrait'] * 2, relevance_indicators['has_book'] * 2, relevance_indicators['is_whitney_official'] * 4 ]) result_data = { google_results.append(result_data) # Show high-relevance results immediately if relevance_score >= 8: print(f'\n ‚òÖ‚òÖ‚òÖ HIGH RELEVANCE RESULT (Score: {relevance_score}) ‚òÖ‚òÖ‚òÖ') print(f' Title: import os import requests from bs4 import BeautifulSoup import json from datetime import datetime import time print('=== WHITNEY MUSEUM 2022 PHOTOGRAPHIC ACQUISITIONS SEARCH ===') print('Objective: Find Whitney Museum press releases about 2022 photographic acquisitions') print('Focus: Press releases about photographs featuring portraits or figures with books\n') # Create workspace directory if it doesn't exist if not os.path.exists('workspace'): os.makedirs('workspace') # First, let's analyze the saved Whitney press page print('=== ANALYZING SAVED WHITNEY PRESS PAGE ===\n') # Check for the saved press page file press_page_files = [f for f in os.listdir('workspace') if 'whitney_page_2_press' in f and f.endswith('.html')] if press_page_files: press_file = press_page_files[0] print(f'Found saved press page: {press_file}') with open(f'workspace/{press_file}', 'r', encoding='utf-8') as f: press_content = f.read() print(f'Press page content length: {len(press_content):,} characters') # Parse the press page content press_soup = BeautifulSoup(press_content, 'html.parser') # Extract all text for analysis press_text = press_soup.get_text() press_text_lower = press_text.lower() # Look for 2022 content specifically if '2022' in press_text_lower: print('\n‚òÖ‚òÖ‚òÖ FOUND 2022 CONTENT IN PRESS PAGE! ‚òÖ‚òÖ‚òÖ') # Find lines containing 2022 press_lines = press_text.split('\n') relevant_2022_lines = [] for i, line in enumerate(press_lines): if '2022' in line.lower(): # Get context around the 2022 mention start = max(0, i-2) end = min(len(press_lines), i+3) context = press_lines[start:end] relevant_2022_lines.extend(context) # Remove duplicates and empty lines unique_2022_lines = [] for line in relevant_2022_lines: clean_line = line.strip() if clean_line and clean_line not in unique_2022_lines: unique_2022_lines.append(clean_line) print('\n2022 Context from Press Page:') for line in unique_2022_lines[:15]: # Show first 15 relevant lines print(f' {line}') # Look for press release links on the page press_links = [] for link in press_soup.find_all('a', href=True): href = link.get('href', '') text = link.get_text().strip() if href and text and len(text) > 5: # Check for press release indicators combined_text = f'{text} {href}'.lower() if any(term in combined_text for term in ['press', 'release', 'announcement', 'news', '2022']): if href.startswith('/'): full_url = 'https://whitney.org' + href elif href.startswith('http'): full_url = href else: continue press_links.append({ 'url': full_url, 'text': text, 'has_2022': '2022' in combined_text, 'has_press': any(term in combined_text for term in ['press', 'release', 'announcement']) }) print(f'\nFound {len(press_links)} press-related links on the page') # Show most promising links priority_press_links = [link for link in press_links if link['has_2022'] or link['has_press']] if priority_press_links: print(f'\nPriority press links ({len(priority_press_links)}):') for i, link in enumerate(priority_press_links[:5], 1): markers = [] if link['has_2022']: markers.append('2022') if link['has_press']: markers.append('PRESS') print(f' {i}. [{"|".join(markers)}] {link["text"][:60]}...') print(f' URL: {link["url"]}') print() else: print('No saved Whitney press page found') press_links = [] # Now use Google Search API for comprehensive search api_key = os.getenv("SERPAPI_API_KEY") if api_key: print('\n=== GOOGLE SEARCH FOR WHITNEY 2022 PHOTOGRAPHIC ACQUISITIONS ===\n') # Multiple targeted search queries search_queries = [ 'Whitney Museum 2022 acquisition photography portrait book press release', 'site:whitney.org 2022 acquired photograph portrait figure book', '"Whitney Museum" "2022" "acquisition" "photograph" "portrait" "book"', 'Whitney Museum press release 2022 new acquisition photography', '"Whitney Museum" "2022" "gift" "donation" photograph portrait book', 'Whitney Museum 2022 collection acquisition photographic works portrait' ] google_results = [] for i, query in enumerate(search_queries, 1): print(f'Search {i}: "{query}"') params = { "q": query, "api_key": api_key, "engine": "google", "google_domain": "google.com", "safe": "off", "num": 10 } try: response = requests.get("https://serpapi.com/search.json", params=params) if response.status_code == 200: results = response.json() if results.get("organic_results"): print(f' Found {len(results["organic_results"])} results') for j, result in enumerate(results["organic_results"], 1): title = result.get('title', 'No title') link = result.get('link', 'No link') snippet = result.get('snippet', 'No snippet') # Analyze result relevance combined_text = f'{title} {snippet}'.lower() relevance_indicators = { 'has_whitney': 'whitney' in combined_text, 'has_2022': '2022' in combined_text, 'has_acquisition': any(term in combined_text for term in ['acquisition', 'acquired', 'gift', 'donation']), 'has_photograph': any(term in combined_text for term in ['photograph', 'photography', 'photo']), 'has_portrait': 'portrait' in combined_text, 'has_book': 'book' in combined_text, 'is_whitney_official': 'whitney.org' in link.lower() } # Calculate relevance score relevance_score = sum([ relevance_indicators['has_whitney'] * 2, relevance_indicators['has_2022'] * 3, relevance_indicators['has_acquisition'] * 3, relevance_indicators['has_photograph'] * 2, relevance_indicators['has_portrait'] * 2, relevance_indicators['has_book'] * 2, relevance_indicators['is_whitney_official'] * 4 ]) result_data = { 'search_query': query, 'result_number': j, 'title': title, 'link': link, 'snippet': snippet, 'relevance_score': relevance_score, 'relevance_indicators': relevance_indicators } google_results.append(result_data) # Show high-relevance results immediately if relevance_score >= 8: print(f'\n ‚òÖ‚òÖ‚òÖ HIGH RELEVANCE RESULT (Score: {relevance_score}) ‚òÖ‚òÖ‚òÖ') print(f' Title: {title}') print(f' URL: {link}') print(f' Snippet: {snippet}') # Show which indicators triggered active_indicators = [k for k, v in relevance_indicators.items() if v] print(f' Indicators: {active_indicators}') print() elif relevance_score >= 5: print(f' ‚Ä¢ Relevant (Score: {relevance_score}): {title[:50]}...') print(f' URL: {link}') else: print(' No organic results found') else: print(f' Search failed with status: {response.status_code}') except Exception as e: print(f' Search error: {str(e)}') time.sleep(1) # Rate limiting print() # Save all search results with open('workspace/whitney_2022_acquisition_search_results.json', 'w') as f: json.dump(google_results, f, indent=2) print(f'Google search results saved to: workspace/whitney_2022_acquisition_search_results.json') print(f'Total Google results collected: {len(google_results)}') # Analyze and prioritize results high_relevance_results = [r for r in google_results if r['relevance_score'] >= 8] medium_relevance_results = [r for r in google_results if 5 <= r['relevance_score'] < 8] whitney_official_results = [r for r in google_results if r['relevance_indicators']['is_whitney_official']] print(f'\n=== SEARCH RESULTS ANALYSIS ===') print(f'High relevance results (score >= 8): {len(high_relevance_results)}') print(f'Medium relevance results (score 5-7): {len(medium_relevance_results)}') print(f'Whitney Museum official results: {len(whitney_official_results)}') if high_relevance_results: print(f'\n‚òÖ‚òÖ‚òÖ TOP HIGH-RELEVANCE RESULTS ‚òÖ‚òÖ‚òÖ') # Sort by relevance score high_relevance_results.sort(key=lambda x: x['relevance_score'], reverse=True) for i, result in enumerate(high_relevance_results[:3], 1): print(f'\n{i}. {result["title"]} (Score: {result["relevance_score"]})') print(f' URL: {result["link"]}') print(f' Snippet: {result["snippet"]}') print(f' Query: {result["search_query"]}') # Show specific indicators active_indicators = [k.replace('has_', '').replace('is_', '') for k, v in result['relevance_indicators'].items() if v] print(f' Matches: {active_indicators}') if whitney_official_results: print(f'\n‚òÖ‚òÖ WHITNEY MUSEUM OFFICIAL RESULTS ‚òÖ‚òÖ') for i, result in enumerate(whitney_official_results[:3], 1): print(f'\n{i}. {result["title"]} (Score: {result["relevance_score"]})') print(f' URL: {result["link"]}') print(f' Snippet: {result["snippet"][:150]}...') else: print('\nNo SERPAPI key available - skipping Google search') google_results = [] # Compile comprehensive search summary search_summary = { 'search_timestamp': datetime.now().strftime('%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S'), 'objective': 'Find Whitney Museum 2022 photographic acquisitions featuring portraits or figures with books', 'whitney_press_page_analyzed': len(press_page_files) > 0, 'press_links_found_on_whitney': len(press_links) if 'press_links' in locals() else 0, 'google_searches_performed': len(search_queries) if api_key else 0, 'total_google_results': len(google_results), 'high_relevance_results': len([r for r in google_results if r['relevance_score'] >= 8]) if google_results else 0, 'whitney_official_results': len([r for r in google_results if r['relevance_indicators']['is_whitney_official']]) if google_results else 0, 'files_created': [ f for f in os.listdir('workspace') if 'whitney' in f and (f.endswith('.json') or f.endswith('.html')) ] } with open('workspace/whitney_2022_acquisition_search_summary.json', 'w') as f: json.dump(search_summary, f, indent=2) print(f'\n=== COMPREHENSIVE SEARCH COMPLETE ===') print(f'Search summary saved to: workspace/whitney_2022_acquisition_search_summary.json') print(f'Files created: {len(search_summary["files_created"])}') if google_results: high_rel_count = len([r for r in google_results if r['relevance_score'] >= 8]) whitney_official_count = len([r for r in google_results if r['relevance_indicators']['is_whitney_official']]) print(f'\n‚òÖ SEARCH SUCCESS METRICS:') print(f' High-relevance results found: {high_rel_count}') print(f' Whitney Museum official results: {whitney_official_count}') print(f' Total search results: {len(google_results)}') if high_rel_count > 0 or whitney_official_count > 0: print(f'\n‚úì PROMISING LEADS DISCOVERED!') print(f' Next step: Access and analyze the high-relevance results for specific 2022 photographic acquisitions') print(f' Focus: Look for press releases about photographs featuring portraits or figures with books') else: print(f'\n‚ö†Ô∏è No high-relevance Whitney Museum 2022 photographic acquisition announcements found') print(f' Consider: Expanding search terms or checking art news sources like Artforum, ARTnews, Hyperallergic') else: print(f'\n‚ö†Ô∏è Google search not performed - check SERPAPI_API_KEY') print('\nWhitney Museum 2022 photographic acquisitions search complete.')

import os import requests from bs4 import BeautifulSoup import json from datetime import datetime import time print('=== WHITNEY MUSEUM 2022 PHOTOGRAPHIC ACQUISITIONS SEARCH - FIXED ===') print('Objective: Find Whitney Museum press releases about 2022 photographic acquisitions') print('Focus: Press releases about photographs featuring portraits or figures with books\n') # Create workspace directory if it doesn't exist if not os.path.exists('workspace'): os.makedirs('workspace') # First, let's analyze the saved Whitney press page print('=== ANALYZING SAVED WHITNEY PRESS PAGE ===\n') # Check for the saved press page file press_page_files = [f for f in os.listdir('workspace') if 'whitney_page_2_press' in f and f.endswith('.html')] if press_page_files: press_file = press_page_files[0] print(f'Found saved press page: {press_file}') with open(f'workspace/{press_file}', 'r', encoding='utf-8') as f: press_content = f.read() print(f'Press page content length: {len(press_content):,} characters') # Parse the press page content press_soup = BeautifulSoup(press_content, 'html.parser') # Extract all text for analysis press_text = press_soup.get_text() press_text_lower = press_text.lower() # Look for 2022 content specifically if '2022' in press_text_lower: print('\n‚òÖ‚òÖ‚òÖ FOUND 2022 CONTENT IN PRESS PAGE! ‚òÖ‚òÖ‚òÖ') # Find lines containing 2022 press_lines = press_text.split('\n') relevant_2022_lines = [] for i, line in enumerate(press_lines): if '2022' in line.lower(): # Get context around the 2022 mention start = max(0, i-2) end = min(len(press_lines), i+3) context = press_lines[start:end] relevant_2022_lines.extend(context) # Remove duplicates and empty lines unique_2022_lines = [] for line in relevant_2022_lines: clean_line = line.strip() if clean_line and clean_line not in unique_2022_lines: unique_2022_lines.append(clean_line) print('\n2022 Context from Press Page:') for line in unique_2022_lines[:15]: # Show first 15 relevant lines print(f' {line}') # Look for press release links on the page - FIXED VERSION press_links = [] for link in press_soup.find_all('a', href=True): href = link.get('href', '') text = link.get_text().strip() if href and text and len(text) > 5: # CRITICAL FIX: Define combined_text BEFORE using it combined_text = f'{text} {href}'.lower() # Check for press release indicators if any(term in combined_text for term in ['press', 'release', 'announcement', 'news', '2022']): if href.startswith('/'): full_url = 'https://whitney.org' + href elif href.startswith('http'): full_url = href else: continue press_links.append({ 'url': full_url, 'text': text, 'has_2022': '2022' in combined_text, 'has_press': any(term in combined_text for term in ['press', 'release', 'announcement']) }) print(f'\nFound {len(press_links)} press-related links on the page') # Show most promising links priority_press_links = [link for link in press_links if link['has_2022'] or link['has_press']] if priority_press_links: print(f'\nPriority press links ({len(priority_press_links)}):') for i, link in enumerate(priority_press_links[:5], 1): markers = [] if link['has_2022']: markers.append('2022') if link['has_press']: markers.append('PRESS') print(f' {i}. [{"|'.join(markers)}] {link["text"][:60]}...') print(f' URL: {link["url"]}') print() else: print('No saved Whitney press page found') press_links = [] # Now use Google Search API for comprehensive search api_key = os.getenv("SERPAPI_API_KEY") if api_key: print('\n=== GOOGLE SEARCH FOR WHITNEY 2022 PHOTOGRAPHIC ACQUISITIONS ===\n') # Multiple targeted search queries search_queries = [ 'Whitney Museum 2022 acquisition photography portrait book press release', 'site:whitney.org 2022 acquired photograph portrait figure book', '"Whitney Museum" "2022" "acquisition" "photograph" "portrait" "book"', 'Whitney Museum press release 2022 new acquisition photography', '"Whitney Museum" "2022" "gift" "donation" photograph portrait book', 'Whitney Museum 2022 collection acquisition photographic works portrait' ] google_results = [] for i, query in enumerate(search_queries, 1): print(f'Search {i}: "{query}"') params = { "q": query, "api_key": api_key, "engine": "google", "google_domain": "google.com", "safe": "off", "num": 10 } try: response = requests.get("https://serpapi.com/search.json", params=params) if response.status_code == 200: results = response.json() if results.get("organic_results"): print(f' Found {len(results["organic_results"])} results') for j, result in enumerate(results["organic_results"], 1): title = result.get('title', 'No title') link = result.get('link', 'No link') snippet = result.get('snippet', 'No snippet') # Analyze result relevance combined_result_text = f'{title} {snippet}'.lower() relevance_indicators = { 'has_whitney': 'whitney' in combined_result_text, 'has_2022': '2022' in combined_result_text, 'has_acquisition': any(term in combined_result_text for term in ['acquisition', 'acquired', 'gift', 'donation']), 'has_photograph': any(term in combined_result_text for term in ['photograph', 'photography', 'photo']), 'has_portrait': 'portrait' in combined_result_text, 'has_book': 'book' in combined_result_text, 'is_whitney_official': 'whitney.org' in link.lower() } # Calculate relevance score relevance_score = sum([ relevance_indicators['has_whitney'] * 2, relevance_indicators['has_2022'] * 3, relevance_indicators['has_acquisition'] * 3, relevance_indicators['has_photograph'] * 2, relevance_indicators['has_portrait'] * 2, relevance_indicators['has_book'] * 2, relevance_indicators['is_whitney_official'] * 4 ]) result_data = { 'search_query': query, 'result_number': j, 'title': title, 'link': link, 'snippet': snippet, 'relevance_score': relevance_score, 'relevance_indicators': relevance_indicators } google_results.append(result_data) # Show high-relevance results immediately if relevance_score >= 8: print(f'\n ‚òÖ‚òÖ‚òÖ HIGH RELEVANCE RESULT (Score: {relevance_score}) ‚òÖ‚òÖ‚òÖ') print(f' Title: {title}') print(f' URL: {link}') print(f' Snippet: {snippet}') # Show which indicators triggered active_indicators = [k for k, v in relevance_indicators.items() if v] print(f' Indicators: {active_indicators}') print() elif relevance_score >= 5: print(f' ‚Ä¢ Relevant (Score: {relevance_score}): {title[:50]}...') print(f' URL: {link}') else: print(' No organic results found') else: print(f' Search failed with status: {response.status_code}') except Exception as e: print(f' Search error: {str(e)}') time.sleep(1) # Rate limiting print() # Save all search results with open('workspace/whitney_2022_acquisition_search_results.json', 'w') as f: json.dump(google_results, f, indent=2) print(f'Google search results saved to: workspace/whitney_2022_acquisition_search_results.json') print(f'Total Google results collected: {len(google_results)}') # Analyze and prioritize results high_relevance_results = [r for r in google_results if r['relevance_score'] >= 8] medium_relevance_results = [r for r in google_results if 5 <= r['relevance_score'] < 8] whitney_official_results = [r for r in google_results if r['relevance_indicators']['is_whitney_official']] print(f'\n=== SEARCH RESULTS ANALYSIS ===') print(f'High relevance results (score >= 8): {len(high_relevance_results)}') print(f'Medium relevance results (score 5-7): {len(medium_relevance_results)}') print(f'Whitney Museum official results: {len(whitney_official_results)}') if high_relevance_results: print(f'\n‚òÖ‚òÖ‚òÖ TOP HIGH-RELEVANCE RESULTS ‚òÖ‚òÖ‚òÖ') # Sort by relevance score high_relevance_results.sort(key=lambda x: x['relevance_score'], reverse=True) for i, result in enumerate(high_relevance_results[:3], 1): print(f'\n{i}. {result["title"]} (Score: {result["relevance_score"]})') print(f' URL: {result["link"]}') print(f' Snippet: {result["snippet"]}') print(f' Query: {result["search_query"]}') # Show specific indicators active_indicators = [k.replace('has_', '').replace('is_', '') for k, v in result['relevance_indicators'].items() if v] print(f' Matches: {active_indicators}') if whitney_official_results: print(f'\n‚òÖ‚òÖ WHITNEY MUSEUM OFFICIAL RESULTS ‚òÖ‚òÖ') for i, result in enumerate(whitney_official_results[:3], 1): print(f'\n{i}. {result["title"]} (Score: {result["relevance_score"]})') print(f' URL: {result["link"]}') print(f' Snippet: {result["snippet"][:150]}...') else: print('\nNo SERPAPI key available - skipping Google search') google_results = [] # Compile comprehensive search summary search_summary = { 'search_timestamp': datetime.now().strftime('%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S'), 'objective': 'Find Whitney Museum 2022 photographic acquisitions featuring portraits or figures with books', 'whitney_press_page_analyzed': len(press_page_files) > 0, 'press_links_found_on_whitney': len(press_links) if 'press_links' in locals() else 0, 'google_searches_performed': len(search_queries) if api_key else 0, 'total_google_results': len(google_results), 'high_relevance_results': len([r for r in google_results if r['relevance_score'] >= 8]) if google_results else 0, 'whitney_official_results': len([r for r in google_results if r['relevance_indicators']['is_whitney_official']]) if google_results else 0, 'files_created': [ f for f in os.listdir('workspace') if 'whitney' in f and (f.endswith('.json') or f.endswith('.html')) ] } with open('workspace/whitney_2022_acquisition_search_summary.json', 'w') as f: json.dump(search_summary, f, indent=2) print(f'\n=== COMPREHENSIVE SEARCH COMPLETE ===') print(f'Search summary saved to: workspace/whitney_2022_acquisition_search_summary.json') print(f'Files created: {len(search_summary["files_created"])}') if google_results: high_rel_count = len([r for r in google_results if r['relevance_score'] >= 8]) whitney_official_count = len([r for r in google_results if r['relevance_indicators']['is_whitney_official']]) print(f'\n‚òÖ SEARCH SUCCESS METRICS:') print(f' High-relevance results found: {high_rel_count}') print(f' Whitney Museum official results: {whitney_official_count}') print(f' Total search results: {len(google_results)}') if high_rel_count > 0 or whitney_official_count > 0: print(f'\n‚úì PROMISING LEADS DISCOVERED!') print(f' Next step: Access and analyze the high-relevance results for specific 2022 photographic acquisitions') print(f' Focus: Look for press releases about photographs featuring portraits or figures with books') else: print(f'\n‚ö†Ô∏è No high-relevance Whitney Museum 2022 photographic acquisition announcements found') print(f' Consider: Expanding search terms or checking art news sources like Artforum, ARTnews, Hyperallergic') else: print(f'\n‚ö†Ô∏è Google search not performed - check SERPAPI_API_KEY') print('\nWhitney Museum 2022 photographic acquisitions search complete.')

import os import requests from bs4 import BeautifulSoup import json from datetime import datetime import time print('=== WHITNEY MUSEUM 2022 PHOTOGRAPHIC ACQUISITIONS SEARCH - SYNTAX FIXED ===') print('Objective: Find Whitney Museum press releases about 2022 photographic acquisitions') print('Focus: Press releases about photographs featuring portraits or figures with books\n') # Create workspace directory if it doesn't exist if not os.path.exists('workspace'): os.makedirs('workspace') # First, let's analyze the saved Whitney press page print('=== ANALYZING SAVED WHITNEY PRESS PAGE ===\n') # Check for the saved press page file press_page_files = [f for f in os.listdir('workspace') if 'whitney_page_2_press' in f and f.endswith('.html')] if press_page_files: press_file = press_page_files[0] print(f'Found saved press page: {press_file}') with open(f'workspace/{press_file}', 'r', encoding='utf-8') as f: press_content = f.read() print(f'Press page content length: {len(press_content):,} characters') # Parse the press page content press_soup = BeautifulSoup(press_content, 'html.parser') # Extract all text for analysis press_text = press_soup.get_text() press_text_lower = press_text.lower() # Look for 2022 content specifically if '2022' in press_text_lower: print('\n‚òÖ‚òÖ‚òÖ FOUND 2022 CONTENT IN PRESS PAGE! ‚òÖ‚òÖ‚òÖ') # Find lines containing 2022 press_lines = press_text.split('\n') relevant_2022_lines = [] for i, line in enumerate(press_lines): if '2022' in line.lower(): # Get context around the 2022 mention start = max(0, i-2) end = min(len(press_lines), i+3) context = press_lines[start:end] relevant_2022_lines.extend(context) # Remove duplicates and empty lines unique_2022_lines = [] for line in relevant_2022_lines: clean_line = line.strip() if clean_line and clean_line not in unique_2022_lines: unique_2022_lines.append(clean_line) print('\n2022 Context from Press Page:') for line in unique_2022_lines[:15]: # Show first 15 relevant lines print(f' {line}') # Look for press release links on the page - FIXED VERSION press_links = [] for link in press_soup.find_all('a', href=True): href = link.get('href', '') text = link.get_text().strip() if href and text and len(text) > 5: # Define combined_text BEFORE using it combined_text = f'{text} {href}'.lower() # Check for press release indicators if any(term in combined_text for term in ['press', 'release', 'announcement', 'news', '2022']): if href.startswith('/'): full_url = 'https://whitney.org' + href elif href.startswith('http'): full_url = href else: continue press_links.append({ 'url': full_url, 'text': text, 'has_2022': '2022' in combined_text, 'has_press': any(term in combined_text for term in ['press', 'release', 'announcement']) }) print(f'\nFound {len(press_links)} press-related links on the page') # Show most promising links - SYNTAX FIXED priority_press_links = [link for link in press_links if link['has_2022'] or link['has_press']] if priority_press_links: print(f'\nPriority press links ({len(priority_press_links)}):') for i, link in enumerate(priority_press_links[:5], 1): markers = [] if link['has_2022']: markers.append('2022') if link['has_press']: markers.append('PRESS') # CRITICAL FIX: Use simple string concatenation to avoid quote conflicts markers_str = '|'.join(markers) print(f' {i}. [{markers_str}] {link["text"][:60]}...') print(f' URL: {link["url"]}') print() else: print('No saved Whitney press page found') press_links = [] # Now use Google Search API for comprehensive search api_key = os.getenv("SERPAPI_API_KEY") if api_key: print('\n=== GOOGLE SEARCH FOR WHITNEY 2022 PHOTOGRAPHIC ACQUISITIONS ===\n') # Multiple targeted search queries search_queries = [ 'Whitney Museum 2022 acquisition photography portrait book press release', 'site:whitney.org 2022 acquired photograph portrait figure book', '"Whitney Museum" "2022" "acquisition" "photograph" "portrait" "book"', 'Whitney Museum press release 2022 new acquisition photography', '"Whitney Museum" "2022" "gift" "donation" photograph portrait book', 'Whitney Museum 2022 collection acquisition photographic works portrait' ] google_results = [] for i, query in enumerate(search_queries, 1): print(f'Search {i}: "{query}"') params = { "q": query, "api_key": api_key, "engine": "google", "google_domain": "google.com", "safe": "off", "num": 10 } try: response = requests.get("https://serpapi.com/search.json", params=params) if response.status_code == 200: results = response.json() if results.get("organic_results"): print(f' Found {len(results["organic_results"])} results') for j, result in enumerate(results["organic_results"], 1): title = result.get('title', 'No title') link = result.get('link', 'No link') snippet = result.get('snippet', 'No snippet') # Analyze result relevance combined_result_text = f'{title} {snippet}'.lower() relevance_indicators = { 'has_whitney': 'whitney' in combined_result_text, 'has_2022': '2022' in combined_result_text, 'has_acquisition': any(term in combined_result_text for term in ['acquisition', 'acquired', 'gift', 'donation']), 'has_photograph': any(term in combined_result_text for term in ['photograph', 'photography', 'photo']), 'has_portrait': 'portrait' in combined_result_text, 'has_book': 'book' in combined_result_text, 'is_whitney_official': 'whitney.org' in link.lower() } # Calculate relevance score relevance_score = sum([ relevance_indicators['has_whitney'] * 2, relevance_indicators['has_2022'] * 3, relevance_indicators['has_acquisition'] * 3, relevance_indicators['has_photograph'] * 2, relevance_indicators['has_portrait'] * 2, relevance_indicators['has_book'] * 2, relevance_indicators['is_whitney_official'] * 4 ]) result_data = { 'search_query': query, 'result_number': j, 'title': title, 'link': link, 'snippet': snippet, 'relevance_score': relevance_score, 'relevance_indicators': relevance_indicators } google_results.append(result_data) # Show high-relevance results immediately if relevance_score >= 8: print(f'\n ‚òÖ‚òÖ‚òÖ HIGH RELEVANCE RESULT (Score: {relevance_score}) ‚òÖ‚òÖ‚òÖ') print(f' Title: {title}') print(f' URL: {link}') print(f' Snippet: {snippet}') # Show which indicators triggered active_indicators = [k for k, v in relevance_indicators.items() if v] print(f' Indicators: {active_indicators}') print() elif relevance_score >= 5: print(f' ‚Ä¢ Relevant (Score: {relevance_score}): {title[:50]}...') print(f' URL: {link}') else: print(' No organic results found') else: print(f' Search failed with status: {response.status_code}') except Exception as e: print(f' Search error: {str(e)}') time.sleep(1) # Rate limiting print() # Save all search results with open('workspace/whitney_2022_acquisition_search_results.json', 'w') as f: json.dump(google_results, f, indent=2) print(f'Google search results saved to: workspace/whitney_2022_acquisition_search_results.json') print(f'Total Google results collected: {len(google_results)}') # Analyze and prioritize results high_relevance_results = [r for r in google_results if r['relevance_score'] >= 8] medium_relevance_results = [r for r in google_results if 5 <= r['relevance_score'] < 8] whitney_official_results = [r for r in google_results if r['relevance_indicators']['is_whitney_official']] print(f'\n=== SEARCH RESULTS ANALYSIS ===') print(f'High relevance results (score >= 8): {len(high_relevance_results)}') print(f'Medium relevance results (score 5-7): {len(medium_relevance_results)}') print(f'Whitney Museum official results: {len(whitney_official_results)}') if high_relevance_results: print(f'\n‚òÖ‚òÖ‚òÖ TOP HIGH-RELEVANCE RESULTS ‚òÖ‚òÖ‚òÖ') # Sort by relevance score high_relevance_results.sort(key=lambda x: x['relevance_score'], reverse=True) for i, result in enumerate(high_relevance_results[:3], 1): print(f'\n{i}. {result["title"]} (Score: {result["relevance_score"]})') print(f' URL: {result["link"]}') print(f' Snippet: {result["snippet"]}') print(f' Query: {result["search_query"]}') # Show specific indicators active_indicators = [k.replace('has_', '').replace('is_', '') for k, v in result['relevance_indicators'].items() if v] print(f' Matches: {active_indicators}') if whitney_official_results: print(f'\n‚òÖ‚òÖ WHITNEY MUSEUM OFFICIAL RESULTS ‚òÖ‚òÖ') for i, result in enumerate(whitney_official_results[:3], 1): print(f'\n{i}. {result["title"]} (Score: {result["relevance_score"]})') print(f' URL: {result["link"]}') print(f' Snippet: {result["snippet"][:150]}...') else: print('\nNo SERPAPI key available - skipping Google search') google_results = [] # Compile comprehensive search summary search_summary = { 'search_timestamp': datetime.now().strftime('%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S'), 'objective': 'Find Whitney Museum 2022 photographic acquisitions featuring portraits or figures with books', 'whitney_press_page_analyzed': len(press_page_files) > 0, 'press_links_found_on_whitney': len(press_links) if 'press_links' in locals() else 0, 'google_searches_performed': len(search_queries) if api_key else 0, 'total_google_results': len(google_results), 'high_relevance_results': len([r for r in google_results if r['relevance_score'] >= 8]) if google_results else 0, 'whitney_official_results': len([r for r in google_results if r['relevance_indicators']['is_whitney_official']]) if google_results else 0, 'files_created': [ f for f in os.listdir('workspace') if 'whitney' in f and (f.endswith('.json') or f.endswith('.html')) ] } with open('workspace/whitney_2022_acquisition_search_summary.json', 'w') as f: json.dump(search_summary, f, indent=2) print(f'\n=== COMPREHENSIVE SEARCH COMPLETE ===') print(f'Search summary saved to: workspace/whitney_2022_acquisition_search_summary.json') print(f'Files created: {len(search_summary["files_created"])}') if google_results: high_rel_count = len([r for r in google_results if r['relevance_score'] >= 8]) whitney_official_count = len([r for r in google_results if r['relevance_indicators']['is_whitney_official']]) print(f'\n‚òÖ SEARCH SUCCESS METRICS:') print(f' High-relevance results found: {high_rel_count}') print(f' Whitney Museum official results: {whitney_official_count}') print(f' Total search results: {len(google_results)}') if high_rel_count > 0 or whitney_official_count > 0: print(f'\n‚úì PROMISING LEADS DISCOVERED!') print(f' Next step: Access and analyze the high-relevance results for specific 2022 photographic acquisitions') print(f' Focus: Look for press releases about photographs featuring portraits or figures with books') else: print(f'\n‚ö†Ô∏è No high-relevance Whitney Museum 2022 photographic acquisition announcements found') print(f' Consider: Expanding search terms or checking art news sources like Artforum, ARTnews, Hyperallergic') else: print(f'\n‚ö†Ô∏è Google search not performed - check SERPAPI_API_KEY') print('\nWhitney Museum 2022 photographic acquisitions search complete.')
