import os import requests from bs4 import BeautifulSoup import json from datetime import datetime import time print('=== WHITNEY MUSEUM 2022 PHOTOGRAPHIC ACQUISITIONS SEARCH - FINAL FIXED ===') print('Objective: Find Whitney Museum press releases about 2022 photographic acquisitions') print('Focus: Press releases about photographs featuring portraits or figures with books\n') # Create workspace directory if it doesn't exist if not os.path.exists('workspace'): os.makedirs('workspace') # First, let's analyze the saved Whitney press page print('=== ANALYZING SAVED WHITNEY PRESS PAGE ===\n') # Check for the saved press page file press_page_files = [f for f in os.listdir('workspace') if 'whitney_page_2_press' in f and f.endswith('.html')] if press_page_files: press_file = press_page_files[0] print(f'Found saved press page: {press_file}') with open(f'workspace/{press_file}', 'r', encoding='utf-8') as f: press_content = f.read() print(f'Press page content length: {len(press_content):,} characters') # Parse the press page content press_soup = BeautifulSoup(press_content, 'html.parser') # Extract all text for analysis press_text = press_soup.get_text() press_text_lower = press_text.lower() # Look for 2022 content specifically if '2022' in press_text_lower: print('\n‚òÖ‚òÖ‚òÖ FOUND 2022 CONTENT IN PRESS PAGE! ‚òÖ‚òÖ‚òÖ') # Find lines containing 2022 press_lines = press_text.split('\n') relevant_2022_lines = [] for i, line in enumerate(press_lines): if '2022' in line.lower(): # Get context around the 2022 mention start = max(0, i-2) end = min(len(press_lines), i+3) context = press_lines[start:end] relevant_2022_lines.extend(context) # Remove duplicates and empty lines unique_2022_lines = [] for line in relevant_2022_lines: clean_line = line.strip() if clean_line and clean_line not in unique_2022_lines: unique_2022_lines.append(clean_line) print('\n2022 Context from Press Page:') for line in unique_2022_lines[:15]: # Show first 15 relevant lines print(f' {line}') # Look for press release links on the page - COMPLETELY FIXED VERSION press_links = [] for link in press_soup.find_all('a', href=True): href = link.get('href', '') text = link.get_text().strip() if href and text and len(text) > 5: # CRITICAL FIX: Define combined_text BEFORE any conditional checks combined_text = f'{text} {href}'.lower() # Now check for press release indicators using explicit loop instead of generator has_press_terms = False press_terms = ['press', 'release', 'announcement', 'news', '2022'] for term in press_terms: if term in combined_text: has_press_terms = True break if has_press_terms: if href.startswith('/'): full_url = 'https://whitney.org' + href elif href.startswith('http'): full_url = href else: continue # Check specific indicators has_2022 = '2022' in combined_text # Check for press terms using explicit loop has_press = False press_check_terms = ['press', 'release', 'announcement'] for term in press_check_terms: if term in combined_text: has_press = True break press_links.append({ 'url': full_url, 'text': text, 'has_2022': has_2022, 'has_press': has_press }) print(f'\nFound {len(press_links)} press-related links on the page') # Show most promising links priority_press_links = [link for link in press_links if link['has_2022'] or link['has_press']] if priority_press_links: print(f'\nPriority press links ({len(priority_press_links)}):') for i, link in enumerate(priority_press_links[:5], 1): markers = [] if link['has_2022']: markers.append('2022') if link['has_press']: markers.append('PRESS') markers_str = '|'.join(markers) print(f' {i}. [{markers_str}] {link["text"][:60]}...') print(f' URL: {link["url"]}') print() else: print('No saved Whitney press page found') press_links = [] # Now use Google Search API for comprehensive search api_key = os.getenv("SERPAPI_API_KEY") if api_key: print('\n=== GOOGLE SEARCH FOR WHITNEY 2022 PHOTOGRAPHIC ACQUISITIONS ===\n') # Multiple targeted search queries search_queries = [ 'Whitney Museum 2022 acquisition photography portrait book press release', 'site:whitney.org 2022 acquired photograph portrait figure book', '"Whitney Museum" "2022" "acquisition" "photograph" "portrait" "book"', 'Whitney Museum press release 2022 new acquisition photography', '"Whitney Museum" "2022" "gift" "donation" photograph portrait book', 'Whitney Museum 2022 collection acquisition photographic works portrait' ] google_results = [] for i, query in enumerate(search_queries, 1): print(f'Search {i}: "{query}"') params = { "q": query, "api_key": api_key, "engine": "google", "google_domain": "google.com", "safe": "off", "num": 10 } try: response = requests.get("https://serpapi.com/search.json", params=params) if response.status_code == 200: results = response.json() if results.get("organic_results"): print(f' Found {len(results["organic_results"])} results') for j, result in enumerate(results["organic_results"], 1): title = result.get('title', 'No title') link = result.get('link', 'No link') snippet = result.get('snippet', 'No snippet') # Analyze result relevance combined_result_text = f'{title} {snippet}'.lower() relevance_indicators = { 'has_whitney': 'whitney' in combined_result_text, 'has_2022': '2022' in combined_result_text, 'has_acquisition': any(term in combined_result_text for term in ['acquisition', 'acquired', 'gift', 'donation']), 'has_photograph': any(term in combined_result_text for term in ['photograph', 'photography', 'photo']), 'has_portrait': 'portrait' in combined_result_text, 'has_book': 'book' in combined_result_text, 'is_whitney_official': 'whitney.org' in link.lower() } # Calculate relevance score relevance_score = sum([ relevance_indicators['has_whitney'] * 2, relevance_indicators['has_2022'] * 3, relevance_indicators['has_acquisition'] * 3, relevance_indicators['has_photograph'] * 2, relevance_indicators['has_portrait'] * 2, relevance_indicators['has_book'] * 2, relevance_indicators['is_whitney_official'] * 4 ]) result_data = { 'search_query': query, 'result_number': j, 'title': title, 'link': link, 'snippet': snippet, 'relevance_score': relevance_score, 'relevance_indicators': relevance_indicators } google_results.append(result_data) # Show high-relevance results immediately if relevance_score >= 8: print(f'\n ‚òÖ‚òÖ‚òÖ HIGH RELEVANCE RESULT (Score: relevance_indicators.items() if v] print(f' Indicators: {active_indicators}') print() elif relevance_score >= 5: print(f' ‚Ä¢ Relevant (Score: {relevance_score}): {title[:50]}...') print(f' URL: {link}') else: print(' No organic results found') else: print(f' Search failed with status: {response.status_code}') except Exception as e: print(f' Search error: {str(e)}') time.sleep(1) # Rate limiting print() # Save all search results with open('workspace/whitney_2022_acquisition_search_results.json', 'w') as f: json.dump(google_results, f, indent=2) print(f'Google search results saved to: workspace/whitney_2022_acquisition_search_results.json') print(f'Total Google results collected: {len(google_results)}') # Analyze and prioritize results high_relevance_results = [r for r in google_results if r['relevance_score'] >= 8] medium_relevance_results = [r for r in google_results if 5 <= r['relevance_score'] < 8] whitney_official_results = [r for r in google_results if r['relevance_indicators']['is_whitney_official']] print(f'\n=== SEARCH RESULTS ANALYSIS ===') print(f'High relevance results (score >= 8): {len(high_relevance_results)}') print(f'Medium relevance results (score 5-7): {len(medium_relevance_results)}') print(f'Whitney Museum official results: {len(whitney_official_results)}') if high_relevance_results: print(f'\n‚òÖ‚òÖ‚òÖ TOP HIGH-RELEVANCE import os import requests from bs4 import BeautifulSoup import json from datetime import datetime import time import re print('=== ACCESSING WHITNEY MUSEUM PRESS ARCHIVE FOR 2022 ACQUISITIONS ===') print('Objective: Find Whitney Museum 2022 photographic acquisition press releases') print('Focus: Direct access to press archive to bypass API rate limits\n') # Create workspace directory if it doesn't exist if not os.path.exists('workspace'): os.makedirs('workspace') # First, let's inspect the existing search summary to understand what we have print('=== INSPECTING EXISTING SEARCH RESULTS ===\n') summary_files = [f for f in os.listdir('workspace') if 'search_summary' in f and f.endswith('.json')] if summary_files: print(f'Found search summary files: {summary_files}') # Inspect the structure first summary_file = summary_files[0] print(f'\nInspecting: {summary_file}') with open(f'workspace/{summary_file}', 'r') as f: summary_data = json.load(f) print(f'Summary file structure: {list(summary_data.keys())}') for key, value in summary_data.items(): if isinstance(value, (int, str, bool)): print(f' {key}: {value}') elif isinstance(value, list): print(f' {key}: List with {len(value)} items') else: print(f' {key}: {type(value).__name__}') # Now access the Whitney Museum press archive directly print('\n=== ACCESSING WHITNEY MUSEUM PRESS ARCHIVE ===\n') archive_url = 'https://whitney.org/press/archive' print(f'Accessing: {archive_url}') headers = { 'User-Agent': 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 10.0; Win64; x64) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/91.0.4472.124 Safari/537.36' } try: response = requests.get(archive_url, headers=headers, timeout=30) if response.status_code == 200: print(f'‚úì Successfully accessed press archive (Status: {response.status_code})') print(f'Content length: {len(response.content):,} bytes') # Save the press archive page archive_filename = 'workspace/whitney_press_archive.html' with open(archive_filename, 'w', encoding='utf-8') as f: f.write(response.text) print(f'‚úì Press archive saved to: {archive_filename}') # Parse the archive content soup = BeautifulSoup(response.content, 'html.parser') # Extract page title page_title = soup.find('title') if page_title: print(f'Page title: {page_title.get_text().strip()}') # Look for 2022 content in the archive page_text = soup.get_text().lower() if '2022' in page_text: print('\n‚òÖ‚òÖ‚òÖ FOUND 2022 CONTENT IN PRESS ARCHIVE! ‚òÖ‚òÖ‚òÖ') # Find all links that might be press releases press_release_links = [] for link in soup.find_all('a', href=True): href = link.get('href', '') text = link.get_text().strip() if href and text and len(text) > 10: # Substantial link text link_text_lower = text.lower() href_lower = href.lower() # Check for 2022 and acquisition-related terms has_2022 = '2022' in link_text_lower or '2022' in href_lower has_acquisition_terms = any(term in link_text_lower for term in [ 'acquisition', 'acquired', 'gift', 'donation', 'collection' ]) has_photo_terms = any(term in link_text_lower for term in [ 'photograph', 'photography', 'photo', 'image' ]) has_portrait_terms = any(term in link_text_lower for term in [ 'portrait', 'figure', 'person', 'book' ]) # Calculate relevance score relevance_score = ( has_2022 * 4 + has_acquisition_terms * 3 + has_photo_terms * 2 + has_portrait_terms * 2 ) if relevance_score >= 4: # Promising links # Construct full URL if href.startswith('/'): full_url = 'https://whitney.org' + href elif href.startswith('http'): full_url = href else: continue press_release_links.append({ 'url': full_url, 'text': text, 'relevance_score': relevance_score, 'has_2022': has_2022, 'has_acquisition_terms': has_acquisition_terms, 'has_photo_terms': has_photo_terms, 'has_portrait_terms': has_portrait_terms }) print(f'\nFound {len(press_release_links)} potentially relevant press releases') # Sort by relevance score and show top results press_release_links.sort(key=lambda x: x['relevance_score'], reverse=True) if press_release_links: print('\n‚òÖ‚òÖ‚òÖ TOP RELEVANT PRESS RELEASES ‚òÖ‚òÖ‚òÖ') for i, link in enumerate(press_release_links[:8], 1): # Show top 8 indicators = [] if link['has_2022']: indicators.append('2022') if link['has_acquisition_terms']: indicators.append('ACQUISITION') if link['has_photo_terms']: indicators.append('PHOTO') if link['has_portrait_terms']: indicators.append('PORTRAIT') indicators_str = '|'.join(indicators) print(f'\n{i}. [{indicators_str}] Score: {link["relevance_score"]}') print(f' Title: {link["text"][:80]}...') print(f' URL: {link["url"]}') # Save the press release links for further analysis with open('workspace/whitney_2022_press_releases.json', 'w') as f: json.dump(press_release_links, f, indent=2) print(f'\n‚úì Press release links saved to: workspace/whitney_2022_press_releases.json') # Now try to access the most promising press releases print('\n=== ACCESSING TOP PRESS RELEASES FOR DETAILED ANALYSIS ===\n') top_releases = press_release_links[:3] # Access top 3 most relevant detailed_releases = [] for i, release in enumerate(top_releases, 1): print(f'Accessing release {i}: {release["text"][:50]}...') print(f'URL: {release["url"]}') try: release_response = requests.get(release['url'], headers=headers, timeout=20) if release_response.status_code == 200: print(f' ‚úì Successfully accessed (Status: {release_response.status_code})') # Parse the press release content release_soup = BeautifulSoup(release_response.content, 'html.parser') release_text = release_soup.get_text() # Look for specific acquisition and photography terms release_text_lower = release_text.lower() # Check for key terms that would indicate this is our target key_findings = { 'has_2022_date': '2022' in release_text_lower, 'has_acquisition': any(term in release_text_lower for term in [ 'acquisition', 'acquired', 'gift', 'donation', 'adds to', 'new to collection' ]), 'has_photograph': any(term in release_text_lower for term in [ 'photograph', 'photography', 'photographic', 'image' ]), 'has_portrait': any(term in release_text_lower for term in [ 'portrait', 'figure', 'person', 'subject' ]), 'has_book': 'book' in release_text_lower, 'has_holding_book': any(phrase in release_text_lower for phrase in [ 'holding a book', 'with a book', 'reading', 'book in hand' ]) } findings_score = sum(key_findings.values()) print(f' Analysis score: {findings_score}/6') print(f' Key findings: {[k for k, v in key_findings.items() if v]}') if findings_score >= 3: # Promising content print(f' ‚òÖ‚òÖ‚òÖ HIGH-RELEVANCE PRESS RELEASE! ‚òÖ‚òÖ‚òÖ') # Save the full press release release_filename = f'workspace/whitney_press_release_{i}_detailed.html' with open(release_filename, 'w', encoding='utf-8') as f: f.write(release_response.text) print(f' ‚úì Detailed release saved to: {release_filename}') # Extract key sections for analysis title_element = release_soup.find('title') h1_elements = release_soup.find_all(['h1', 'h2', 'h3']) release_analysis = { 'url': release['url'], 'title': title_element.get_text().strip() if title_element else 'No title', 'headings': [h.get_text().strip() for h in h1_elements[:5]], 'key_findings': key_findings, 'findings_score': findings_score, 'content_length': len(release_text), 'filename': release_filename } detailed_releases.append(release_analysis) # Show key content excerpts if key_findings['has_acquisition'] and key_findings['has_photograph']: print(f' üì∏ POTENTIAL PHOTOGRAPHIC ACQUISITION FOUND!') # Look for specific content about the photograph lines = release_text.split('\n') relevant_lines = [] for line in lines: line_lower = line.strip().lower() if (any(term in line_lower for term in ['photograph', 'portrait', 'book']) and len(line.strip()) > 20): relevant_lines.append(line.strip()) if relevant_lines: print(f' Key content excerpts:') for excerpt in relevant_lines[:3]: # Show top 3 excerpts print(f' "{excerpt[:100]}..."') else: print(f' ‚úó Failed to access (Status: {release_response.status_code})') except Exception as e: print(f' ‚úó Error accessing release: {str(e)}') time.sleep(2) # Be respectful to servers print() # Save detailed analysis if detailed_releases: with open('workspace/whitney_2022_detailed_press_analysis.json', 'w') as f: json.dump(detailed_releases, f, indent=2) print(f'‚úì Detailed press release analysis saved to: workspace/whitney_2022_detailed_press_analysis.json') # Summary of findings high_relevance_count = len([r for r in detailed_releases if r['findings_score'] >= 4]) photo_acquisition_count = len([r for r in detailed_releases if r['key_findings']['has_acquisition'] and r['key_findings']['has_photograph']]) print(f'\n=== SEARCH RESULTS SUMMARY ===') print(f'Total press releases analyzed: {len(detailed_releases)}') print(f'High-relevance releases (score >= 4): {high_relevance_count}') print(f'Potential photographic acquisitions: {photo_acquisition_count}') if photo_acquisition_count > 0: print(f'\nüéØ SUCCESS: Found potential 2022 Whitney Museum photographic acquisitions!') print(f'Next step: Review the detailed HTML files for complete information') else: print(f'\n‚ö†Ô∏è No clear photographic acquisitions with portrait/book elements found') print(f'Consider: Manual review of saved press releases for additional context') else: print('\nNo relevant press release links found in archive') else: print('\n‚ö†Ô∏è No 2022 content found in press archive') print('Archive may use different date formatting or pagination') else: print(f'‚úó Failed to access press archive (Status: {response.status_code})') print(f'Response: {response.text[:200]}...') except Exception as e: print(f'‚úó Exception accessing press archive: {str(e)}') # Create final comprehensive summary final_summary = { 'search_timestamp': datetime.now().strftime('%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S'), 'objective': 'Find Whitney Museum 2022 photographic acquisitions featuring portraits or figures with books', 'method': 'Direct access to Whitney Museum press archive', 'archive_url': archive_url, 'archive_accessed': response.status_code == 200 if 'response' in locals() else False, 'press_releases_found': len(press_release_links) if 'press_release_links' in locals() else 0, 'detailed_releases_analyzed': len(detailed_releases) if 'detailed_releases' in locals() else 0, 'files_created': [ f for f in os.listdir('workspace') if f.startswith('whitney') and (f.endswith('.json') or f.endswith('.html')) ] } with open('workspace/whitney_2022_final_search_summary.json', 'w') as f: json.dump(final_summary, f, indent=2) print(f'\n=== WHITNEY MUSEUM 2022 ACQUISITION SEARCH COMPLETE ===') print(f'Final summary saved to: workspace/whitney_2022_final_search_summary.json') print(f'Total files created: {len(final_summary["files_created"])}') print(f'\nAll Whitney Museum press archive content has been analyzed for 2022 photographic acquisitions.')

import os import requests from bs4 import BeautifulSoup import json from datetime import datetime import time import re print('=== WHITNEY MUSEUM PRESS ARCHIVE ANALYSIS - VARIABLE SCOPING FIXED ===') print('Objective: Find Whitney Museum 2022 photographic acquisition press releases') print('Focus: Direct access to press archive with proper variable definitions\n') # Parse the existing archive content soup = BeautifulSoup(archive_content, 'html.parser') else: print('No existing archive found, accessing Whitney Museum press archive...') archive_url = 'https://whitney.org/press/archive' print(f'Accessing: {archive_url}') headers = { 'User-Agent': 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 10.0; Win64; x64) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/91.0.4472.124 Safari/537.36' } try: response = requests.get(archive_url, headers=headers, timeout=30) if response.status_code == 200: print(f'‚úì Successfully accessed press archive (Status: {response.status_code})') print(f'Content length: {len(response.content):,} bytes') # Save the press archive page archive_filename = 'workspace/whitney_press_archive.html' with open(archive_filename, 'w', encoding='utf-8') as f: f.write(response.text) print(f'‚úì Press archive saved to: {archive_filename}') # Parse the archive content soup = BeautifulSoup(response.content, 'html.parser') archive_content = response.text else: print(f'‚úó Failed to access press archive (Status: {response.status_code})') print(f'Response: {response.text[:200]}...') soup = None archive_content = None except Exception as e: print(f'‚úó Exception accessing press archive: {str(e)}') soup = None archive_content = None if soup and archive_content: print('\n=== ANALYZING PRESS ARCHIVE FOR 2022 ACQUISITIONS ===\n') # Extract page title page_title = soup.find('title') if page_title: print(f'Page title: {page_title.get_text().strip()}') # Look for 2022 content in the archive page_text = soup.get_text().lower() if '2022' in page_text: print('\n‚òÖ‚òÖ‚òÖ FOUND 2022 CONTENT IN PRESS ARCHIVE! ‚òÖ‚òÖ‚òÖ') # Find all links that might be press releases - WITH PROPER VARIABLE DEFINITIONS press_release_links = [] for link in soup.find_all('a', href=True): href = link.get('href', '') text = link.get_text().strip() if href and text and len(text) > 10: # Substantial link text # CRITICAL FIX: Define variables BEFORE using them link_text_lower = text.lower() href_lower = href.lower() # Check for 2022 and acquisition-related terms has_2022 = '2022' in link_text_lower or '2022' in href_lower has_acquisition_terms = any(term in link_text_lower for term in [ 'acquisition', 'acquired', 'gift', 'donation', 'collection' ]) has_photo_terms = any(term in link_text_lower for term in [ 'photograph', 'photography', 'photo', 'image' ]) has_portrait_terms = any(term in link_text_lower for term in [ 'portrait', 'figure', 'person', 'book' ]) # Calculate relevance score relevance_score = ( has_2022 * 4 + has_acquisition_terms * 3 + has_photo_terms * 2 + has_portrait_terms * 2 ) if relevance_score >= 4: # Promising links # Construct full URL if href.startswith('/'): full_url = 'https://whitney.org' + href elif href.startswith('http'): full_url = href else: continue press_release_links.append({ 'url': full_url, 'text': text, 'relevance_score': relevance_score, 'has_2022': has_2022, 'has_acquisition_terms': has_acquisition_terms, 'has_photo_terms': has_photo_terms, 'has_portrait_terms': has_portrait_terms }) print(f'\nFound {len(press_release_links)} potentially relevant press releases') # Also look for any 2022 content directly in the archive page print('\n=== SEARCHING FOR 2022 CONTENT DIRECTLY IN ARCHIVE ===\n') # Split content into lines and find 2022 mentions archive_lines = archive_content.split('\n') relevant_2022_content = [] for i, line in enumerate(archive_lines): if '2022' in line.lower(): # Get context around the 2022 mention start = max(0, i-2) end = min(len(archive_lines), i+3) context_lines = archive_lines[start:end] # Clean and add to relevant content for context_line in context_lines: clean_line = context_line.strip() if clean_line and len(clean_line) > 10 and clean_line not in relevant_2022_content: relevant_2022_content.append(clean_line) if relevant_2022_content: print(f'Found {len(relevant_2022_content)} lines with 2022 content:') # Show the most relevant 2022 content for i, content in enumerate(relevant_2022_content[:20], 1): # Show first 20 lines # Look for acquisition and photography terms content_lower = content.lower() indicators = [] if any(term in content_lower for term in ['acquisition', 'acquired', 'gift', 'donation']): indicators.append('ACQUISITION') if any(term in content_lower for term in ['photograph', 'photography', 'photo']): indicators.append('PHOTO') if any(term in content_lower for term in ['portrait', 'figure', 'book']): indicators.append('PORTRAIT/BOOK') if indicators: indicators_str = '|'.join(indicators) print(f' {i}. [{indicators_str}] {content[:100]}...') else: print(f' {i}. {content[:100]}...') # Sort press release links by relevance score and show top results if press_release_links: press_release_links.sort(key=lambda x: x['relevance_score'], reverse=True) print('\n‚òÖ‚òÖ‚òÖ TOP RELEVANT PRESS RELEASES ‚òÖ‚òÖ‚òÖ') for i, link in enumerate(press_release_links[:8], 1): # Show top 8 indicators = [] if link['has_2022']: indicators.append('2022') if link['has_acquisition_terms']: indicators.append('ACQUISITION') if link['has_photo_terms']: indicators.append('PHOTO') if link['has_portrait_terms']: indicators.append('PORTRAIT') indicators_str = '|'.join(indicators) print(f'\n{i}. [{indicators_str}] Score: {link["relevance_score"]}') print(f' Title: {link["text"][:80]}...') print(f' URL: {link["url"]}') # Save the press release links for further analysis with open('workspace/whitney_2022_press_releases.json', 'w') as f: json.dump(press_release_links, f, indent=2) print(f'\n‚úì Press release links saved to: workspace/whitney_2022_press_releases.json') # Now try to access the most promising press releases print('\n=== ACCESSING TOP PRESS RELEASES FOR DETAILED ANALYSIS ===\n') top_releases = press_release_links[:3] # Access top 3 most relevant detailed_releases = [] headers = { 'User-Agent': 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 10.0; Win64; x64) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/91.0.4472.124 Safari/537.36' } for i, release in enumerate(top_releases, 1): print(f'Accessing release {i}: {release["text"][:50]}...') print(f'URL: {release["url"]}') try: release_response = requests.get(release['url'], headers=headers, timeout=20) if release_response.status_code == 200: print(f' ‚úì Successfully accessed (Status: {release_response.status_code})') # Parse the press release content release_soup = BeautifulSoup(release_response.content, 'html.parser') release_text = release_soup.get_text() # Look for specific acquisition and photography terms release_text_lower = release_text.lower() # Check for key terms that would indicate this is our target key_findings = { 'has_2022_date': '2022' in release_text_lower, 'has_acquisition': any(term in release_text_lower for term in [ 'acquisition', 'acquired', 'gift', 'donation', 'adds to', 'new to collection' ]), 'has_photograph': any(term in release_text_lower for term in [ 'photograph', 'photography', 'photographic', 'image' ]), 'has_portrait': any(term in release_text_lower for term in [ 'portrait', 'figure', 'person', 'subject' ]), 'has_book': 'book' in release_text_lower, 'has_holding_book': any(phrase in release_text_lower for phrase in [ 'holding a book', 'with a book', 'reading', 'book in hand' ]) } findings_score = sum(key_findings.values()) print(f' Analysis score: {findings_score}/6') print(f' Key findings: {[k for k, v in key_findings.items() if v]}') if findings_score >= 3: # Promising content print(f' ‚òÖ‚òÖ‚òÖ HIGH-RELEVANCE PRESS RELEASE! ‚òÖ‚òÖ‚òÖ') # Save the full press release release_filename = f'workspace/whitney_press_release_{i}_detailed.html' with open(release_filename, 'w', encoding='utf-8') as f: f.write(release_response.text) print(f' ‚úì Detailed release saved to: {release_filename}') # Extract key sections for analysis title_element = release_soup.find('title') h1_elements = release_soup.find_all(['h1', 'h2', 'h3']) release_analysis = { 'url': release['url'], 'title': title_element.get_text().strip() if title_element else 'No title', 'headings': [h.get_text().strip() for h in h1_elements[:5]], 'key_findings': key_findings, 'findings_score': findings_score, 'content_length': len(release_text), 'filename': release_filename } detailed_releases.append(release_analysis) # Show key content excerpts if key_findings['has_acquisition'] and key_findings['has_photograph']: print(f' üì∏ POTENTIAL PHOTOGRAPHIC ACQUISITION FOUND!') # Look for specific content about the photograph lines = release_text.split('\n') relevant_lines = [] for line in lines: line_lower = line.strip().lower() if (any(term in line_lower for term in ['photograph', 'portrait', 'book']) and len(line.strip()) > 20): relevant_lines.append(line.strip()) if relevant_lines: print(f' Key content excerpts:') for excerpt in relevant_lines[:3]: # Show top 3 excerpts print(f' "{excerpt[:100]}..."') else: print(f' ‚úó Failed to access (Status: {release_response.status_code})') except Exception as e: print(f' ‚úó Error accessing release: {str(e)}') time.sleep(2) # Be respectful to servers print() # Save detailed analysis if detailed_releases: with open('workspace/whitney_2022_detailed_press_analysis.json', 'w') as f: json.dump(detailed_releases, f, indent=2) print(f'‚úì Detailed press release analysis saved to: workspace/whitney_2022_detailed_press_analysis.json') # Summary of findings high_relevance_count = len([r for r in detailed_releases if r['findings_score'] >= 4]) photo_acquisition_count = len([r for r in detailed_releases if r['key_findings']['has_acquisition'] and r['key_findings']['has_photograph']]) print(f'\n=== SEARCH RESULTS SUMMARY ===') print(f'Total press releases analyzed: {len(detailed_releases)}') print(f'High-relevance releases (score >= 4): {high_relevance_count}') print(f'Potential photographic acquisitions: {photo_acquisition_count}') if photo_acquisition_count > 0: print(f'\nüéØ SUCCESS: Found potential 2022 Whitney Museum photographic acquisitions!') print(f'Next step: Review the detailed HTML files for complete information') else: print(f'\n‚ö†Ô∏è No clear photographic acquisitions with portrait/book elements found') print(f'Consider: Manual review of saved press releases for additional context') else: print('\nNo relevant press release links found in archive') else: print('\n‚ö†Ô∏è No 2022 content found in press archive') print('Archive may use different date formatting or pagination') else: print('\n‚ö†Ô∏è Unable to analyze press archive - no content available') # Create final comprehensive summary final_summary = { 'search_timestamp': datetime.now().strftime('%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S'), 'objective': 'Find Whitney Museum 2022 photographic acquisitions featuring portraits or figures with books', 'method': 'Direct access to Whitney Museum press archive with fixed variable scoping', 'archive_accessed': soup is not None, 'press_releases_found': len(press_release_links) if 'press_release_links' in locals() else 0, 'detailed_releases_analyzed': len(detailed_releases) if 'detailed_releases' in locals() else 0, 'files_created': [ f for f in os.listdir('workspace') if f.startswith('whitney') and (f.endswith('.json') or f.endswith('.html')) ] } with open('workspace/whitney_2022_final_search_summary.json', 'w') as f: json.dump(final_summary, f, indent=2) print(f'\n=== WHITNEY MUSEUM 2022 ACQUISITION SEARCH COMPLETE ===') print(f'Final summary saved to: workspace/whitney_2022_final_search_summary.json') print(f'Total files created: {len(final_summary["files_created"])}') print(f'\nAll Whitney Museum press archive content has been analyzed for 2022 photographic acquisitions.')

Python Code python
import os import requests from bs4 import BeautifulSoup import json from datetime import datetime import time import re print('=== WHITNEY MUSEUM PRESS ARCHIVE ANALYSIS - COMPLETE VARIABLE FIX ===') print('Objective: Find Whitney Museum 2022 photographic acquisition press releases') print('Focus: Properly structured link analysis with all variables defined upfront\n') # Create workspace directory if it doesn't exist if not os.path.exists('workspace'): os.makedirs('workspace') # Check if we already have the press archive saved print('=== LOADING EXISTING PRESS ARCHIVE ===\n') archive_files = [f for f in os.listdir('workspace') if 'whitney_press_archive' in f and f.endswith('.html')] if archive_files: archive_file = archive_files[0] print(f'Found existing press archive: {archive_file}') with open(f'workspace/{archive_file}', 'r', encoding='utf-8') as f: archive_content = f.read() print(f'Archive content length: {len(archive_content):,} characters') # Parse the existing archive content soup = BeautifulSoup(archive_content, 'html.parser') else: print('No existing archive found - this should not happen based on previous execution') soup = None archive_content = None if soup and archive_content: print('\n=== ANALYZING PRESS ARCHIVE FOR 2022 ACQUISITIONS ===\n') # Extract page title page_title = soup.find('title') if page_title: print(f'Page title: {page_title.get_text().strip()}') # Look for 2022 content in the archive page_text = soup.get_text().lower() if '2022' in page_text: print('\n‚òÖ‚òÖ‚òÖ FOUND 2022 CONTENT IN PRESS ARCHIVE! ‚òÖ‚òÖ‚òÖ') # Find all links - COMPLETELY RESTRUCTURED WITH PROPER VARIABLE SCOPING print('\nProcessing all links in the archive...') all_links = soup.find_all('a', href=True) print(f'Total links found: {len(all_links)}') press_release_links = [] for link_index, link in enumerate(all_links): # Get basic link information href = link.get('href', '') text = link.get_text().strip() # Skip if no substantial content if not href or not text or len(text) <= 10: continue # CRITICAL FIX: Define ALL variables at the start of each iteration link_text_lower = text.lower() href_lower = href.lower() # Now safely check for terms has_2022 = ('2022' in link_text_lower) or ('2022' in href_lower) # Check acquisition terms acquisition_terms = ['acquisition', 'acquired', 'gift', 'donation', 'collection'] has_acquisition_terms = False for term in acquisition_terms: if term in link_text_lower: has_acquisition_terms = True break # Check photo terms photo_terms = ['photograph', 'photography', 'photo', 'image'] has_photo_terms = False for term in photo_terms: if term in link_text_lower: has_photo_terms = True break # Check portrait/book terms portrait_terms = ['portrait', 'figure', 'person', 'book'] has_portrait_terms = False for term in portrait_terms: if term in link_text_lower: has_portrait_terms = True break # Calculate relevance score using explicit boolean values relevance_score = 0 if has_2022: relevance_score += 4 if has_acquisition_terms: relevance_score += 3 if has_photo_terms: relevance_score += 2 if has_portrait_terms: relevance_score += 2 # Only keep promising links if relevance_score >= 4: # Construct full URL if href.startswith('/'): full_url = 'https://whitney.org' + href elif href.startswith('http'): full_url = href else: continue press_release_links.append({ 'url': full_url, 'text': text, 'relevance_score': relevance_score, 'has_2022': has_2022, 'has_acquisition_terms': has_acquisition_terms, 'has_photo_terms': has_photo_terms, 'has_portrait_terms': has_portrait_terms, 'link_index': link_index }) print(f'\nFound {len(press_release_links)} potentially relevant press releases') # Also search for 2022 content directly in the archive text print('\n=== SEARCHING FOR 2022 CONTENT DIRECTLY IN ARCHIVE ===\n') # Split content into lines and find 2022 mentions archive_lines = archive_content.split('\n') relevant_2022_content = [] for i, line in enumerate(archive_lines): if '2022' in line.lower(): # Get context around the 2022 mention start = max(0, i-2) end = min(len(archive_lines), i+3) context_lines = archive_lines[start:end] # Clean and add to relevant content for context_line in context_lines: clean_line = context_line.strip() if clean_line and len(clean_line) > 10 and clean_line not in relevant_2022_content: relevant_2022_content.append(clean_line) if relevant_2022_content: print(f'Found {len(relevant_2022_content)} lines with 2022 content:') # Show the most relevant 2022 content for i, content in enumerate(relevant_2022_content[:20], 1): # Check for key terms in this content content_lower = content.lower() indicators = [] if any(term in content_lower for term in ['acquisition', 'acquired', 'gift', 'donation']): indicators.append('ACQUISITION') if any(term in content_lower for term in ['photograph', 'photography', 'photo']): indicators.append('PHOTO') if any(term in content_lower for term in ['portrait', 'figure', 'book']): indicators.append('PORTRAIT/BOOK') if indicators: indicators_str = '|'.join(indicators) print(f' {i}. [{indicators_str}] {content[:100]}...') else: print(f' {i}. {content[:100]}...') # Sort and display press release links if press_release_links: # Sort by relevance score press_release_links.sort(key=lambda x: x['relevance_score'], reverse=True) print('\n‚òÖ‚òÖ‚òÖ TOP RELEVANT PRESS RELEASES ‚òÖ‚òÖ‚òÖ') for i, link in enumerate(press_release_links[:8], 1): indicators = [] if link['has_2022']: indicators.append('2022') if link['has_acquisition_terms']: indicators.append('ACQUISITION') if link['has_photo_terms']: indicators.append('PHOTO') if link['has_portrait_terms']: indicators.append('PORTRAIT') indicators_str = '|'.join(indicators) print(f'\n{i}. [{indicators_str}] Score: {link["relevance_score"]}') print(f' Title: {link["text"][:80]}...') print(f' URL: {link["url"]}') # Save the press release links with open('workspace/whitney_2022_press_releases.json', 'w') as f: json.dump(press_release_links, f, indent=2) print(f'\n‚úì Press release links saved to: workspace/whitney_2022_press_releases.json') # Access the most promising press releases print('\n=== ACCESSING TOP PRESS RELEASES FOR DETAILED ANALYSIS ===\n') top_releases = press_release_links[:3] # Top 3 most relevant detailed_releases = [] headers = { 'User-Agent': 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 10.0; Win64; x64) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/91.0.4472.124 Safari/537.36' } for i, release in enumerate(top_releases, 1): print(f'Accessing release {i}: {release["text"][:50]}...') print(f'URL: {release["url"]}') try: release_response = requests.get(release['url'], headers=headers, timeout=20) if release_response.status_code == 200: print(f' ‚úì Successfully accessed (Status: {release_response.status_code})') # Parse the press release content release_soup = BeautifulSoup(release_response.content, 'html.parser') release_text = release_soup.get_text() release_text_lower = release_text.lower() # Check for key acquisition and photography terms key_findings = { 'has_2022_date': '2022' in release_text_lower, 'has_acquisition': any(term in release_text_lower for term in [ 'acquisition', 'acquired', 'gift', 'donation', 'adds to', 'new to collection' ]), 'has_photograph': any(term in release_text_lower for term in [ 'photograph', 'photography', 'photographic', 'image' ]), 'has_portrait': any(term in release_text_lower for term in [ 'portrait', 'figure', 'person', 'subject' ]), 'has_book': 'book' in release_text_lower, 'has_holding_book': any(phrase in release_text_lower for phrase in [ 'holding a book', 'with a book', 'reading', 'book in hand' ]) } findings_score = sum(key_findings.values()) print(f' Analysis score: {findings_score}/6') active_findings = [k for k, v in key_findings.items() if v] print(f' Key findings: {active_findings}') if findings_score >= 3: # High-relevance content print(f' ‚òÖ‚òÖ‚òÖ HIGH-RELEVANCE PRESS RELEASE! ‚òÖ‚òÖ‚òÖ') # Save the full press release release_filename = f'workspace/whitney_press_release_{i}_detailed.html' with open(release_filename, 'w', encoding='utf-8') as f: f.write(release_response.text) print(f' ‚úì Detailed release saved to: {release_filename}') # Extract key information title_element = release_soup.find('title') h1_elements = release_soup.find_all(['h1', 'h2', 'h3']) release_analysis = { 'url': release['url'], 'title': title_element.get_text().strip() if title_element else 'No title', 'headings': [h.get_text().strip() for h in h1_elements[:5]], 'key_findings': key_findings, 'findings_score': findings_score, 'content_length': len(release_text), 'filename': release_filename } detailed_releases.append(release_analysis) # Extract key content about photographs if key_findings['has_acquisition'] and key_findings['has_photograph']: print(f' üì∏ POTENTIAL PHOTOGRAPHIC ACQUISITION FOUND!') # Look for specific content about the photograph lines = release_text.split('\n') relevant_lines = [] for line in lines: line_stripped = line.strip() line_lower = line_stripped.lower() # Look for lines mentioning photographs, portraits, or books if (any(term in line_lower for term in ['photograph', 'portrait', 'book']) and len(line_stripped) > 20): relevant_lines.append(line_stripped) if relevant_lines: print(f' Key content excerpts:') for excerpt in relevant_lines[:3]: print(f' "{excerpt[:100]}..."') else: print(f' ‚úó Failed to access (Status: {release_response.status_code})') except Exception as e: print(f' ‚úó Error accessing release: {str(e)}') time.sleep(2) # Be respectful to servers print() # Save detailed analysis if detailed_releases: with open('workspace/whitney_2022_detailed_press_analysis.json', 'w') as f: json.dump(detailed_releases, f, indent=2) print(f'‚úì Detailed press release analysis saved to: workspace/whitney_2022_detailed_press_analysis.json') # Summary of findings high_relevance_count = len([r for r in detailed_releases if r['findings_score'] >= 4]) photo_acquisition_count = len([r for r in detailed_releases if r['key_findings']['has_acquisition'] and r['key_findings']['has_photograph']]) print(f'\n=== SEARCH RESULTS SUMMARY ===') print(f'Total press releases analyzed: {len(detailed_releases)}') print(f'High-relevance releases (score >= 4): {high_relevance_count}') print(f'Potential photographic acquisitions: {photo_acquisition_count}') if photo_acquisition_count > 0: print(f'\nüéØ SUCCESS: Found potential 2022 Whitney Museum photographic acquisitions!') print(f'Review the detailed HTML files for complete information about:') for release in detailed_releases: if (release['key_findings']['has_acquisition'] and release['key_findings']['has_photograph']): print(f' - {release["title"]}') print(f' File: {release["filename"]}') print(f' URL: {release["url"]}') else: print(f'\n‚ö†Ô∏è No clear photographic acquisitions with portrait/book elements found') print(f'Consider: Manual review of saved press releases for additional context') else: print('\nNo relevant press release links found in archive') print('This may indicate that 2022 acquisitions are not prominently featured in press releases') else: print('\n‚ö†Ô∏è No 2022 content found in press archive') print('Archive may use different date formatting or pagination') else: print('\n‚ö†Ô∏è Unable to analyze press archive - no content available') # Create final comprehensive summary final_summary = { 'search_timestamp': datetime.now().strftime('%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S'), 'objective': 'Find Whitney Museum 2022 photographic acquisitions featuring portraits or figures with books', 'method': 'Direct Whitney Museum press archive analysis with complete variable scoping fix', 'archive_analyzed': soup is not None, 'press_releases_found': len(press_release_links) if 'press_release_links' in locals() else 0, 'detailed_releases_analyzed': len(detailed_releases) if 'detailed_releases' in locals() else 0, 'photographic_acquisitions_found': len([r for r in detailed_releases if r['key_findings']['has_acquisition'] and r['key_findings']['has_photograph']]) if 'detailed_releases' in locals() else 0, 'files_created': [ f for f in os.listdir('workspace') if f.startswith('whitney') and (f.endswith('.json') or f.endswith('.html')) ] } with open('workspace/whitney_2022_final_search_summary.json', 'w') as f: json.dump(final_summary, f, indent=2) print(f'\n=== WHITNEY MUSEUM 2022 ACQUISITION SEARCH COMPLETE ===') print(f'Final summary saved to: workspace/whitney_2022_final_search_summary.json') print(f'Total files created: {len(final_summary["files_created"])}') print(f'\nComprehensive analysis of Whitney Museum press archive for 2022 photographic acquisitions complete.')

import os import requests from bs4 import BeautifulSoup import json from datetime import datetime import time import re print('=== WHITNEY MUSEUM PRESS ARCHIVE ANALYSIS - FINAL VARIABLE SCOPING FIX ===') print('Objective: Find Whitney Museum 2022 photographic acquisition press releases') print('Focus: Complete elimination of all variable scoping issues\n') # Create workspace directory if it doesn't exist if not os.path.exists('workspace'): os.makedirs('workspace') # Load the existing press archive print('=== LOADING EXISTING PRESS ARCHIVE ===') archive_files = [f for f in os.listdir('workspace') if 'whitney_press_archive' in f and f.endswith('.html')] if archive_files: archive_file = archive_files[0] print(f'Found existing press archive: {archive_file}') with open(f'workspace/{archive_file}', 'r', encoding='utf-8') as f: archive_content = f.read() print(f'Archive content length: {len(archive_content):,} characters') # Parse the existing archive content soup = BeautifulSoup(archive_content, 'html.parser') else: print('No existing archive found') soup = None archive_content = None if soup and archive_content: print('\n=== ANALYZING PRESS ARCHIVE FOR 2022 ACQUISITIONS ===\n') # Extract page title page_title = soup.find('title') if page_title: print(f'Page title: {page_title.get_text().strip()}') # Look for 2022 content in the archive page_text = soup.get_text().lower() if '2022' in page_text: print('\n‚òÖ‚òÖ‚òÖ FOUND 2022 CONTENT IN PRESS ARCHIVE! ‚òÖ‚òÖ‚òÖ') # Process all links with proper variable scoping print('\nProcessing all links in the archive...') all_links = soup.find_all('a', href=True) print(f'Total links found: {len(all_links)}') press_release_links = [] for link_index, link in enumerate(all_links): # Get basic link information href = link.get('href', '') text = link.get_text().strip() # Skip if no substantial content if not href or not text or len(text) <= 10: continue # Define ALL variables at the start of each iteration link_text_lower = text.lower() href_lower = href.lower() # Check for terms using explicit loops (no generator expressions) has_2022 = ('2022' in link_text_lower) or ('2022' in href_lower) # Check acquisition terms with explicit loop acquisition_terms = ['acquisition', 'acquired', 'gift', 'donation', 'collection'] has_acquisition_terms = False for term in acquisition_terms: if term in link_text_lower: has_acquisition_terms = True break # Check photo terms with explicit loop photo_terms = ['photograph', 'photography', 'photo', 'image'] has_photo_terms = False for term in photo_terms: if term in link_text_lower: has_photo_terms = True break # Check portrait/book terms with explicit loop portrait_terms = ['portrait', 'figure', 'person', 'book'] has_portrait_terms = False for term in portrait_terms: if term in link_text_lower: has_portrait_terms = True break # Calculate relevance score using explicit boolean values relevance_score = 0 if has_2022: relevance_score += 4 if has_acquisition_terms: relevance_score += 3 if has_photo_terms: relevance_score += 2 if has_portrait_terms: relevance_score += 2 # Only keep promising links if relevance_score >= 4: # Construct full URL if href.startswith('/'): full_url = 'https://whitney.org' + href elif href.startswith('http'): full_url = href else: continue press_release_links.append({ 'url': full_url, 'text': text, 'relevance_score': relevance_score, 'has_2022': has_2022, 'has_acquisition_terms': has_acquisition_terms, 'has_photo_terms': has_photo_terms, 'has_portrait_terms': has_portrait_terms, 'link_index': link_index }) print(f'\nFound {len(press_release_links)} potentially relevant press releases') # Search for 2022 content directly in archive text - WITH PROPER VARIABLE SCOPING print('\n=== SEARCHING FOR 2022 CONTENT DIRECTLY IN ARCHIVE ===\n') # Split content into lines and find 2022 mentions archive_lines = archive_content.split('\n') relevant_2022_content = [] for i, line in enumerate(archive_lines): if '2022' in line.lower(): # Get context around the 2022 mention start = max(0, i-2) end = min(len(archive_lines), i+3) context_lines = archive_lines[start:end] # Clean and add to relevant content for context_line in context_lines: clean_line = context_line.strip() if clean_line and len(clean_line) > 10 and clean_line not in relevant_2022_content: relevant_2022_content.append(clean_line) if relevant_2022_content: print(f'Found {len(relevant_2022_content)} lines with 2022 content:') # Show the most relevant 2022 content - WITH PROPER VARIABLE SCOPING for i, content in enumerate(relevant_2022_content[:20], 1): # CRITICAL FIX: Define content_lower BEFORE using it content_lower = content.lower() indicators = [] # Check for acquisition terms with explicit loop acquisition_check_terms = ['acquisition', 'acquired', 'gift', 'donation'] for term in acquisition_check_terms: if term in content_lower: indicators.append('ACQUISITION') break # Check for photo terms with explicit loop photo_check_terms = ['photograph', 'photography', 'photo'] for term in photo_check_terms: if term in content_lower: indicators.append('PHOTO') break # Check for portrait/book terms with explicit loop portrait_check_terms = ['portrait', 'figure', 'book'] for term in portrait_check_terms: if term in content_lower: indicators.append('PORTRAIT/BOOK') break if indicators: indicators_str = '|'.join(indicators) print(f' {i}. [{indicators_str}] {content[:100]}...') else: print(f' {i}. {content[:100]}...') # Sort and display press release links if press_release_links: # Sort by relevance score press_release_links.sort(key=lambda x: x['relevance_score'], reverse=True) print('\n‚òÖ‚òÖ‚òÖ TOP RELEVANT PRESS RELEASES ‚òÖ‚òÖ‚òÖ') for i, link in enumerate(press_release_links[:8], 1): indicators = [] if link['has_2022']: indicators.append('2022') if link['has_acquisition_terms']: indicators.append('ACQUISITION') if link['has_photo_terms']: indicators.append('PHOTO') if link['has_portrait_terms']: indicators.append('PORTRAIT') indicators_str = '|'.join(indicators) print(f'\n{i}. [{indicators_str}] Score: {link["relevance_score"]}') print(f' Title: {link["text"][:80]}...') print(f' URL: {link["url"]}') # Save the press release links with open('workspace/whitney_2022_press_releases.json', 'w') as f: json.dump(press_release_links, f, indent=2) print(f'\n‚úì Press release links saved to: workspace/whitney_2022_press_releases.json') # Access the most promising press releases print('\n=== ACCESSING TOP PRESS RELEASES FOR DETAILED ANALYSIS ===') top_releases = press_release_links[:3] # Top 3 most relevant detailed_releases = [] headers = { 'User-Agent': 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 10.0; Win64; x64) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/91.0.4472.124 Safari/537.36' } for i, release in enumerate(top_releases, 1): print(f'\nAccessing release {i}: {release["text"][:50]}...') print(f'URL: {release["url"]}') try: release_response = requests.get(release['url'], headers=headers, timeout=20) if release_response.status_code == 200: print(f' ‚úì Successfully accessed (Status: {release_response.status_code})') # Parse the press release content release_soup = BeautifulSoup(release_response.content, 'html.parser') release_text = release_soup.get_text() release_text_lower = release_text.lower() # Check for key acquisition and photography terms with explicit loops key_findings = { 'has_2022_date': '2022' in release_text_lower, 'has_acquisition': False, 'has_photograph': False, 'has_portrait': False, 'has_book': 'book' in release_text_lower, 'has_holding_book': False } # Check acquisition terms with explicit loop acquisition_check = ['acquisition', 'acquired', 'gift', 'donation', 'adds to', 'new to collection'] for term in acquisition_check: if term in release_text_lower: key_findings['has_acquisition'] = True break # Check photograph terms with explicit loop photo_check = ['photograph', 'photography', 'photographic', 'image'] for term in photo_check: if term in release_text_lower: key_findings['has_photograph'] = True break # Check portrait terms with explicit loop portrait_check = ['portrait', 'figure', 'person', 'subject'] for term in portrait_check: if term in release_text_lower: key_findings['has_portrait'] = True break # Check holding book phrases with explicit loop holding_book_check = ['holding a book', 'with a book', 'reading', 'book in hand'] for phrase in holding_book_check: if phrase in release_text_lower: key_findings['has_holding_book'] = True break findings_score = sum(key_findings.values()) print(f' Analysis score: {findings_score}/6') active_findings = [k for k, v in key_findings.items() if v] print(f' Key findings: {active_findings}') if findings_score >= 3: # High-relevance content print(f' ‚òÖ‚òÖ‚òÖ HIGH-RELEVANCE PRESS RELEASE! ‚òÖ‚òÖ‚òÖ') # Save the full press release release_filename = f'workspace/whitney_press_release_{i}_detailed.html' with open(release_filename, 'w', encoding='utf-8') as f: f.write(release_response.text) print(f' ‚úì Detailed release saved to: {release_filename}') # Extract key information title_element = release_soup.find('title') h1_elements = release_soup.find_all(['h1', 'h2', 'h3']) release_analysis = { 'url': release['url'], 'title': title_element.get_text().strip() if title_element else 'No title', 'headings': [h.get_text().strip() for h in h1_elements[:5]], 'key_findings': key_findings, 'findings_score': findings_score, 'content_length': len(release_text), 'filename': release_filename } detailed_releases.append(release_analysis) # Define line_lower before using it line_lower = line_stripped.lower() # Check for relevant terms with explicit loop has_relevant_terms = False relevant_terms = ['photograph', 'portrait', 'book'] for term in relevant_terms: if term in line_lower: has_relevant_terms = True break if has_relevant_terms: relevant_lines.append(line_stripped) if relevant_lines: print(f' Key content excerpts:') for excerpt in relevant_lines[:3]: print(f' "{excerpt[:100]}..."') else: print(f' ‚úó Failed to access (Status: {release_response.status_code})') except Exception as e: print(f' ‚úó Error accessing release: {str(e)}') time.sleep(2) # [{indicators_str}] Score: {link["relevance_score"]}') print(f' Title: {link["text"][:80]}...') print(f' URL: {link["url"]}') # Save the press release links with open('workspace/whitney_2022_press_releases.json', 'w') as f: json.dump(press_release_links, f, indent=2) print(f'\n‚úì Press release links saved to: workspace/whitney_2022_press_releases.json') # Parse the press release content release_soup = BeautifulSoup(release_response.content, 'html.parser') release_text = release_soup.get_text() release_text_lower = release_text.lower() # Check for key acquisition and photography terms with explicit loops key_findings = { 'has_2022_date': '2022' in release_text_lower, 'has_acquisition': False, 'has_photograph': False, 'has_portrait': False, 'has_book': 'book' in release_text_lower, 'has_holding_book': False } # Check acquisition terms with explicit loop acquisition_check = ['acquisition', 'acquired', 'gift', 'donation', 'adds to', 'new to collection'] for term in acquisition_check: if term in release_text_lower: key_findings['has_acquisition'] = True break # Check photograph terms with explicit loop photo_check = ['photograph', 'photography', 'photographic', 'image'] for term in photo_check: if term in release_text_lower: key_findings['has_photograph'] = True break # Check portrait terms with explicit loop portrait_check = ['portrait', 'figure', 'person', 'subject'] for term in portrait_check: if term in release_text_lower: key_findings['has_portrait'] = True break # Check holding book phrases with explicit loop holding_book_check = ['holding a book', 'with a book', 'reading', 'book in hand'] for phrase in holding_book_check: if phrase in release_text_lower: key_findings['has_holding_book'] = True break findings_score = sum(key_findings.values()) print(f' Analysis score: {findings_score}/6') active_findings = [k for k, v in key_findings.items() if v] print(f' Key findings: {active_findings}') if findings_score >= 3: # High-relevance content print(f' ‚òÖ‚òÖ‚òÖ HIGH-RELEVANCE PRESS RELEASE! ‚òÖ‚òÖ‚òÖ') # Save the full press release release_filename = f'workspace/whitney_press_release_{i}_detailed.html' with open(release_filename, 'w', encoding='utf-8') as f: f.write(release_response.text) print(f' ‚úì Detailed release saved to: {release_filename}') # Extract key information title_element = release_soup.find('title') h1_elements = release_soup.find_all(['h1', 'h2', 'h3']) release_analysis = { 'url': release['url'], 'title': title_element.get_text().strip() if title_element else 'No title', 'headings': [h.get_text().strip() for h in h1_elements[:5]], 'key_findings': key_findings, 'findings_score': findings_score, 'content_length': len(release_text), 'filename': release_filename } detailed_releases.append(release_analysis) # import os import requests from bs4 import BeautifulSoup import json from datetime import datetime import time print('=== WHITNEY MUSEUM 2022 PHOTOGRAPHIC ACQUISITIONS - COMPREHENSIVE GOOGLE SEARCH ===') print('Objective: Find Whitney Museum press releases about 2022 photographic acquisitions') print('Focus: Targeted Google searches for press releases featuring portraits or figures with books\n') # Prepare API request parameters params = { "q": query, "api_key": api_key, "engine": "google", "google_domain": "google.com", "safe": "off", "num": 10, "tbs": "cdr:1,cd_min:1/1/2022,cd_max:12/31/2022" # Restrict to 2022 } try: response = requests.get("https://serpapi.com/search.json", params=params) if response.status_code == 200: results = response.json() if results.get("organic_results"): print(f' Found {len(results["organic_results"])} results') # Process and analyze each result for j, result in enumerate(results['organic_results'], 1): result_info = { 'query_number': i, 'result_number': j, 'title': result.get('title', 'No title'), 'link': result.get('link', 'No link'), 'snippet': result.get('snippet', 'No snippet'), 'is_whitney_official': 'whitney.org' in result.get('link', '').lower(), 'is_press_release': 'press' in result.get('link', '').lower() or 'press' in result.get('title', '').lower(), 'mentions_2022': '2022' in (result.get('title', '') + ' ' + result.get('snippet', '')).lower(), 'mentions_acquisition': any(term in (result.get('title', '') + ' ' + result.get('snippet', '')).lower() for term in ['acquisition', 'acquired', 'gift', 'donation']), 'mentions_photograph': any(term in (result.get('title', '') + ' ' + result.get('snippet', '')).lower() for term in ['photograph', 'photography', 'photo']), 'mentions_portrait': any(term in (result.get('title', '') + ' ' + result.get('snippet', '')).lower() for term in ['portrait', 'figure', 'person', 'book']) } # Calculate relevance score relevance_score = ( result_info['is_whitney_official'] * 5 + result_info['is_press_release'] * 4 + result_info['mentions_2022'] * 3 + result_info['mentions_acquisition'] * 3 + result_info['mentions_photograph'] * 2 + result_info['mentions_portrait'] * 2 ) result_info['relevance_score'] = relevance_score all_search_results.append(result_info) # Highlight high-relevance results if relevance_score >= 10: print(f' ‚òÖ‚òÖ‚òÖ HIGH-RELEVANCE RESULT {j}: Score {relevance_score}') print(f' Title: {result_info["title"][:80]}...') print(f' Link: {result_info["link"]}') print(f' Snippet: {result_info["snippet"][:100]}...') if result_info['is_whitney_official']: whitney_specific_results.append(result_info) elif result_info['is_whitney_official']: print(f' ‚òÖ WHITNEY OFFICIAL RESULT {j}: Score {relevance_score}') print(f' Title: {result_info["title"][:60]}...') print(f' Link: {result_info["link"]}') whitney_specific_results.append(result_info) else: print(f' Result {j}: {result_info["title"][:50]}... | Score: {relevance_score}') else: print(f' No organic results found') else: print(f' API Error: {response.status_code} - {response.text[:100]}...') except Exception as e: print(f' Exception during search: {str(e)}') print() # Space between queries time.sleep(1) # Rate limiting print(f'\n=== SEARCH RESULTS SUMMARY ===\n') print(f'Total results collected: {len(all_search_results)}') print(f'Whitney Museum official results: {len(whitney_specific_results)}') # Sort all results by relevance score all_search_results.sort(key=lambda x: x['relevance_score'], reverse=True) top_results = all_search_results[:10] # Top 10 most relevant print(f'\n=== TOP 10 MOST RELEVANT RESULTS ===\n') for i, result in enumerate(top_results, 1): indicators = [] if result['is_whitney_official']: indicators.append('WHITNEY.ORG') if result['is_press_release']: indicators.append('PRESS') if result['mentions_2022']: indicators.append('2022') if result['mentions_acquisition']: indicators.append('ACQUISITION') if result['mentions_photograph']: indicators.append('PHOTO') if result['mentions_portrait']: indicators.append('PORTRAIT') indicators_str = '|'.join(indicators) print(f'{i}. [{indicators_str}] Score: {result["relevance_score"]}') print(f' Title: {result["title"]}') print(f' Link: {result["link"]}') print(f' Snippet: {result["snippet"][:150]}...') print() # Now try to access the most promising Whitney Museum results if whitney_specific_results: print(f'\n=== ACCESSING WHITNEY MUSEUM OFFICIAL RESULTS ===\n') # Parse the page content soup = BeautifulSoup(page_response.content, 'html.parser') page_text = soup.get_text() page_text_lower = page_text.lower() # Analyze content for key acquisition and photography terms content_analysis = { 'has_2022_date': '2022' in page_text_lower, 'has_acquisition_terms': any(term in page_text_lower for term in [ 'acquisition', 'acquired', 'gift', 'donation', 'new to collection', 'adds to' ]), 'has_photograph_terms': any(term in page_text_lower for term in [ 'photograph', 'photography', 'photographic', 'image' ]), 'has_portrait_terms': any(term in page_text_lower for term in [ 'portrait', 'figure', 'person', 'subject' ]), 'has_book_terms': any(term in page_text_lower for term in [ 'book', 'reading', 'holding' ]), 'has_specific_book_context': any(phrase in page_text_lower for phrase in [ 'holding a book', 'with a book', 'reading a book', 'book in hand' ]) } analysis_score = sum(content_analysis.values()) print(f' Content analysis score: {analysis_score}/6') active_terms = [k for k, v in content_analysis.items() if v] print(f' Found terms: {active_terms}') if analysis_score >= 4: # High-relevance content print(f' ‚òÖ‚òÖ‚òÖ HIGH-RELEVANCE WHITNEY CONTENT! ‚òÖ‚òÖ‚òÖ') # Save the full page content page_filename = f'workspace/whitney_2022_acquisition_{i}.html' with open(page_filename, 'w', encoding='utf-8') as f: f.write(page_response.text) print(f' ‚úì Page content saved to: {page_filename}') # import os import requests from bs4 import BeautifulSoup import json from datetime import datetime import time print('=== WHITNEY MUSEUM 2022 PHOTOGRAPHIC ACQUISITIONS - COMPREHENSIVE GOOGLE SEARCH ===') print('Objective: Find Whitney Museum press releases about 2022 photographic acquisitions') print('Focus: Targeted Google searches for press releases featuring portraits or figures with books\n') # Create workspace directory if it doesn't exist if not os.path.exists('workspace'): os.makedirs('workspace') # First, inspect existing search results to understand what we already have print('=== INSPECTING EXISTING SEARCH DATA ===\n') # Look for existing search summary files summary_files = [f for f in os.listdir('workspace') if 'search_summary' in f and f.endswith('.json')] if summary_files: print(f'Found existing search summary files: {len(summary_files)}') for summary_file in summary_files[:3]: # Show first 3 files print(f' - {summary_file}') # Inspect the structure first with open(f'workspace/{summary_file}', 'r') as f: try: summary_data = json.load(f) print(f' Keys: {list(summary_data.keys()) if isinstance(summary_data, dict) else "List data"}') if isinstance(summary_data, dict) and 'files_created' in summary_data: files_count = len(summary_data['files_created']) if isinstance(summary_data['files_created'], list) else 'Unknown' print(f' Files created: {files_count}') except Exception as e: print(f' Error reading file: {e}') print() # Get SerpAPI key from environment api_key = os.getenv("SERPAPI_API_KEY") if not api_key: print('Error: SERPAPI_API_KEY not found in environment variables') print('Cannot proceed with Google Search API calls') else: print(f'API key found: {api_key[:8]}...') # Comprehensive search queries targeting Whitney Museum 2022 photographic acquisitions search_queries = [ 'Whitney Museum "2022" "acquisition" "photograph" "portrait" press release', 'site:whitney.org "press release" "2022" "acquired" "photograph" "figure"', 'Whitney Museum "new acquisition" "2022" "photography" "book" press', '"Whitney Museum" "2022" "gift" "donation" "photograph" "portrait"', 'Whitney Museum press release 2022 "photographic work" "figure with book"', 'site:whitney.org "2022" "collection" "photograph" "person holding book"', 'Whitney Museum acquisition announcement 2022 photography portrait', '"Whitney Museum of American Art" "2022" "acquired" "photograph" press' ] print(f'Executing {len(search_queries)} targeted search queries...\n') all_search_results = [] whitney_specific_results = [] for i, query in enumerate(search_queries, 1): print(f'Query {i}: {query}') # Prepare API request parameters params = { "q": query, "api_key": api_key, "engine": "google", "google_domain": "google.com", "safe": "off", "num": 10, "tbs": "cdr:1,cd_min:1/1/2022,cd_max:12/31/2022" # Restrict to 2022 } try: response = requests.get("https://serpapi.com/search.json", params=params) if response.status_code == 200: results = response.json() if results.get("organic_results"): print(f' Found {len(results["organic_results"])} results') # Process and analyze each result for j, result in enumerate(results['organic_results'], 1): result_info = { 'query_number': i, 'result_number': j, 'title': result.get('title', 'No title'), 'link': result.get('link', 'No link'), 'snippet': result.get('snippet', 'No snippet'), 'is_whitney_official': 'whitney.org' in result.get('link', '').lower(), 'is_press_release': 'press' in result.get('link', '').lower() or 'press' in result.get('title', '').lower(), 'mentions_2022': '2022' in (result.get('title', '') + ' ' + result.get('snippet', '')).lower(), 'mentions_acquisition': any(term in (result.get('title', '') + ' ' + result.get('snippet', '')).lower() for term in ['acquisition', 'acquired', 'gift', 'donation']), 'mentions_photograph': any(term in (result.get('title', '') + ' ' + result.get('snippet', '')).lower() for term in ['photograph', 'photography', 'photo']), 'mentions_portrait': any(term in (result.get('title', '') + ' ' + result.get('snippet', '')).lower() for term in ['portrait', 'figure', 'person', 'book']) } # Calculate relevance score relevance_score = ( result_info['is_whitney_official'] * 5 + result_info['is_press_release'] * 4 + result_info['mentions_2022'] * 3 + result_info['mentions_acquisition'] * 3 + result_info['mentions_photograph'] * 2 + result_info['mentions_portrait'] * 2 ) result_info['relevance_score'] = relevance_score all_search_results.append(result_info) # Highlight high-relevance results if relevance_score >= 10: print(f' ‚òÖ‚òÖ‚òÖ HIGH-RELEVANCE RESULT {j}: Score {relevance_score}') print(f' Title: {result_info["title"][:80]}...') print(f' Link: {result_info["link"]}') print(f' Snippet: {result_info["snippet"][:100]}...') if result_info['is_whitney_official']: whitney_specific_results.append(result_info) elif result_info['is_whitney_official']: print(f' ‚òÖ WHITNEY OFFICIAL RESULT {j}: Score {relevance_score}') print(f' Title: {result_info["title"][:60]}...') print(f' Link: {result_info["link"]}') whitney_specific_results.append(result_info) else: print(f' Result {j}: {result_info["title"][:50]}... | Score: {relevance_score}') else: print(f' No organic results found') else: print(f' API Error: {response.status_code} - {response.text[:100]}...') except Exception as e: print(f' Exception during search: {str(e)}') print() # Space between queries time.sleep(1) # Rate limiting print(f'\n=== SEARCH RESULTS SUMMARY ===\n') print(f'Total results collected: {len(all_search_results)}') print(f'Whitney Museum official results: {len(whitney_specific_results)}') # Sort all results by relevance score all_search_results.sort(key=lambda x: x['relevance_score'], reverse=True) top_results = all_search_results[:10] # Top 10 most relevant print(f'\n=== TOP 10 MOST RELEVANT RESULTS ===\n') for i, result in enumerate(top_results, 1): indicators = [] if result['is_whitney_official']: indicators.append('WHITNEY.ORG') if result['is_press_release']: indicators.append('PRESS') if result['mentions_2022']: indicators.append('2022') if result['mentions_acquisition']: indicators.append('ACQUISITION') if result['mentions_photograph']: indicators.append('PHOTO') if result['mentions_portrait']: indicators.append('PORTRAIT') indicators_str = '|'.join(indicators) print(f'{i}. [{indicators_str}] Score: {result["relevance_score"]}') print(f' Title: {result["title"]}') print(f' Link: {result["link"]}') print(f' Snippet: {result["snippet"][:150]}...') print() # Now try to access the most promising Whitney Museum results if whitney_specific_results: print(f'\n=== ACCESSING WHITNEY MUSEUM OFFICIAL RESULTS ===\n') # Sort Whitney results by relevance whitney_specific_results.sort(key=lambda x: x['relevance_score'], reverse=True) top_whitney_results = whitney_specific_results[:3] # Top 3 Whitney results detailed_whitney_content = [] headers = { 'User-Agent': 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 10.0; Win64; x64) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/91.0.4472.124 Safari/537.36' } for i, result in enumerate(top_whitney_results, 1): print(f'Accessing Whitney result {i}: {result["title"][:50]}...') print(f'URL: {result["link"]}') try: page_response = requests.get(result['link'], headers=headers, timeout=30) if page_response.status_code == 200: print(f' ‚úì Successfully accessed (Status: {page_response.status_code})') print(f' Content length: {len(page_response.content):,} bytes') # Parse the page content soup = BeautifulSoup(page_response.content, 'html.parser') page_text = soup.get_text() page_text_lower = page_text.lower() # Analyze content for key acquisition and photography terms content_analysis = { 'has_2022_date': '2022' in page_text_lower, 'has_acquisition_terms': any(term in page_text_lower for term in [ 'acquisition', 'acquired', 'gift', 'donation', 'new to collection', 'adds to' ]), 'has_photograph_terms': any(term in page_text_lower for term in [ 'photograph', 'photography', 'photographic', 'image' ]), 'has_portrait_terms': any(term in page_text_lower for term in [ 'portrait', 'figure', 'person', 'subject' ]), 'has_book_terms': any(term in page_text_lower for term in [ 'book', 'reading', 'holding' ]), 'has_specific_book_context': any(phrase in page_text_lower for phrase in [ 'holding a book', 'with a book', 'reading a book', 'book in hand' ]) } analysis_score = sum(content_analysis.values()) print(f' Content analysis score: {analysis_score}/6') active_terms = [k for k, v in content_analysis.items() if v] print(f' Found terms: {active_terms}') if analysis_score >= 4: # High-relevance content print(f' ‚òÖ‚òÖ‚òÖ HIGH-RELEVANCE WHITNEY CONTENT! ‚òÖ‚òÖ‚òÖ') # Save the full page content page_filename = f'workspace/whitney_2022_acquisition_{i}.html' with open(page_filename, 'w', encoding='utf-8') as f: f.write(page_response.text) print(f' ‚úì Page content saved to: {page_filename}') # Extract key sections about the acquisition title_element = soup.find('title') headings = soup.find_all(['h1', 'h2', 'h3', 'h4']) # Look for specific content about photographic works lines = page_text.split('\n') relevant_content = [] for line in lines: line_stripped = line.strip() if len(line_stripped) <= 20: continue line_lower = line_stripped.lower() # Look for lines mentioning photography and acquisition together has_photo_and_acquisition = False photo_terms = ['photograph', 'photography', 'portrait'] acquisition_terms = ['acquired', 'acquisition', 'gift', 'donation'] has_photo = any(term in line_lower for term in photo_terms) has_acquisition = any(term in line_lower for term in acquisition_terms) has_book = 'book' in line_lower if (has_photo and has_acquisition) or (has_photo and has_book): relevant_content.append(line_stripped) if relevant_content: print(f' üì∏ FOUND PHOTOGRAPHIC ACQUISITION CONTENT!') print(f' Key excerpts:') for excerpt in relevant_content[:5]: # Show top 5 excerpts print(f' "{excerpt[:120]}..."') detailed_analysis = { 'url': result['link'], 'title': title_element.get_text().strip() if title_element else 'No title', 'headings': [h.get_text().strip() for h in headings[:10]], 'content_analysis': content_analysis, 'analysis_score': analysis_score, 'relevant_excerpts': relevant_content[:10], # Top 10 relevant excerpts 'content_length': len(page_text), 'filename': page_filename } detailed_whitney_content.append(detailed_analysis) else: print(f' Lower relevance content (score: {analysis_score})') else: print(f' ‚úó Failed to access (Status: {page_response.status_code})') except Exception as e: print(f' ‚úó Error accessing page: {str(e)}') time.sleep(2) # Be respectful to servers print() # Save detailed Whitney content analysis if detailed_whitney_content: with open('workspace/whitney_2022_detailed_content_analysis.json', 'w') as f: json.dump(detailed_whitney_content, f, indent=2) print(f'‚úì Detailed Whitney content analysis saved to: workspace/whitney_2022_detailed_content_analysis.json') # Final summary of findings high_relevance_count = len([c for c in detailed_whitney_content if c['analysis_score'] >= 4]) photographic_acquisition_count = len([c for c in detailed_whitney_content if c['content_analysis']['has_acquisition_terms'] and c['content_analysis']['has_photograph_terms']]) print(f'\n=== FINAL SEARCH RESULTS ===\n') print(f'Whitney Museum pages analyzed: {len(detailed_whitney_content)}') print(f'High-relevance pages (score >= 4): {high_relevance_count}') print(f'Pages with photographic acquisition content: {photographic_acquisition_count}') if photographic_acquisition_count > 0: print(f'\nüéØ SUCCESS: Found Whitney Museum 2022 photographic acquisitions!') print(f'\nDetailed findings:') for content in detailed_whitney_content: if (content['content_analysis']['has_acquisition_terms'] and content['content_analysis']['has_photograph_terms']): print(f'\nüì∏ PHOTOGRAPHIC ACQUISITION FOUND:') print(f' Title: {content["title"]}') print(f' URL: {content["url"]}') print(f' File: {content["filename"]}') print(f' Analysis score: {content["analysis_score"]}/6') if content['relevant_excerpts']: print(f' Key content:') for excerpt in content['relevant_excerpts'][:3]: print(f' "{excerpt[:100]}..."') else: print(f'\n‚ö†Ô∏è No clear photographic acquisitions found in analyzed Whitney pages') print(f'Consider: Review saved HTML files for manual analysis') else: print(f'\n‚ö†Ô∏è No Whitney Museum official results found') print(f'Showing top non-Whitney results for reference:') for i, result in enumerate(top_results[:5], 1): if not result['is_whitney_official']: print(f' {i}. {result["title"][:60]}...') print(f' Link: {result["link"]}') print(f' Score: {result["relevance_score"]}') # Save comprehensive search results search_summary = { 'search_timestamp': datetime.now().strftime('%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S'), 'objective': 'Find Whitney Museum 2022 photographic acquisitions featuring portraits or figures with books', 'method': 'Comprehensive Google Search API with 2022 date restriction', 'queries_executed': search_queries, 'total_results': len(all_search_results), 'whitney_official_results': len(whitney_specific_results), 'detailed_content_analyzed': len(detailed_whitney_content) if 'detailed_whitney_content' in locals() else 0, 'photographic_acquisitions_found': len([c for c in detailed_whitney_content if c['content_analysis']['has_acquisition_terms'] and c['content_analysis']['has_photograph_terms']]) if 'detailed_whitney_content' in locals() else 0, 'all_results': all_search_results, 'whitney_results': whitney_specific_results, 'files_created': [ f for f in os.listdir('workspace') if f.startswith('whitney') and (f.endswith('.json') or f.endswith('.html')) ] } with open('workspace/whitney_2022_comprehensive_search_final.json', 'w') as f: json.dump(search_summary, f, indent=2) print(f'\n=== WHITNEY MUSEUM 2022 PHOTOGRAPHIC ACQUISITION SEARCH COMPLETE ===\n') print(f'Comprehensive search results saved to: workspace/whitney_2022_comprehensive_search_final.json') print(f'Total files created: {len(search_summary["files_created"])}') print(f'\nSearch completed successfully with detailed analysis of Whitney Museum official sources.')
