import os import requests from bs4 import BeautifulSoup import json from datetime import datetime import time print('=== WHITNEY MUSEUM 2022 PHOTOGRAPHIC ACQUISITIONS - ALTERNATIVE SEARCH STRATEGY ===') print('Objective: Find Whitney Museum 2022 photographic acquisitions using direct website exploration') print('Focus: Bypass API limits by directly accessing Whitney collection and exhibition pages\n') # Create workspace directory if it doesn't exist if not os.path.exists('workspace'): os.makedirs('workspace') # Since API searches are exhausted, let's explore Whitney Museum website directly print('=== DIRECT WHITNEY MUSEUM WEBSITE EXPLORATION ===') print('Strategy: Access collection, exhibition, and news pages directly\n') # Define Whitney Museum URLs to explore for 2022 acquisitions whitney_urls_to_explore = [ 'https://whitney.org/collection/works', 'https://whitney.org/exhibitions/2022', 'https://whitney.org/about/press', 'https://whitney.org/about/press/archive', 'https://whitney.org/collection/works?classification=Photography', 'https://whitney.org/about/support/donors', 'https://whitney.org/about/annual-reports' ] headers = { 'User-Agent': 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 10.0; Win64; x64) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/91.0.4472.124 Safari/537.36' } exploration_results = [] for i, url in enumerate(whitney_urls_to_explore, 1): print(f'Exploring {i}: {url}') try: response = requests.get(url, headers=headers, timeout=30) if response.status_code == 200: print(f' ‚úì Successfully accessed (Status: {response.status_code})') print(f' Content length: {len(response.content):,} bytes') # Parse the content soup = BeautifulSoup(response.content, 'html.parser') page_text = soup.get_text().lower() # Check for 2022 content has_2022 = '2022' in page_text # Check for acquisition-related terms acquisition_terms = ['acquisition', 'acquired', 'gift', 'donation', 'new to collection', 'recently acquired'] has_acquisition_content = any(term in page_text for term in acquisition_terms) # Check for photography terms photography_terms = ['photograph', 'photography', 'photographic', 'image'] has_photography_content = any(term in page_text for term in photography_terms) # Check for portrait/book terms portrait_book_terms = ['portrait', 'figure', 'person', 'book', 'reading', 'holding'] has_portrait_book_content = any(term in page_text for term in portrait_book_terms) content_analysis = { 'url': url, 'status': response.status_code, 'content_length': len(response.content), 'has_2022': has_2022, 'has_acquisition_content': has_acquisition_content, 'has_photography_content': has_photography_content, 'has_portrait_book_content': has_portrait_book_content } # Calculate relevance score relevance_score = ( has_2022 * 3 + has_acquisition_content * 3 + has_photography_content * 2 + has_portrait_book_content * 2 ) content_analysis['relevance_score'] = relevance_score print(f' Analysis: 2022={has_2022}, Acquisition={has_acquisition_content}, Photo={has_photography_content}, Portrait/Book={has_portrait_book_content}') print(f' Relevance score: {relevance_score}/10') if relevance_score >= 6: # High relevance print(f' ‚òÖ‚òÖ‚òÖ HIGH-RELEVANCE PAGE! ‚òÖ‚òÖ‚òÖ') # Save the page content page_filename = f'workspace/whitney_page_{i}_{url.split("/")[-1] or "main"}.html' with open(page_filename, 'w', encoding='utf-8') as f: f.write(response.text) print(f' ‚úì Page saved to: {page_filename}') content_analysis['filename'] = page_filename # Look for specific 2022 acquisition content if has_2022 and has_acquisition_content and has_photography_content: print(f' üì∏ POTENTIAL 2022 PHOTOGRAPHIC ACQUISITION CONTENT!') # Extract relevant lines mentioning 2022 acquisitions lines = response.text.split('\n') relevant_lines = [] for line in lines: line_stripped = line.strip() if len(line_stripped) <= 20: continue line_lower = line_stripped.lower() # Look for lines with 2022 AND acquisition/photography terms has_2022_in_line = '2022' in line_lower has_acquisition_in_line = any(term in line_lower for term in acquisition_terms) has_photo_in_line = any(term in line_lower for term in photography_terms) has_portrait_book_in_line = any(term in line_lower for term in portrait_book_terms) if (has_2022_in_line and (has_acquisition_in_line or has_photo_in_line)) or \ (has_acquisition_in_line and has_photo_in_line and has_portrait_book_in_line): relevant_lines.append(line_stripped) if relevant_lines: print(f' Key content excerpts:') for excerpt in relevant_lines[:5]: # Show top 5 excerpts print(f' "{excerpt[:120]}..."') content_analysis['relevant_excerpts'] = relevant_lines[:10] # Save top 10 elif relevance_score >= 3: # Moderate relevance print(f' ‚òÖ MODERATE RELEVANCE - Worth investigating') # Still save moderately relevant pages for potential manual review page_filename = f'workspace/whitney_page_{i}_{url.split("/")[-1] or "main"}.html' with open(page_filename, 'w', encoding='utf-8') as f: f.write(response.text) content_analysis['filename'] = page_filename exploration_results.append(content_analysis) else: print(f' ‚úó Failed to access (Status: {response.status_code})') exploration_results.append({ 'url': url, 'status': response.status_code, 'error': f'HTTP {response.status_code}' }) except Exception as e: print(f' ‚úó Error accessing page: {str(e)}') exploration_results.append({ 'url': url, 'error': str(e) }) time.sleep(2) # Be respectful to servers print() # Now let's try some specific searches within the Whitney website print('=== WHITNEY WEBSITE INTERNAL SEARCH ATTEMPTS ===') print('Attempting to access Whitney search functionality for 2022 acquisitions\n') # Try Whitney's internal search if available whitney_search_urls = [ 'https://whitney.org/search?q=2022+acquisition+photograph', 'https://whitney.org/search?q=2022+gift+photography', 'https://whitney.org/search?q=acquired+2022+portrait', 'https://whitney.org/collection/works?year=2022', 'https://whitney.org/collection/works?medium=Photography&year=2022' ] for i, search_url in enumerate(whitney_search_urls, 1): print(f'Search attempt {i}: {search_url}') try: response = requests.get(search_url, headers=headers, timeout=20) if response.status_code == 200: print(f' ‚úì Search successful (Status: {response.status_code})') soup = BeautifulSoup(response.content, 'html.parser') page_text = soup.get_text().lower() # Look for search results if 'no results' in page_text or 'no matches' in page_text: print(f' No results found for this search') else: print(f' Potential results found - analyzing content...') # Check for acquisition and photography content has_acquisition = any(term in page_text for term in ['acquisition', 'acquired', 'gift', 'donation']) has_photography = any(term in page_text for term in ['photograph', 'photography', 'portrait']) has_2022 = '2022' in page_text print(f' Content analysis: 2022={has_2022}, Acquisition={has_acquisition}, Photography={has_photography}') if has_acquisition and has_photography and has_2022: print(f' ‚òÖ‚òÖ‚òÖ PROMISING SEARCH RESULTS! ‚òÖ‚òÖ‚òÖ') # Save the search results page search_filename = f'workspace/whitney_search_results_{i}.html' with open(search_filename, 'w', encoding='utf-8') as f: f.write(response.text) print(f' ‚úì Search results saved to: {search_filename}') # Look for specific work titles or artist names title_elements = soup.find_all(['h1', 'h2', 'h3', 'h4'], class_=lambda x: x and ('title' in x.lower() or 'work' in x.lower())) if title_elements: print(f' Found potential artwork titles:') for title_elem in title_elements[:3]: # Show first 3 titles title_text = title_elem.get_text().strip() if len(title_text) > 5 and len(title_text) < 200: print(f' - {title_text}') else: print(f' ‚úó Search failed (Status: {response.status_code})') except Exception as e: print(f' ‚úó Error during search: {str(e)}') time.sleep(1) print() # Analyze and summarize findings print('=== EXPLORATION RESULTS SUMMARY ===') successful_explorations = [r for r in exploration_results if r.get('status') == 200] high_relevance_pages = [r for r in exploration_results if r.get('relevance_score', 0) >= 6] potential_acquisition_pages = [r for r in exploration_results if r.get('has_2022') and r.get('has_acquisition_content') and r.get('has_photography_content')] print(f'\nPages successfully accessed: {len(successful_explorations)}') print(f'High-relevance pages (score >= 6): {len(high_relevance_pages)}') print(f'Pages with potential 2022 photographic acquisitions: {len(potential_acquisition_pages)}') if potential_acquisition_pages: print(f'\nüéØ POTENTIAL WHITNEY MUSEUM 2022 PHOTOGRAPHIC ACQUISITIONS FOUND!') print(f'\nDetailed findings:') for i, page in enumerate(potential_acquisition_pages, 1): print(f'\n{i}. Relevant page found:') print(f' URL: {page["url"]}') print(f' Relevance score: {page["relevance_score"]}/10') if 'filename' in page: print(f' Saved to: {page["filename"]}') if 'relevant_excerpts' in page: print(f' Key excerpts:') for excerpt in page['relevant_excerpts'][:3]: print(f' "{excerpt[:100]}..."') else: print(f'\n‚ö†Ô∏è No clear 2022 photographic acquisitions found in direct website exploration') print(f'\nHowever, found {len(high_relevance_pages)} high-relevance pages for manual review:') for page in high_relevance_pages: print(f' - {page["url"]} (Score: {page["relevance_score"]}/10)') if 'filename' in page: print(f' Saved to: {page["filename"]}') # Save comprehensive exploration results exploration_summary = { 'search_timestamp': datetime.now().strftime('%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S'), 'objective': 'Find Whitney Museum 2022 photographic acquisitions featuring portraits or figures with books', 'method': 'Direct Whitney Museum website exploration (API exhausted)', 'urls_explored': whitney_urls_to_explore, 'search_urls_attempted': whitney_search_urls, 'successful_explorations': len(successful_explorations), 'high_relevance_pages': len(high_relevance_pages), 'potential_acquisitions_found': len(potential_acquisition_pages), 'detailed_results': exploration_results, 'files_created': [ f for f in os.listdir('workspace') if f.startswith('whitney') and (f.endswith('.json') or f.endswith('.html')) ] } with open('workspace/whitney_2022_direct_exploration_final.json', 'w') as f: json.dump(exploration_summary, f, indent=2) print(f'\n=== WHITNEY MUSEUM 2022 DIRECT EXPLORATION COMPLETE ===') print(f'Exploration results saved to: workspace/whitney_2022_direct_exploration_final.json') print(f'Total files created: {len(exploration_summary["files_created"])}') print(f'\nDirect website exploration completed - review saved HTML files for detailed analysis.')

import os import requests from bs4 import BeautifulSoup import json from datetime import datetime import time print('=== WHITNEY MUSEUM 2022 PHOTOGRAPHIC ACQUISITIONS - ALTERNATIVE SEARCH STRATEGY ===') print('Objective: Find Whitney Museum 2022 photographic acquisitions using direct website exploration') print('Focus: Bypass API limits by directly accessing Whitney collection and exhibition pages\n') # Create workspace directory if it doesn't exist if not os.path.exists('workspace'): os.makedirs('workspace') # Since API searches are exhausted, let's explore Whitney Museum website directly print('=== DIRECT WHITNEY MUSEUM WEBSITE EXPLORATION ===') print('Strategy: Access collection, exhibition, and news pages directly\n') # Define Whitney Museum URLs to explore for 2022 acquisitions whitney_urls_to_explore = [ 'https://whitney.org/collection/works', 'https://whitney.org/exhibitions/2022', 'https://whitney.org/about/press', 'https://whitney.org/about/press/archive', 'https://whitney.org/collection/works?classification=Photography', 'https://whitney.org/about/support/donors', 'https://whitney.org/about/annual-reports' ] headers = { 'User-Agent': 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 10.0; Win64; x64) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/91.0.4472.124 Safari/537.36' } exploration_results = [] for i, url in enumerate(whitney_urls_to_explore, 1): print(f'Exploring {i}: {url}') try: response = requests.get(url, headers=headers, timeout=30) if response.status_code == 200: print(f' ‚úì Successfully accessed (Status: {response.status_code})') print(f' Content length: {len(response.content):,} bytes') # Parse the content soup = BeautifulSoup(response.content, 'html.parser') page_text = soup.get_text().lower() # Check for 2022 content has_2022 = '2022' in page_text # Check for acquisition-related terms acquisition_terms = ['acquisition', 'acquired', 'gift', 'donation', 'new to collection', 'recently acquired'] has_acquisition_content = any(term in page_text for term in acquisition_terms) # Check for photography terms photography_terms = ['photograph', 'photography', 'photographic', 'image'] has_photography_content = any(term in page_text for term in photography_terms) # Check for portrait/book terms portrait_book_terms = ['portrait', 'figure', 'person', 'book', 'reading', 'holding'] has_portrait_book_content = any(term in page_text for term in portrait_book_terms) content_analysis = { 'url': url, 'status': response.status_code, 'content_length': len(response.content), 'has_2022': has_2022, 'has_acquisition_content': has_acquisition_content, 'has_photography_content': has_photography_content, 'has_portrait_book_content': has_portrait_book_content } # Calculate relevance score relevance_score = ( has_2022 * 3 + has_acquisition_content * 3 + has_photography_content * 2 + has_portrait_book_content * 2 ) content_analysis['relevance_score'] = relevance_score print(f' Analysis: 2022={has_2022}, Acquisition={has_acquisition_content}, Photo={has_photography_content}, Portrait/Book={has_portrait_book_content}') print(f' Relevance score: {relevance_score}/10') if relevance_score >= 6: # High relevance print(f' ‚òÖ‚òÖ‚òÖ HIGH-RELEVANCE PAGE! ‚òÖ‚òÖ‚òÖ') # Save the page content page_filename = f'workspace/whitney_page_{i}_{url.split("/")[-1] or "main"}.html' with open(page_filename, 'w', encoding='utf-8') as f: f.write(response.text) print(f' ‚úì Page saved to: {page_filename}') content_analysis['filename'] = page_filename # Look for specific 2022 acquisition content if has_2022 and has_acquisition_content and has_photography_content: print(f' üì∏ POTENTIAL 2022 PHOTOGRAPHIC ACQUISITION CONTENT!') # Extract relevant lines mentioning 2022 acquisitions lines = response.text.split('\n') relevant_lines = [] for line in lines: line_stripped = line.strip() if len(line_stripped) <= 20: continue line_lower = line_stripped.lower() # Look for lines with 2022 AND acquisition/photography terms has_2022_in_line = '2022' in line_lower has_acquisition_in_line = any(term in line_lower for term in acquisition_terms) has_photo_in_line = any(term in line_lower for term in photography_terms) has_portrait_book_in_line = any(term in line_lower for term in portrait_book_terms) if (has_2022_in_line and (has_acquisition_in_line or has_photo_in_line)) or \ (has_acquisition_in_line and has_photo_in_line and has_portrait_book_in_line): relevant_lines.append(line_stripped) if relevant_lines: print(f' Key content excerpts:') for excerpt in relevant_lines[:5]: # Show top 5 excerpts print(f' "{excerpt[:120]}..."') content_analysis['relevant_excerpts'] = relevant_lines[:10] # Save top 10 elif relevance_score >= 3: # Moderate relevance print(f' ‚òÖ MODERATE RELEVANCE - Worth investigating') # Still save moderately relevant pages for potential manual review page_filename = f'workspace/whitney_page_{i}_{url.split("/")[-1] or "main"}.html' with open(page_filename, 'w', encoding='utf-8') as f: f.write(response.text) content_analysis['filename'] = page_filename exploration_results.append(content_analysis) else: print(f' ‚úó Failed to access (Status: {response.status_code})') exploration_results.append({ 'url': url, 'status': response.status_code, 'error': f'HTTP {response.status_code}' }) except Exception as e: print(f' ‚úó Error accessing page: {str(e)}') exploration_results.append({ 'url': url, 'error': str(e) }) time.sleep(2) # import os import requests from bs4 import BeautifulSoup import json from datetime import datetime import time print('=== WHITNEY MUSEUM 2022 PHOTOGRAPHIC ACQUISITIONS - DIRECT SEARCH WITH PROPER SCOPING ===') print('Objective: Find Whitney Museum press releases about 2022 photographic acquisitions') print('Focus: Direct website exploration with all variable scoping issues resolved\n') # Create workspace directory if it doesn't exist if not os.path.exists('workspace'): os.makedirs('workspace') # Since API searches are exhausted, let's explore Whitney Museum website directly print('=== DIRECT WHITNEY MUSEUM WEBSITE EXPLORATION ===') print('Strategy: Access collection, exhibition, and news pages directly\n') # Define Whitney Museum URLs to explore for 2022 acquisitions whitney_urls_to_explore = [ 'https://whitney.org/collection/works', 'https://whitney.org/exhibitions', 'https://whitney.org/about/press', 'https://whitney.org/press-releases', 'https://whitney.org/collection/works?classification=Photography', 'https://whitney.org/about/support/donors', 'https://whitney.org/about/annual-report' ] headers = { 'User-Agent': 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 10.0; Win64; x64) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/91.0.4472.124 Safari/537.36' } exploration_results = [] for i, url in enumerate(whitney_urls_to_explore, 1): print(f'Exploring {i}: {url}') try: response = requests.get(url, headers=headers, timeout=30) if response.status_code == 200: print(f' ‚úì Successfully accessed (Status: {response.status_code})') print(f' Content length: {len(response.content):,} bytes') # CRITICAL FIX: Parse the content and define page_text immediately soup = BeautifulSoup(response.content, 'html.parser') page_text = soup.get_text().lower() # Define page_text BEFORE using it # Now safely check for content with all variables properly defined has_2022 = '2022' in page_text # Check for acquisition-related terms with explicit definitions acquisition_terms = ['acquisition', 'acquired', 'gift', 'donation', 'new to collection', 'recently acquired'] has_acquisition_content = False for term in acquisition_terms: if term in page_text: has_acquisition_content = True break # Check for photography terms with explicit definitions photography_terms = ['photograph', 'photography', 'photographic', 'image'] has_photography_content = False for term in photography_terms: if term in page_text: has_photography_content = True break # Check for portrait/book terms with explicit definitions portrait_book_terms = ['portrait', 'figure', 'person', 'book', 'reading', 'holding'] has_portrait_book_content = False for term in portrait_book_terms: if term in page_text: has_portrait_book_content = True break content_analysis = { 'url': url, 'status': response.status_code, 'content_length': len(response.content), 'has_2022': has_2022, 'has_acquisition_content': has_acquisition_content, 'has_photography_content': has_photography_content, 'has_portrait_book_content': has_portrait_book_content } # Calculate relevance score using explicit boolean values relevance_score = 0 if has_2022: relevance_score += 3 if has_acquisition_content: relevance_score += 3 if has_photography_content: relevance_score += 2 if has_portrait_book_content: relevance_score += 2 content_analysis['relevance_score'] = relevance_score print(f' Analysis: 2022={has_2022}, Acquisition={has_acquisition_content}, Photo={has_photography_content}, Portrait/Book={has_portrait_book_content}') print(f' Relevance score: {relevance_score}/10') if relevance_score >= 6: # High relevance print(f' ‚òÖ‚òÖ‚òÖ HIGH-RELEVANCE PAGE! ‚òÖ‚òÖ‚òÖ') # Save the page content url_suffix = url.split('/')[-1] if url.split('/')[-1] else 'main' page_filename = f'workspace/whitney_page_{i}_{url_suffix}.html' with open(page_filename, 'w', encoding='utf-8') as f: f.write(response.text) print(f' ‚úì Page saved to: {page_filename}') content_analysis['filename'] = page_filename # Look for specific 2022 acquisition content with proper variable scoping if has_2022 and has_acquisition_content and has_photography_content: print(f' üì∏ POTENTIAL 2022 PHOTOGRAPHIC ACQUISITION CONTENT!') # Extract relevant lines mentioning 2022 acquisitions lines = response.text.split('\n') relevant_lines = [] for line in lines: line_stripped = line.strip() if len(line_stripped) <= 20: continue # Define line_lower BEFORE using it line_lower = line_stripped.lower() # Check terms with explicit loops (no generator expressions) has_2022_in_line = '2022' in line_lower has_acquisition_in_line = False for term in acquisition_terms: if term in line_lower: has_acquisition_in_line = True break has_photo_in_line = False for term in photography_terms: if term in line_lower: has_photo_in_line = True break has_portrait_book_in_line = False for term in portrait_book_terms: if term in line_lower: has_portrait_book_in_line = True break # Check if line is relevant using explicit boolean logic is_relevant_line = False if has_2022_in_line and (has_acquisition_in_line or has_photo_in_line): is_relevant_line = True elif has_acquisition_in_line and has_photo_in_line and has_portrait_book_in_line: is_relevant_line = True if is_relevant_line: relevant_lines.append(line_stripped) if relevant_lines: print(f' Key content excerpts:') for excerpt in relevant_lines[:5]: # Show top 5 excerpts print(f' "{excerpt[:120]}..."') content_analysis['relevant_excerpts'] = relevant_lines[:10] # Save top 10 elif relevance_score >= 3: # Moderate relevance print(f' ‚òÖ MODERATE RELEVANCE - Worth investigating') # Still save moderately relevant pages for potential manual review url_suffix = url.split('/')[-1] if url.split('/')[-1] else 'main' page_filename = f'workspace/whitney_page_{i}_{url_suffix}.html' with open(page_filename, 'w', encoding='utf-8') as f: f.write(response.text) content_analysis['filename'] = page_filename exploration_results.append(content_analysis) else: print(f' ‚úó Failed to access (Status: {response.status_code})') exploration_results.append({ 'url': url, 'status': response.status_code, 'error': f'HTTP {response.status_code}' }) except Exception as e: print(f' ‚úó Error accessing page: {str(e)}') exploration_results.append({ 'url': url, 'error': str(e) }) time.sleep(2) # Be respectful to servers print() # Now let's try some specific art news sources for Whitney 2022 acquisitions print('=== ART NEWS SOURCES SEARCH FOR WHITNEY 2022 ACQUISITIONS ===') print('Searching art journalism sites for Whitney acquisition announcements\n') # Art news URLs to check for Whitney acquisition coverage art_news_base_urls = [ 'https://www.artforum.com', 'https://www.artnews.com', 'https://hyperallergic.com', 'https://artcritical.com', 'https://www.artsy.net' ] # Parse content and look for Whitney mentions soup = BeautifulSoup(response.content, 'html.parser') page_text = soup.get_text().lower() # Define page_text immediately after parsing # Check for Whitney Museum mentions has_whitney = 'whitney' in page_text has_2022 = '2022' in page_text print(f' Whitney mentions: {has_whitney}, 2022 content: {has_2022}') if has_whitney and has_2022: print(f' ‚òÖ POTENTIAL WHITNEY 2022 COVERAGE!') # Save for potential manual review news_filename = f'workspace/art_news_{i}_{base_url.split("//")[1].split(".")[1]}.html' with open(news_filename, 'w', encoding='utf-8') as f: f.write(response.text) print(f' ‚úì Art news page saved to: {news_filename}') else: print(f' ‚úó Failed to access (Status: {response.status_code})') except Exception as e: print(f' ‚úó Error accessing art news site: {str(e)}') time.sleep(1) print() # Analyze and summarize findings print('=== EXPLORATION RESULTS SUMMARY ===') successful_explorations = [r for r in exploration_results if r.get('status') == 200] high_relevance_pages = [r for r in exploration_results if r.get('relevance_score', 0) >= 6] potential_acquisition_pages = [r for r in exploration_results if r.get('has_2022') and r.get('has_acquisition_content') and r.get('has_photography_content')] print(f'\nPages successfully accessed: {len(successful_explorations)}') print(f'High-relevance pages (score >= 6): {len(high_relevance_pages)}') print(f'Pages with potential 2022 photographic acquisitions: {len(potential_acquisition_pages)}') if potential_acquisition_pages: print(f'\nüéØ POTENTIAL WHITNEY MUSEUM 2022 PHOTOGRAPHIC ACQUISITIONS FOUND!') print(f'\nDetailed findings:') for i, page in enumerate(potential_acquisition_pages, 1): print(f'\n{i}. Relevant page found:') print(f' URL: {page["url"]}') print(f' Relevance score: {page["relevance_score"]}/10') if 'filename' in page: print(f' Saved to: {page["filename"]}') if 'relevant_excerpts' in page: print(f' Key excerpts:') for excerpt in page['relevant_excerpts'][:3]: print(f' "{excerpt[:100]}..."') else: print(f'\n‚ö†Ô∏è No clear 2022 photographic acquisitions found in direct website exploration') print(f'\nHowever, found {len(high_relevance_pages)} high-relevance pages for manual review:') for page in high_relevance_pages: print(f' - {page["url"]} (Score: {page["relevance_score"]}/10)') if 'filename' in page: print(f' Saved to: {page["filename"]}') # Show what we found overall print(f'\n=== OVERALL FINDINGS SUMMARY ===') print(f'Whitney Museum pages explored: {len(whitney_urls_to_explore)}') print(f'Successfully accessed pages: {len(successful_explorations)}') print(f'Art news sources checked: {len(art_news_base_urls)}') # Look at what files we have created workspace_files = [f for f in os.listdir('workspace') if f.startswith('whitney') and (f.endswith('.json') or f.endswith('.html'))] print(f'Total Whitney-related files created: {len(workspace_files)}') if workspace_files: print(f'\nFiles created for manual review:') for file in workspace_files[-10:]: # Show last 10 files print(f' - {file}') # Save comprehensive exploration results exploration_summary = { 'search_timestamp': datetime.now().strftime('%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S'), 'objective': 'Find Whitney Museum 2022 photographic acquisitions featuring portraits or figures with books', 'method': 'Direct Whitney Museum website exploration with proper variable scoping', 'urls_explored': whitney_urls_to_explore, 'art_news_sources_checked': art_news_base_urls, 'successful_explorations': len(successful_explorations), 'high_relevance_pages': len(high_relevance_pages), 'potential_acquisitions_found': len(potential_acquisition_pages), 'detailed_results': exploration_results, 'files_created': workspace_files } with open('workspace/whitney_2022_comprehensive_exploration_final.json', 'w') as f: json.dump(exploration_summary, f, indent=2) print(f'\n=== WHITNEY MUSEUM 2022 COMPREHENSIVE EXPLORATION COMPLETE ===') print(f'Exploration results saved to: workspace/whitney_2022_comprehensive_exploration_final.json') print(f'Total files created: {len(workspace_files)}') print(f'\nDirect website exploration completed successfully with proper variable scoping.') print(f'Review saved HTML files for detailed analysis of potential 2022 photographic acquisitions.')

import os import requests from bs4 import BeautifulSoup import json from datetime import datetime import time print('=== WHITNEY MUSEUM 2022 PHOTOGRAPHIC ACQUISITIONS - ART NEWS COVERAGE SEARCH ===') print('Objective: Find art journalism coverage of Whitney Museum 2022 photographic acquisitions') print('Focus: Search art news sources for Whitney acquisition announcements featuring portraits or figures with books\n') # Create workspace directory if it doesn't exist if not os.path.exists('workspace'): os.makedirs('workspace') # First, let's inspect what we already have in the workspace to understand previous findings print('=== INSPECTING EXISTING WHITNEY RESEARCH FILES ===') print('Understanding what has been found in previous searches\n') whitney_files = [f for f in os.listdir('workspace') if 'whitney' in f.lower()] print(f'Found {len(whitney_files)} Whitney-related files in workspace') # Look at the most recent comprehensive search results comprehensive_files = [f for f in whitney_files if 'comprehensive' in f and f.endswith('.json')] if comprehensive_files: latest_file = comprehensive_files[-1] # Get the most recent print(f'\nInspecting latest comprehensive search: {latest_file}') try: with open(f'workspace/{latest_file}', 'r') as f: search_data = json.load(f) print('File structure inspection:') if isinstance(search_data, dict): print(f' Main keys: {list(search_data.keys())}') if 'detailed_results' in search_data: results = search_data['detailed_results'] print(f' Detailed results: {len(results)} entries') # Show what pages were successfully accessed successful_pages = [r for r in results if r.get('status') == 200] print(f' Successfully accessed pages: {len(successful_pages)}') for page in successful_pages: print(f' - {page.get("url", "Unknown URL")} (Score: {page.get("relevance_score", "N/A")})') if 'files_created' in search_data: files_count = len(search_data['files_created']) if isinstance(search_data['files_created'], list) else 'Unknown' print(f' Files created: {files_count}') except Exception as e: print(f'Error reading comprehensive search file: {e}') print('\n' + '='*70) print('STRATEGY: Since direct Whitney searches haven\'t found specific 2022 acquisition') print('announcements, let\'s search art news archives for coverage of Whitney acquisitions') print('='*70 + '\n') # Try accessing archived art news content about Whitney Museum 2022 acquisitions # Using the Wayback Machine to find historical coverage print('=== WAYBACK MACHINE SEARCH FOR ART NEWS COVERAGE ===') print('Searching archived art news content for Whitney 2022 acquisition coverage\n') # Key art news URLs to check via Wayback Machine for 2022 Whitney coverage art_news_wayback_searches = [ { 'url': 'https://www.artnews.com/c/art-news/news/', 'date': '20220701', # July 2022 'description': 'ARTnews July 2022 - checking for Whitney acquisition coverage' }, { 'url': 'https://hyperallergic.com', 'date': '20220601', # June 2022 'description': 'Hyperallergic June 2022 - checking for Whitney coverage' }, { 'url': 'https://www.artforum.com/news', 'date': '20220801', # August 2022 'description': 'Artforum August 2022 - checking for Whitney news' } ] wayback_results = [] for i, search in enumerate(art_news_wayback_searches, 1): print(f'Wayback search {i}: {search["description"]}') print(f'Target URL: {search["url"]}') print(f'Target date: {search["date"]}') # Check if the webpage is available in the Wayback Machine api_url = f"https://archive.org/wayback/available?url={search['url']}&timestamp={search['date']}" try: avail_response = requests.get(api_url, timeout=20) if avail_response.status_code == 200: avail_data = avail_response.json() if ("archived_snapshots" in avail_data and "closest" in avail_data["archived_snapshots"] and avail_data["archived_snapshots"]["closest"]["available"]): closest = avail_data["archived_snapshots"]["closest"] archive_url = closest["url"] archive_date = closest["timestamp"] print(f' ‚úì Found archived version from {archive_date[:8]}') print(f' Archive URL: {archive_url}') # Get the archived version headers = { 'User-Agent': 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 10.0; Win64; x64) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/91.0.4472.124 Safari/537.36' } try: archive_response = requests.get(archive_url, headers=headers, timeout=30) if archive_response.status_code == 200: print(f' ‚úì Successfully accessed archived content ({len(archive_response.content):,} bytes)') # Parse the archived content soup = BeautifulSoup(archive_response.content, 'html.parser') # Remove wayback machine elements for element in soup.find_all(class_=lambda x: x and 'wayback' in x.lower()): element.decompose() page_text = soup.get_text().lower() # Check for Whitney Museum and acquisition content has_whitney = 'whitney' in page_text has_museum = 'museum' in page_text has_acquisition = False acquisition_terms = ['acquisition', 'acquired', 'gift', 'donation', 'new to collection'] for term in acquisition_terms: if term in page_text: has_acquisition = True break has_photography = False photo_terms = ['photograph', 'photography', 'photographic', 'portrait'] for term in photo_terms: if term in page_text: has_photography = True break has_book = 'book' in page_text has_2022 = '2022' in page_text print(f' Content analysis:') print(f' Whitney: {has_whitney}, Museum: {has_museum}, 2022: {has_2022}') print(f' Acquisition: {has_acquisition}, Photography: {has_photography}, Book: {has_book}') # Calculate relevance score relevance_score = ( has_whitney * 4 + has_acquisition * 3 + has_photography * 2 + has_2022 * 3 + has_book * 1 ) print(f' Relevance score: {relevance_score}/13') if relevance_score >= 6: # High relevance threshold print(f' ‚òÖ‚òÖ‚òÖ HIGH-RELEVANCE ARCHIVED CONTENT! ‚òÖ‚òÖ‚òÖ') # Save the archived content archive_filename = f'workspace/art_news_archive_{i}_{search["date"]}.html' with open(archive_filename, 'w', encoding='utf-8') as f: f.write(archive_response.text) print(f' ‚úì Archived content saved to: {archive_filename}') # Look for specific Whitney acquisition mentions if has_whitney and has_acquisition: print(f' üì∞ POTENTIAL WHITNEY ACQUISITION COVERAGE FOUND!') # Extract relevant excerpts lines = page_text.split('\n') relevant_excerpts = [] for line in lines: line_stripped = line.strip() if len(line_stripped) <= 20: continue line_lower = line_stripped.lower() # Look for lines mentioning Whitney and acquisitions has_whitney_in_line = 'whitney' in line_lower has_acquisition_in_line = False for term in acquisition_terms: if term in line_lower: has_acquisition_in_line = True break has_photo_in_line = False for term in photo_terms: if term in line_lower: has_photo_in_line = True break if (has_whitney_in_line and has_acquisition_in_line) or \ (has_whitney_in_line and has_photo_in_line): relevant_excerpts.append(line_stripped) if relevant_excerpts: print(f' Key excerpts about Whitney acquisitions:') for excerpt in relevant_excerpts[:3]: print(f' "{excerpt[:120]}..."') wayback_results.append({ 'search_info': search, 'archive_url': archive_url, 'archive_date': archive_date, 'content_analysis': { 'has_whitney': has_whitney, 'has_acquisition': has_acquisition, 'has_photography': has_photography, 'has_2022': has_2022, 'has_book': has_book, 'relevance_score': relevance_score }, 'filename': archive_filename if relevance_score >= 6 else None }) else: print(f' ‚úó Failed to access archived content (Status: {archive_response.status_code})') except Exception as e: print(f' ‚úó Error accessing archived content: {str(e)}') else: print(f' ‚úó No archived version found for {search["date"]}') else: print(f' ‚úó Error checking archive availability (Status: {avail_response.status_code})') except Exception as e: print(f' ‚úó Error during wayback search: {str(e)}') time.sleep(2) # Be respectful to archive.org print() # Now try some direct searches on art news sites for Whitney 2022 content print('=== DIRECT ART NEWS SITE SEARCHES ===') print('Searching current art news sites for Whitney 2022 acquisition coverage\n') # Try specific search URLs on art news sites art_news_search_urls = [ 'https://www.artnews.com/?s=Whitney+Museum+2022+acquisition', 'https://hyperallergic.com/?s=Whitney+2022+photography', 'https://www.artforum.com/search?q=Whitney+Museum+acquisition+2022' ] for i, search_url in enumerate(art_news_search_urls, 1): print(f'Art news search {i}: {search_url}') try: headers = { 'User-Agent': 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 10.0; Win64; x64) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/91.0.4472.124 Safari/537.36' } response = requests.get(search_url, headers=headers, timeout=20) if response.status_code == 200: print(f' ‚úì Search successful (Status: {response.status_code})') soup = BeautifulSoup(response.content, 'html.parser') page_text = soup.get_text().lower() # Check for Whitney 2022 acquisition content has_whitney = 'whitney' in page_text has_2022 = '2022' in page_text has_acquisition = False acquisition_terms = ['acquisition', 'acquired', 'gift', 'donation'] for term in acquisition_terms: if term in page_text: has_acquisition = True break has_photography = False photo_terms = ['photograph', 'photography', 'portrait'] for term in photo_terms: if term in page_text: has_photography = True break print(f' Content found: Whitney={has_whitney}, 2022={has_2022}, Acquisition={has_acquisition}, Photo={has_photography}') if has_whitney and has_2022 and (has_acquisition or has_photography): print(f' ‚òÖ‚òÖ‚òÖ POTENTIAL WHITNEY 2022 CONTENT FOUND! ‚òÖ‚òÖ‚òÖ') # Save the search results search_filename = f'workspace/art_news_search_{i}_results.html' with open(search_filename, 'w', encoding='utf-8') as f: f.write(response.text) print(f' ‚úì Search results saved to: {search_filename}') # Look for article titles or headlines headlines = soup.find_all(['h1', 'h2', 'h3'], class_=lambda x: x and ('title' in x.lower() or 'headline' in x.lower())) if not headlines: headlines = soup.find_all(['h1', 'h2', 'h3'])[:10] # Get first 10 headings if headlines: print(f' Found potential article headlines:') for headline in headlines[:5]: # Show first 5 headline_text = headline.get_text().strip() if len(headline_text) > 10 and len(headline_text) < 200: if 'whitney' in headline_text.lower(): print(f' ‚òÖ {headline_text}') else: print(f' - {headline_text}') else: print(f' ‚úó Search failed (Status: {response.status_code})') except Exception as e: print(f' ‚úó Error during art news search: {str(e)}') time.sleep(2) print() # Summarize all findings print('=== COMPREHENSIVE SEARCH RESULTS SUMMARY ===') high_relevance_wayback = [r for r in wayback_results if r.get('content_analysis', {}).get('relevance_score', 0) >= 6] whitney_acquisition_content = [r for r in wayback_results if r.get('content_analysis', {}).get('has_whitney') and r.get('content_analysis', {}).get('has_acquisition')] print(f'\nWayback Machine searches performed: {len(art_news_wayback_searches)}') print(f'High-relevance archived content found: {len(high_relevance_wayback)}') print(f'Content mentioning Whitney acquisitions: {len(whitney_acquisition_content)}') print(f'Direct art news searches performed: {len(art_news_search_urls)}') if whitney_acquisition_content: print(f'\nüéØ SUCCESS: Found art news coverage of Whitney Museum acquisitions!') print(f'\nDetailed findings:') for i, content in enumerate(whitney_acquisition_content, 1): print(f'\n{i}. Whitney acquisition coverage found:') print(f' Source: {content["search_info"]["description"]}') print(f' Archive date: {content["archive_date"][:8]}') print(f' Relevance score: {content["content_analysis"]["relevance_score"]}/13') if content.get('filename'): print(f' Saved to: {content["filename"]}') analysis = content['content_analysis'] active_terms = [k for k, v in analysis.items() if v and k != 'relevance_score'] print(f' Found terms: {active_terms}') else: print(f'\n‚ö†Ô∏è No specific Whitney Museum acquisition coverage found in art news archives') print(f'\nThis suggests that Whitney\'s 2022 photographic acquisitions featuring portraits') print(f'or figures with books may not have received prominent art journalism coverage,') print(f'or such acquisitions may not have occurred in 2022.') # Save comprehensive search results search_summary = { 'search_timestamp': datetime.now().strftime('%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S'), 'objective': 'Find Whitney Museum 2022 photographic acquisitions featuring portraits or figures with books', 'method': 'Art news coverage search via Wayback Machine and direct site searches', 'wayback_searches': art_news_wayback_searches, 'direct_searches': art_news_search_urls, 'wayback_results': wayback_results, 'high_relevance_content': len(high_relevance_wayback), 'whitney_acquisition_coverage': len(whitney_acquisition_content), 'files_created': [ f for f in os.listdir('workspace') if f.startswith(('art_news', 'whitney')) and (f.endswith('.json') or f.endswith('.html')) ] } with open('workspace/whitney_2022_art_news_comprehensive_search.json', 'w') as f: json.dump(search_summary, f, indent=2) print(f'\n=== WHITNEY MUSEUM ART NEWS COVERAGE SEARCH COMPLETE ===') print(f'Comprehensive search results saved to: workspace/whitney_2022_art_news_comprehensive_search.json') print(f'Total files created: {len(search_summary["files_created"])}') print(f'\nArt news coverage search completed - comprehensive analysis of potential Whitney 2022 acquisition coverage.')

Check for Whitney 2022 acquisition content has_whitney = 'whitney' in page_text has_2022 = '2022' in page_text has_acquisition = False acquisition_terms = ['acquisition', 'acquired', 'gift', 'donation'] for term in acquisition_terms: if term in page_text: has_acquisition = True break has_photography = False photo_terms = ['photograph', 'photography', 'portrait'] for term in photo_terms: if term in page_text: has_photography = True break print(f' Content found: Whitney={has_whitney}, 2022={has_2022}, Acquisition={has_acquisition}, Photo={has_photography}') if has_whitney and has_2022 and (has_acquisition or has_photography): print(f' ‚òÖ‚òÖ‚òÖ POTENTIAL WHITNEY 2022 CONTENT FOUND! ‚òÖ‚òÖ‚òÖ') # Save the search results search_filename = f'workspace/art_news_search_{i}_results.html' with open(search_filename, 'w', encoding='utf-8') as f: f.write(response.text) print(f' ‚úì Search results saved to: {search_filename}') # Look for article titles or headlines headlines = soup.find_all(['h1', 'h2', 'h3'], class_=lambda x: x and ('title' in x.lower() or 'headline' in x.lower())) if not headlines: headlines = soup.find_all(['h1', 'h2', 'h3'])[:10] # Get first 10 headings if headlines: print(f' Found potential article headlines:') for headline in headlines[:5]: # Show first 5 headline_text = headline.get_text().strip() if len(headline_text) > 10 and len(headline_text) < 200: if 'whitney' in headline_text.lower(): print(f' ‚òÖ {headline_text}') else: print(f' - {headline_text}') else: print(f' ‚úó Search failed (Status: {response.status_code})') except Exception as e: print(f' ‚úó Error during art news search: {str(e)}') time.sleep(2) print() # Summarize all findings print('=== COMPREHENSIVE SEARCH RESULTS SUMMARY ===') high_relevance_wayback = [r for r in wayback_results if r.get('content_analysis', {}).get('relevance_score', 0) >= 6] whitney_acquisition_content = [r for r in wayback_results if r.get('content_analysis', {}).get('has_whitney') and r.get('content_analysis', {}).get('has_acquisition')] print(f'\nWayback Machine searches performed: {len(art_news_wayback_searches)}') print(f'High-relevance archived content found: {len(high_relevance_wayback)}') print(f'Content mentioning Whitney acquisitions: {len(whitney_acquisition_content)}') print(f'Direct art news searches performed: {len(art_news_search_urls)}') if whitney_acquisition_content: print(f'\nüéØ SUCCESS: Found art news coverage of Whitney Museum acquisitions!') print(f'\nDetailed findings:') for i, content in enumerate(whitney_acquisition_content, 1): print(f'\n{i}. import os import requests from bs4 import BeautifulSoup import json from datetime import datetime import time print('=== WHITNEY MUSEUM 2022 PHOTOGRAPHIC ACQUISITIONS - FINAL COMPREHENSIVE ANALYSIS ===') print('Objective: Analyze all collected data and provide definitive findings') print('Focus: Review all search results and saved files to determine final conclusions\n') # Create workspace directory if it doesn't exist if not os.path.exists('workspace'): os.makedirs('workspace') print('=== COMPREHENSIVE REVIEW OF ALL WHITNEY MUSEUM RESEARCH FILES ===') print('Analyzing all collected data to provide final assessment\n') # Get all Whitney-related files in workspace whitney_files = [f for f in os.listdir('workspace') if 'whitney' in f.lower()] print(f'Total Whitney-related files found: {len(whitney_files)}') # Categorize files by type json_files = [f for f in whitney_files if f.endswith('.json')] html_files = [f for f in whitney_files if f.endswith('.html')] print(f'JSON summary files: {len(json_files)}') print(f'HTML content files: {len(html_files)}') # Analyze the most comprehensive search results print('\n=== ANALYZING COMPREHENSIVE SEARCH SUMMARIES ===') comprehensive_files = [f for f in json_files if 'comprehensive' in f] if comprehensive_files: print(f'Found {len(comprehensive_files)} comprehensive search files:') for file in comprehensive_files: print(f' - {file}') # Inspect the latest comprehensive search latest_comprehensive = comprehensive_files[-1] print(f'\nAnalyzing latest comprehensive search: {latest_comprehensive}') try: with open(f'workspace/{latest_comprehensive}', 'r') as f: comprehensive_data = json.load(f) print('\nFile structure inspection:') if isinstance(comprehensive_data, dict): print(f'Main keys: {list(comprehensive_data.keys())}') # Extract key findings if 'objective' in comprehensive_data: print(f'\nObjective: {comprehensive_data["objective"]}') if 'search_timestamp' in comprehensive_data: print(f'Search completed: {comprehensive_data["search_timestamp"]}') # Look for specific results about acquisitions if 'wayback_results' in comprehensive_data: wayback_results = comprehensive_data['wayback_results'] print(f'\nWayback Machine searches: {len(wayback_results)} performed') for i, result in enumerate(wayback_results, 1): if 'content_analysis' in result: analysis = result['content_analysis'] print(f' Search {i}: Relevance score {analysis.get("relevance_score", "N/A")}') if analysis.get('has_whitney') and analysis.get('has_acquisition'): print(f' ‚òÖ Found Whitney acquisition content!') if 'high_relevance_content' in comprehensive_data: high_rel = comprehensive_data['high_relevance_content'] print(f'\nHigh-relevance content found: {high_rel}') if 'whitney_acquisition_coverage' in comprehensive_data: coverage = comprehensive_data['whitney_acquisition_coverage'] print(f'Whitney acquisition coverage found: {coverage}') except Exception as e: print(f'Error analyzing comprehensive file: {e}') # Parse HTML and look for specific acquisition content soup = BeautifulSoup(html_content, 'html.parser') page_text = soup.get_text().lower() # Look for 2022 acquisition indicators has_2022 = '2022' in page_text print(f' Contains 2022: {has_2022}') if has_2022: # Show first 5 lines print(f' "{line[:100]}..."') # Look for acquisition terms acquisition_terms = ['acquired', 'acquisition', 'gift', 'donation', 'new to collection'] acquisition_mentions = [] for term in acquisition_terms: if term in page_text: acquisition_mentions.append(term) print(f' Acquisition terms found: {acquisition_mentions}') # Look for photography/portrait terms photo_terms = ['photograph', 'photography', 'portrait', 'image'] photo_mentions = [] for term in photo_terms: if term in page_text: photo_mentions.append(term) print(f' Photography terms found: {photo_mentions}') # Look for book-related terms book_terms = ['book', 'reading', 'holding'] book_mentions = [] for term in book_terms: if term in page_text: book_mentions.append(term) print(f' Book-related terms found: {book_mentions}') #
